WEBVTT

00:00:02.419 --> 00:00:04.421
[waves crashing]

00:00:29.655 --> 00:00:31.949
[engine revving]

00:00:45.671 --> 00:00:48.006
[knocking on door]

00:00:51.218 --> 00:00:53.095
Hey, Sonny. Five minutes.

00:00:58.392 --> 00:01:00.894
["Whole Lotta Love" playing]

00:01:09.278 --> 00:01:10.779
♪ You need coolin' ♪

00:01:10.863 --> 00:01:12.281
[grunts]

00:01:12.364 --> 00:01:13.907
♪ Baby, I'm not foolin' ♪

00:01:14.783 --> 00:01:19.454
♪ I'm gonna send ya
Back to schoolin' ♪

00:01:20.998 --> 00:01:25.878
♪ Way down inside
Honey, you need it ♪

00:01:26.587 --> 00:01:31.466
♪ I'm gonna give you my love
I'm gonna give you my love ♪

00:01:31.550 --> 00:01:33.635
[people chattering]

00:01:33.719 --> 00:01:37.472
♪ Want a whole lotta love
Want a whole lotta love ♪

00:01:38.432 --> 00:01:42.978
Sonny! Hey. BMW guys are over there
bitching about brake trouble.

00:01:43.061 --> 00:01:44.438
Thanks, Molly. You're a superstar.

00:01:44.521 --> 00:01:45.689
I'll see you out there.

00:01:47.107 --> 00:01:51.695
♪ All the good times
Baby, baby, I've been yearning ♪

00:01:53.071 --> 00:01:57.034
♪ Way, way down inside
Honey, you need it ♪

00:01:58.118 --> 00:02:00.996
♪ I'm gonna give you my love ♪

00:02:01.079 --> 00:02:03.248
♪ I'm gonna give you my love ♪

00:02:05.000 --> 00:02:07.461
♪ Want a whole lotta love ♪

00:02:07.544 --> 00:02:09.295
Turn my back for one minute.

00:02:09.838 --> 00:02:11.423
♪ Want a whole lotta love ♪

00:02:12.674 --> 00:02:14.801
It's all gone to shit, Sonny.

00:02:14.885 --> 00:02:16.178
Pat had to ease off.

00:02:16.261 --> 00:02:17.721
We've dropped down to seventh.

00:02:18.222 --> 00:02:22.726
If you can just hold position overnight,
hopeful sunrise catches us a break.

00:02:27.397 --> 00:02:31.318
Sonny, watch that high-speed balance.
High-speed balance.

00:02:33.904 --> 00:02:35.781
[drills whirring]

00:02:35.864 --> 00:02:37.032
How's the gearbox?

00:02:37.115 --> 00:02:38.367
It's holding up, but go easy.

00:02:39.201 --> 00:02:40.827
[breathing deeply]

00:02:42.538 --> 00:02:44.831
[breathing heavily]

00:02:58.178 --> 00:03:01.390
[commentator] The crowds may
have gone home, but the racing continues.

00:03:01.473 --> 00:03:04.935
Sonny Hayes back in the Porsche
for Peak Geico Chip Hart Racing,

00:03:05.018 --> 00:03:06.562
the midnight shift.

00:03:06.645 --> 00:03:08.063
We all know Hayes

00:03:08.146 --> 00:03:09.273
likes to light up the night,

00:03:09.356 --> 00:03:13.360
but with the BMW at the head of this pack,
he's got a massive job ahead of him.

00:03:25.706 --> 00:03:28.584
Right out of the gate,
Hayes threads the needle into turn three,

00:03:28.667 --> 00:03:29.710
moving up to fourth place.

00:03:29.793 --> 00:03:31.920
Sonny, wanna maybe pass on the straights?

00:03:32.004 --> 00:03:33.255
Just let me drive, will ya?

00:03:35.591 --> 00:03:36.800
[song continues]

00:03:36.884 --> 00:03:39.469
[commentator] Look out.
Engine trouble for the number 12.

00:03:42.139 --> 00:03:44.224
That moves Hayes up another spot.

00:03:54.651 --> 00:03:59.656
♪ You've been coolin'
Baby, I've been droolin' ♪

00:04:00.782 --> 00:04:02.743
Sweet baby Jesus. We got ten more hours.

00:04:03.327 --> 00:04:05.204
Just let Sonny do his thing.

00:04:05.287 --> 00:04:07.748
And if these first few laps
are any indication,

00:04:07.831 --> 00:04:11.293
it appears as though Sonny Hayes
may have left his brake pedal at home.

00:04:11.376 --> 00:04:13.962
♪ I'm gonna give you
Every inch of my love ♪

00:04:14.046 --> 00:04:16.297
Hayes sets his sights on the BMW.

00:04:16.380 --> 00:04:18.966
♪ Yeah, all right, let's go ♪

00:04:19.051 --> 00:04:20.636
-[grunts]
-[commentator] And he attacks.

00:04:20.719 --> 00:04:24.431
♪ Want a whole lotta love
Want a whole lotta love ♪

00:04:24.515 --> 00:04:26.642
[commentator]
Here comes Hayes on the outside.

00:04:26.725 --> 00:04:27.893
Come on, Sonny.

00:04:27.976 --> 00:04:29.895
♪ Want a whole lotta love ♪

00:04:32.314 --> 00:04:36.318
♪ Way down inside ♪

00:04:39.821 --> 00:04:41.156
[pants]

00:04:41.240 --> 00:04:47.412
♪ Love ♪

00:04:52.709 --> 00:04:56.505
♪ My, my, my, my
My, my, my, my ♪

00:04:56.588 --> 00:04:59.716
[commentator] The BMW late on the brakes.
He's in the grass.

00:05:04.429 --> 00:05:05.597
Can Hayes hang on?

00:05:07.182 --> 00:05:08.183
And he does.

00:05:08.267 --> 00:05:09.601
Goddamn!

00:05:10.269 --> 00:05:12.229
See that? That's how you race, boys.

00:05:12.312 --> 00:05:15.274
When you get back in that car,
you need to do the same goddamn thing.

00:05:15.357 --> 00:05:19.903
♪ Hey, oh, ooh ♪

00:05:19.987 --> 00:05:23.365
[commentator] Sonny Hayes brings it
into pit lane after an epic third stint

00:05:23.448 --> 00:05:25.742
that puts Chip Hart Racing out in front.

00:05:26.243 --> 00:05:29.037
Now, it's up to Cale Kelso
to hang on to that lead.

00:05:29.121 --> 00:05:30.789
[Kelso] Thanks for the head start, Chief.

00:05:34.084 --> 00:05:36.628
Hey. Lose that lead, I'll kill ya.

00:05:39.298 --> 00:05:44.344
♪ Shake for me, girl
I wanna be your backdoor man ♪

00:05:44.428 --> 00:05:45.596
[BMW driver] Hayes!

00:05:46.180 --> 00:05:47.556
Hey, dirt bag!

00:05:49.433 --> 00:05:51.977
-Gonna run me off the track, Hayes?
-[crew member] It's not worth it.

00:05:52.060 --> 00:05:55.731
You think I don't know where to find you?
Screw you!

00:05:57.232 --> 00:05:58.400
Let go of me!

00:05:59.401 --> 00:06:00.819
♪ Oh, oh, oh ♪

00:06:00.903 --> 00:06:02.321
Hey. Attaboy, Sonny.

00:06:03.363 --> 00:06:05.532
Thanks. Don't wake me if we lose.

00:06:06.074 --> 00:06:09.286
[crowd cheering]

00:06:09.953 --> 00:06:11.622
[laughs]

00:06:13.582 --> 00:06:15.292
[cheers]

00:06:15.375 --> 00:06:17.085
♪ Keep it coolin', baby ♪

00:06:17.169 --> 00:06:18.712
[song fades]

00:06:20.506 --> 00:06:23.300
Sonny Hayes,
I believe you forgot something.

00:06:24.259 --> 00:06:25.385
Bag's full, Chip.

00:06:26.261 --> 00:06:27.262
Seriously?

00:06:27.930 --> 00:06:30.557
Your first win at Daytona.
Don't you even want to touch it?

00:06:30.641 --> 00:06:31.642
-Ooh, bad luck.
-Come on.

00:06:31.725 --> 00:06:33.644
-Just touch it.
-[laughing] No. Hey.

00:06:34.728 --> 00:06:36.813
I will take that bonus check though.

00:06:38.106 --> 00:06:42.277
Sonny. Sonny! Just hear me out.

00:06:43.111 --> 00:06:44.488
Look, I wanna bring you on board.

00:06:44.571 --> 00:06:45.989
-[laughs]
-You're CHR family now.

00:06:46.073 --> 00:06:47.866
Right here, next year, let's run it back.

00:06:47.950 --> 00:06:49.826
We did it, man. Deal's a deal.

00:06:49.910 --> 00:06:52.079
I-I know what a deal is.

00:06:53.622 --> 00:06:55.374
So that's it? One and done?

00:06:55.457 --> 00:06:58.043
I appreciate the seat, Chip. I really do.

00:06:58.126 --> 00:06:59.628
What kind of way is that to race?

00:07:00.128 --> 00:07:02.047
You just spend your whole life
starting over, man.

00:07:02.130 --> 00:07:03.131
You take care.

00:07:04.299 --> 00:07:06.218
-[engine starts]
-I'll see you down the road.

00:07:13.976 --> 00:07:16.103
Hey! Don't you want the watch?

00:07:16.186 --> 00:07:17.271
[Sonny] Got one!

00:07:17.354 --> 00:07:18.939
["Round and Round" playing on radio]

00:07:19.022 --> 00:07:20.774
[radio presenter 1]
WHOG, Ormond-by-the-Sea.

00:07:20.858 --> 00:07:22.193
[radio presenter 2]
Proud to be locally owned.

00:07:22.276 --> 00:07:23.735
A Southern Stone station.

00:07:23.819 --> 00:07:25.153
The world's most famous rock…

00:07:25.237 --> 00:07:28.448
[radio presenter 1] …from the world's
most famous beach, we are…

00:07:28.532 --> 00:07:30.242
[radio presenter 2]
…Daytona's rock station…

00:07:30.325 --> 00:07:32.205
[radio presenter 1]
…ninety-five seven, the Hog.

00:07:33.245 --> 00:07:36.874
♪ Out on the streets
That's where we'll meet ♪

00:07:36.957 --> 00:07:40.878
♪ You make the night
I always cross the line ♪

00:07:40.961 --> 00:07:44.256
♪ Tightened our belts
Abused ourselves ♪

00:07:44.339 --> 00:07:45.925
♪ Get in our way
We'll put you on your shelf ♪

00:07:46.008 --> 00:07:47.217
[timer buzzes]

00:07:48.135 --> 00:07:51.305
Sorry, can I use your phone
for a second, please?

00:07:51.388 --> 00:07:52.556
It's not working.

00:07:52.639 --> 00:07:54.474
Um, no.

00:07:57.311 --> 00:08:00.564
You know, you remind me of this friend
I used to have.

00:08:00.647 --> 00:08:01.648
Which friend?

00:08:02.149 --> 00:08:03.400
Friend who dressed better.

00:08:04.651 --> 00:08:06.028
This is a Gucci suit.

00:08:06.111 --> 00:08:07.237
So's this.

00:08:07.321 --> 00:08:09.239
Huh. What did your friend do?

00:08:09.323 --> 00:08:10.324
Drove cars.

00:08:10.407 --> 00:08:12.159
-Was he fast?
-Wasn't slow.

00:08:12.242 --> 00:08:15.287
-Did he win?
-[inhales sharply] Yeah, he did.

00:08:17.497 --> 00:08:19.833
-Come here, you son of a bitch.
-[laughs]

00:08:19.917 --> 00:08:20.918
Oh, God.

00:08:21.001 --> 00:08:22.711
[friend] Are you thinking Baja?

00:08:22.794 --> 00:08:24.880
[Sonny] Yeah. New day, new challenge.

00:08:24.963 --> 00:08:27.258
That's exactly what I said to myself
when I bought Apex GP.

00:08:27.341 --> 00:08:29.968
-["The Stroke" playing on radio]
-[groans]

00:08:30.052 --> 00:08:31.512
How deep in the hole are you?

00:08:32.679 --> 00:08:35.057
I'll tell you,
but you have to promise not to laugh.

00:08:35.890 --> 00:08:36.933
Shoot.

00:08:38.684 --> 00:08:40.145
350…

00:08:41.647 --> 00:08:43.190
Million.

00:08:45.609 --> 00:08:46.693
Don't laugh.

00:08:48.153 --> 00:08:49.321
Impressive.

00:08:50.531 --> 00:08:51.740
Well, been fun?

00:08:51.823 --> 00:08:53.992
Oh, yeah. Absolutely.

00:08:54.076 --> 00:08:55.244
What's the problem then?

00:08:55.327 --> 00:08:58.664
Problem is two seasons and a half,
zero points.

00:08:58.747 --> 00:09:00.874
My best driver left for another team.

00:09:00.958 --> 00:09:03.210
He said the car was a shitbox.

00:09:03.293 --> 00:09:04.294
[laughs]

00:09:04.378 --> 00:09:06.046
The team is in last place.

00:09:06.129 --> 00:09:07.673
My number two's a rookie.

00:09:08.173 --> 00:09:09.633
And the season's half over.

00:09:09.716 --> 00:09:11.260
-How many races left?
-Nine.

00:09:11.760 --> 00:09:13.720
And if we don't turn it around,
I lose the team.

00:09:13.804 --> 00:09:15.305
-What?
-Mmm.

00:09:15.389 --> 00:09:16.515
But you own the team.

00:09:17.140 --> 00:09:21.228
No race wins in your first three seasons,
the board can force a sale.

00:09:22.729 --> 00:09:24.648
Man, sounds like you need a new board.

00:09:26.275 --> 00:09:27.484
I need a new driver.

00:09:32.906 --> 00:09:35.284
[laughs]

00:09:36.243 --> 00:09:37.661
[Sonny] You got F2. You got F3.

00:09:37.744 --> 00:09:40.247
You got an entire assembly line of kids
raised on the simulator.

00:09:40.330 --> 00:09:43.458
No, I don't have time for some kid
to learn how to come in tenth. I don't.

00:09:43.542 --> 00:09:46.211
Well, you don't just walk off the street
and pilot a rocket.

00:09:46.295 --> 00:09:48.881
Yes, you can if you've done it before.
That's the whole point.

00:09:48.964 --> 00:09:53.010
Louis Chiron was 57 years old
when he won the Monaco Grand Prix.

00:09:53.093 --> 00:09:55.429
-Louis who?
-Philippe Étancelin, 56 years old.

00:09:55.512 --> 00:09:56.806
You just Googled these names, didn't you?

00:09:56.889 --> 00:10:00.517
Some people look at Sonny Hayes,
they see a guy who lives in a van,

00:10:00.601 --> 00:10:02.644
a gambling junkie who missed his shot.

00:10:02.728 --> 00:10:04.855
Wow, Ruben, you are really selling this.

00:10:04.938 --> 00:10:07.065
But I see a guy who makes teams better.

00:10:07.149 --> 00:10:09.151
-I see experience. I see know-how.
-Mmm.

00:10:09.234 --> 00:10:10.361
[laughs] You're off your meds.

00:10:10.444 --> 00:10:13.989
My rookie's a phenomenal talent.
Phenomenal. But he's young.

00:10:14.489 --> 00:10:15.949
You know what he lacks? Maturity.

00:10:16.700 --> 00:10:18.243
You plus him?

00:10:18.327 --> 00:10:20.495
Boom. I got a team.

00:10:20.579 --> 00:10:22.581
[Sonny]
All right. Let's say I'm the next Louis…

00:10:22.664 --> 00:10:24.499
-Chiron. Mm-hmm.
-Him.

00:10:25.501 --> 00:10:28.086
The problem is it's not just the driver,
it's the car.

00:10:28.837 --> 00:10:30.589
I've followed your season, Ruben.

00:10:30.672 --> 00:10:32.007
"Shitbox" is being kind.

00:10:32.090 --> 00:10:33.300
I knew you were watching.

00:10:33.383 --> 00:10:36.136
What if I told you
we get an upgrade package this weekend?

00:10:36.220 --> 00:10:38.013
-Six months in development...
-Ruben…

00:10:38.096 --> 00:10:39.223
No, no, no. Wait.

00:10:39.306 --> 00:10:43.435
I just need one of my cars
across the finish line first. One.

00:10:44.019 --> 00:10:45.979
I love ya. I'm not going back.

00:10:47.356 --> 00:10:48.482
[sighs]

00:10:50.108 --> 00:10:51.109
Okay.

00:10:54.613 --> 00:10:56.323
What would he want you to do?

00:10:56.406 --> 00:10:58.325
[chuckles]

00:10:58.951 --> 00:10:59.952
[Sonny] Join a boy band?

00:11:00.035 --> 00:11:01.578
Seriously. Come on.

00:11:03.747 --> 00:11:05.791
Seriously, I'd ask him
what he's smiling about.

00:11:05.874 --> 00:11:06.875
Come on.

00:11:07.876 --> 00:11:10.087
He's smiling at the possibility.

00:11:12.005 --> 00:11:13.507
We both know how that ended.

00:11:15.342 --> 00:11:16.343
Yep.

00:11:17.427 --> 00:11:18.428
Okay.

00:11:19.096 --> 00:11:22.558
-This is a first-class ticket to London.
-Oh, my God.

00:11:22.641 --> 00:11:23.851
First class.

00:11:23.934 --> 00:11:27.437
I'm offering you
an open seat in Formula 1.

00:11:28.397 --> 00:11:31.066
The only place you could say for one day,

00:11:31.149 --> 00:11:36.405
if you win,
you are the absolute best in the world.

00:11:46.456 --> 00:11:48.292
-Hey, Ruben.
-Mmm.

00:11:48.834 --> 00:11:50.794
-Ever seen a miracle?
-Not yet.

00:11:51.420 --> 00:11:52.504
Me neither.

00:11:53.547 --> 00:11:54.715
Good to see you, amigo.

00:11:56.925 --> 00:11:59.011
-All right, sweetie, here you go.
-Thank you.

00:11:59.094 --> 00:12:01.305
-Mm-hmm.
-Hey, let me ask you something.

00:12:03.557 --> 00:12:08.145
Close friend of yours made you an offer
that was 100%, positively

00:12:08.228 --> 00:12:09.479
too good to be true.

00:12:10.439 --> 00:12:11.440
What do you do?

00:12:11.523 --> 00:12:14.151
[sighs] Well, how much are we talking?

00:12:14.234 --> 00:12:15.611
Not about the money.

00:12:17.196 --> 00:12:18.697
So what is it about?

00:12:19.823 --> 00:12:20.908
Hmm.

00:12:32.169 --> 00:12:33.629
[engine revving]

00:12:51.480 --> 00:12:54.066
[driving synth music playing]

00:13:02.282 --> 00:13:05.160
[crew member] Tire temps look good.
Eighty-five front, 75 rear.

00:13:05.244 --> 00:13:07.538
-You are good to push.
-[driver] Copy.

00:13:16.463 --> 00:13:18.299
[crew member] Battery is full.
You're good for strat two.

00:13:18.382 --> 00:13:19.383
[driver] Going for a lap.

00:13:37.150 --> 00:13:39.361
Purple sector one. Best one yet.

00:13:40.028 --> 00:13:41.196
[driver] Car feels good.

00:14:16.106 --> 00:14:17.691
[tires squeal]

00:14:17.774 --> 00:14:18.817
Damn!

00:14:22.905 --> 00:14:24.907
Locked it up. Flat spot, front left.

00:14:30.662 --> 00:14:32.289
[sighs]

00:14:33.248 --> 00:14:34.333
Bring him in.

00:14:34.416 --> 00:14:35.792
Go to strat one.

00:14:35.876 --> 00:14:37.628
Uh, box this lap. Box this lap.

00:14:50.265 --> 00:14:52.768
-[groans]
-Let's go find those gremlins.

00:15:11.411 --> 00:15:12.704
[blows]

00:15:15.791 --> 00:15:18.293
[crew chattering]

00:15:19.920 --> 00:15:21.380
[groans]

00:15:28.512 --> 00:15:29.930
[grunts, gasps]

00:15:30.013 --> 00:15:31.265
Sorry, Joshua.

00:15:34.226 --> 00:15:36.311
Jodie, try not to kill our driver.

00:15:43.193 --> 00:15:44.945
What's the verdict? [sniffs]

00:15:45.028 --> 00:15:48.615
[sighs] I don't know what's happening.
I mean, it feels good. I start to push.

00:15:49.116 --> 00:15:51.494
Then it understeers in the slow corners
and oversteers the fast.

00:15:51.577 --> 00:15:53.120
What? On entries or exits?

00:15:53.203 --> 00:15:54.830
Either. Both.

00:15:54.913 --> 00:15:56.206
Oh, great. Yeah.

00:15:56.290 --> 00:15:59.085
There's 10,000 sensors on this thing
and you can't tell me what's going on.

00:15:59.168 --> 00:16:00.961
But I'm not out there, am I?

00:16:01.044 --> 00:16:03.964
So, I-I'm gonna need
your help on this. Please.

00:16:08.510 --> 00:16:11.263
[speaking German]

00:16:12.139 --> 00:16:13.390
[speaking German]

00:16:18.604 --> 00:16:20.522
[child giggles]

00:16:20.606 --> 00:16:23.192
[in English]
150 million dollar jungle gym.

00:16:23.817 --> 00:16:24.818
So cute.

00:16:25.444 --> 00:16:28.363
We should let her drive.
Can't be any worse.

00:16:29.114 --> 00:16:30.782
[child imitating engine]

00:16:31.450 --> 00:16:32.784
Joshua.

00:16:32.868 --> 00:16:35.120
-Hi.
-Lisbeth. PR?

00:16:35.204 --> 00:16:36.872
-Oh, yeah.
-Doesn't matter.

00:16:36.955 --> 00:16:39.583
For the press conference,
we want to steer around tech issues

00:16:39.666 --> 00:16:43.128
and focus on the super strong bond
with your new teammate, Luca Cortez.

00:16:43.212 --> 00:16:44.963
[laughs] Luca?

00:16:45.047 --> 00:16:46.465
Who I've known a week.

00:16:47.007 --> 00:16:49.134
Who when he was third banana
on the left at Red Bull,

00:16:49.218 --> 00:16:51.720
told the press he thought
Joshua Pearce was overrated.

00:16:52.763 --> 00:16:54.181
That Luca Cortez?

00:16:54.264 --> 00:16:55.724
Yes.

00:16:55.807 --> 00:16:58.936
-[chuckles] Can't wait. Yeah.
-All right. Great. Thank you.

00:16:59.019 --> 00:17:00.020
-Yo.
-Yep.

00:17:00.103 --> 00:17:02.314
That's a yes? Yeah? Yes? [groans]

00:17:02.397 --> 00:17:03.398
[Joshua] What's up?

00:17:03.482 --> 00:17:05.108
Yo, you were right, bro.

00:17:05.651 --> 00:17:08.111
Ruben's in big trouble.
He might have to sell the team.

00:17:08.194 --> 00:17:10.030
-[snaps fingers]
-I knew it.

00:17:10.113 --> 00:17:11.282
And what does that mean for me?

00:17:11.365 --> 00:17:13.742
New buyers, they're likely to clean house.

00:17:14.952 --> 00:17:15.953
Listen.

00:17:16.537 --> 00:17:20.624
You need to show these people
who the number one driver really is, man.

00:17:21.250 --> 00:17:22.251
Now.

00:17:23.919 --> 00:17:25.212
Or you're gonna lose your job.

00:17:25.753 --> 00:17:28.423
Yeah. Let that sink in.

00:17:28.507 --> 00:17:30.759
[speaking German]

00:17:31.552 --> 00:17:33.720
-[in English] Hey.
-[parent, speaking German]

00:17:34.930 --> 00:17:36.265
You good?

00:17:38.600 --> 00:17:42.855
Okay, let's take
the first half of the season

00:17:42.938 --> 00:17:44.940
and erase it from our minds.

00:17:45.023 --> 00:17:46.024
[crew cheers]

00:17:46.108 --> 00:17:48.318
Someone says,
"Kaspar, what happened this year?"

00:17:48.902 --> 00:17:52.948
I swear on the lives of my children,
I do not freaking know.

00:17:53.031 --> 00:17:54.366
[laughs]

00:17:54.449 --> 00:17:55.701
There's only this car.

00:17:56.285 --> 00:17:59.955
And there is only our future.

00:18:00.038 --> 00:18:02.833
[crew exclaiming] Yes. Our future.

00:18:11.842 --> 00:18:13.427
[Kaspar] Who is that asshole?

00:18:13.510 --> 00:18:14.511
He's with me.

00:18:15.429 --> 00:18:18.223
Your man thought I was maintenance.
Sent me to the back gate.

00:18:18.307 --> 00:18:19.683
[Ruben chuckles]

00:18:20.726 --> 00:18:22.144
Brother, you have never let me down.

00:18:22.227 --> 00:18:24.313
-[chuckles] Well, there's still time.
-[chuckles]

00:18:24.396 --> 00:18:25.981
Apex GP!

00:18:26.064 --> 00:18:28.525
Sonny Hayes.
He raced with me back in the day.

00:18:28.609 --> 00:18:30.360
-Against you, you mean.
-Yeah.

00:18:30.444 --> 00:18:32.905
-Kate McKenna, our technical director.
-Hi.

00:18:32.988 --> 00:18:35.908
-Dodge Dauda, our chief mechanic.
-Hi.

00:18:35.991 --> 00:18:38.160
And Kaspar Smolinski, team principal.

00:18:38.243 --> 00:18:39.786
You may know him by reputation.

00:18:39.870 --> 00:18:42.623
Five-time Constructors champion
with Ferrari.

00:18:43.165 --> 00:18:44.499
Huh.

00:18:45.250 --> 00:18:46.418
As a rear jack man.

00:18:46.502 --> 00:18:48.128
So was my pop. Can't win without 'em.

00:18:48.212 --> 00:18:51.089
-And our talented rookie, Joshua.
-Why has he got a helmet?

00:18:52.174 --> 00:18:54.051
-Uh, safety?
-[chuckles]

00:18:54.134 --> 00:18:56.512
Joshua, your seat is safe. Okay?

00:18:56.595 --> 00:18:58.514
Sonny is here for the audition.

00:19:00.933 --> 00:19:02.351
When was the last time you won a race?

00:19:02.434 --> 00:19:04.061
Sunday. Daytona.

00:19:04.144 --> 00:19:06.063
Oh, I'm sorry. I-I meant Formula 1.

00:19:06.146 --> 00:19:08.398
Oh, I'm sorry. Then same as you.

00:19:08.482 --> 00:19:11.485
-[laughs, exclaims] Wow.
-[chuckles]

00:19:11.568 --> 00:19:14.279
Never thought I'd say this,
has anyone seen Luca Cortez?

00:19:14.363 --> 00:19:16.406
-[chuckles]
-Sidebar bitte, Ruben.

00:19:16.490 --> 00:19:19.451
When I interview with you,
many veteran drivers...

00:19:19.535 --> 00:19:21.119
Yeah, who all turned you down.

00:19:21.203 --> 00:19:22.746
-How many?
-Seven.

00:19:22.829 --> 00:19:24.581
-That's a lot.
-I'm number seven?

00:19:24.665 --> 00:19:26.083
-Mm-hmm.
-You're eight.

00:19:26.166 --> 00:19:27.417
This is a disaster.

00:19:27.501 --> 00:19:28.794
Starting to feel more like a nine.

00:19:28.877 --> 00:19:30.588
Technically, there is one
who I've not heard from yet.

00:19:30.671 --> 00:19:31.797
-[stammers]
-So I am a nine?

00:19:31.880 --> 00:19:33.465
You know how numbers work, right?

00:19:33.549 --> 00:19:36.468
In business,
my most inspired ideas come late.

00:19:36.552 --> 00:19:39.096
Yeah. Best things in life
usually arrive ninth, right?

00:19:39.179 --> 00:19:42.599
With respect, Ruben, I cannot condone
we spend our only test day

00:19:42.683 --> 00:19:44.810
giving your long-lost teammate
an audition.

00:19:44.893 --> 00:19:46.228
Kaspar, you misunderstand.

00:19:46.311 --> 00:19:48.647
We're not auditioning him.
He's auditioning us.

00:19:50.065 --> 00:19:51.358
That's your new driver.

00:19:51.441 --> 00:19:52.526
Good luck.

00:19:55.696 --> 00:19:57.114
New wing, new side pods.

00:19:57.197 --> 00:19:58.615
Any changes to the floor?

00:19:59.783 --> 00:20:02.411
Nothing the eight other drivers
wouldn't have figured out.

00:20:03.287 --> 00:20:05.038
That's why they call me Lucky Number Nine.

00:20:05.122 --> 00:20:07.916
Listen, it's been a while
since you've driven here, mate. Yeah?

00:20:08.000 --> 00:20:10.761
The balance on these cars are tricky,
so be careful turn one and nine.

00:20:10.878 --> 00:20:12.238
Wouldn't want to see you get hurt.

00:20:13.505 --> 00:20:14.965
How about we set a reasonable target?

00:20:15.048 --> 00:20:18.635
Give me the same setup as him. If I can't
post a lap time within a second of JP's,

00:20:18.719 --> 00:20:20.387
then I will promptly see myself out

00:20:21.054 --> 00:20:23.015
and you're free to take a shot
at lucky number ten.

00:20:23.098 --> 00:20:24.808
-Ten?
-Ten.

00:20:25.517 --> 00:20:26.518
Ten.

00:20:28.729 --> 00:20:29.813
Who's JP?

00:20:31.148 --> 00:20:32.691
[rock music playing]

00:20:33.817 --> 00:20:36.528
Cross round on Brooklands,
easy on Luffield.

00:20:36.612 --> 00:20:38.780
Up to Woodcote, hard out in Copse.

00:20:38.864 --> 00:20:40.157
And be careful on the curve.

00:20:44.912 --> 00:20:47.873
Default mode, settings one, to two,
back to three.

00:20:48.498 --> 00:20:50.250
Differential one through four.

00:20:50.334 --> 00:20:51.627
DRS.

00:20:55.756 --> 00:20:59.551
♪ I bet you thought
You'd seen the last of me ♪

00:20:59.635 --> 00:21:03.096
♪ I can't change the way I am, you see ♪

00:21:03.180 --> 00:21:05.015
♪ I think it's my responsibility ♪

00:21:05.098 --> 00:21:06.600
[exhales deeply]

00:21:06.683 --> 00:21:10.312
♪ To tell you
I'm just as bad as I used to be ♪

00:21:10.395 --> 00:21:12.231
[engine starts, revs]

00:21:12.314 --> 00:21:15.150
♪ I'm just as bad as I used to be ♪

00:21:16.193 --> 00:21:17.569
[breathes deeply]

00:21:18.820 --> 00:21:20.906
Okay. Let's see what you got.

00:21:28.205 --> 00:21:33.377
If he raced with Ruben,
he raced with Schumacher. With Senna.

00:21:35.754 --> 00:21:39.132
♪ I tried changing my reality ♪

00:21:39.758 --> 00:21:42.761
♪ But I don't think
It's gonna set me free ♪

00:21:43.762 --> 00:21:46.557
♪ There's only one thing I can guarantee ♪

00:21:46.640 --> 00:21:51.019
♪ And that's
I'm just as bad as I used to be ♪

00:21:51.812 --> 00:21:54.523
♪ I'm just as bad as I used to be ♪

00:21:55.232 --> 00:21:58.694
♪ I'm just as bad as I used to be ♪

00:21:59.194 --> 00:22:03.365
♪ I'm just as bad as I used to be ♪

00:22:03.448 --> 00:22:05.242
All right, pull up Joshua's sector times.

00:22:15.043 --> 00:22:16.753
Twenty quid says he stacks it.

00:22:16.837 --> 00:22:18.463
Make it a hundred, you're on.

00:22:19.381 --> 00:22:20.632
Oh, shit.

00:22:20.716 --> 00:22:22.843
-[laughs]
-[laughs]

00:22:22.926 --> 00:22:26.096
Sorry, uh, this is Hugh Nickleby,
your race engineer.

00:22:26.180 --> 00:22:28.182
Good morning, Hugh.
How are my tire temps looking?

00:22:28.265 --> 00:22:31.101
Yep, almost warm. End of the lap,
you should be good to push.

00:22:31.185 --> 00:22:32.644
[exhales deeply]

00:22:34.104 --> 00:22:35.105
[grunts]

00:22:36.190 --> 00:22:37.274
[exhales deeply]

00:22:40.569 --> 00:22:42.863
[tires squeal]

00:22:46.658 --> 00:22:48.660
[sighs]

00:22:48.744 --> 00:22:50.495
Right. Man.

00:22:51.538 --> 00:22:53.248
-[Sonny] Hugh?
-Yes, sir?

00:22:53.332 --> 00:22:55.292
-You should've taken that bet.
-[chuckles]

00:22:55.375 --> 00:22:56.710
-[sighs]
-[Hugh] Copy that.

00:22:57.336 --> 00:23:01.006
♪ No one's accusing me of sanity ♪

00:23:01.798 --> 00:23:05.385
♪ I ain't everybody's cup of tea ♪

00:23:06.053 --> 00:23:07.847
♪ But that's the facts
I'm talkin' factually ♪

00:23:07.930 --> 00:23:09.097
Going for a lap.

00:23:10.057 --> 00:23:12.476
♪ I'm just as bad as I used to be ♪

00:23:12.559 --> 00:23:16.939
♪ Yes, I'm just as bad as I used to be ♪

00:23:17.022 --> 00:23:20.859
♪ Whoa, I'm just as bad as I used to be ♪

00:23:21.443 --> 00:23:25.614
♪ I'm just as bad as I used to be ♪

00:23:27.074 --> 00:23:29.159
Nope. Shit.

00:23:29.243 --> 00:23:30.244
He's dead.

00:23:30.327 --> 00:23:33.038
Come on. Don't do that.

00:23:33.121 --> 00:23:34.748
[all groan]

00:23:34.831 --> 00:23:35.832
And buried.

00:24:12.953 --> 00:24:14.329
[grunts]

00:24:15.497 --> 00:24:16.582
Wait.

00:24:18.584 --> 00:24:19.960
Wait.

00:24:20.878 --> 00:24:22.171
[inhales sharply]

00:24:22.963 --> 00:24:24.381
Now.

00:24:24.464 --> 00:24:25.465
[grunts]

00:24:27.885 --> 00:24:29.178
The car is there, come on.

00:24:33.432 --> 00:24:35.100
He's gaining.

00:24:35.184 --> 00:24:36.393
Ah, shit.

00:24:37.269 --> 00:24:39.897
-[tires squealing]
-[grunts]

00:24:45.194 --> 00:24:47.821
[grunts, groans]

00:24:47.905 --> 00:24:48.906
[song ends]

00:24:48.989 --> 00:24:50.741
-[grunts]
-You okay?

00:24:50.824 --> 00:24:53.368
[groans] Yep. All good.

00:24:53.452 --> 00:24:56.997
-[laughs]
-[sirens wailing]

00:24:57.080 --> 00:24:59.708
[grunting]

00:25:05.881 --> 00:25:08.258
-[groans, sighs]
-[Kaspar] Oh!

00:25:09.009 --> 00:25:11.970
-[Kate] Come on.
-[Sonny pants]

00:25:12.054 --> 00:25:13.430
Yeah, she's got something.

00:25:13.514 --> 00:25:14.973
Yeah, you mean had something.

00:25:16.308 --> 00:25:18.602
But definitely snappy
in the high-speed corners.

00:25:18.685 --> 00:25:19.937
Unpredictable in the lows.

00:25:20.896 --> 00:25:22.981
Had trouble with the
rears, turns 14, 16...

00:25:23.065 --> 00:25:24.566
And the final turn, maybe?

00:25:24.650 --> 00:25:26.860
-No, that's on me.
-What was his lap time?

00:25:27.528 --> 00:25:32.282
He passed his entirely self-imposed test
by five hundredths of a second.

00:25:34.785 --> 00:25:36.245
[sighs] Huh.

00:25:36.828 --> 00:25:37.955
[chuckles]

00:25:39.414 --> 00:25:40.457
Well… [sighs]

00:25:42.334 --> 00:25:43.544
…it's a start.

00:25:43.627 --> 00:25:45.170
[scoffs]

00:25:46.505 --> 00:25:48.507
[laid-back music playing]

00:25:52.469 --> 00:25:56.181
Bro, we got nine races to catch
the eye of another team, you know.

00:25:56.849 --> 00:25:58.684
And as your manager, I have to advise you

00:25:58.767 --> 00:26:01.228
that we need to start hitting
these social and sponsor events.

00:26:01.311 --> 00:26:02.938
You need more engagement, Josh,
more followers.

00:26:03.021 --> 00:26:05.421
-All right, deal.
-All right, cool. I'm just saying, innit?

00:26:06.275 --> 00:26:07.401
You eaten? I'm starving.

00:26:07.943 --> 00:26:08.944
Nah.

00:26:09.444 --> 00:26:10.696
Gotta see someone though.

00:26:10.779 --> 00:26:13.490
Yeah? Hey, take a picture, post that shit.

00:26:13.574 --> 00:26:15.117
Send it to me, I'll post that shit.

00:26:15.200 --> 00:26:16.618
It's my mum.

00:26:16.702 --> 00:26:18.287
Don't you dare post that shit.

00:26:18.370 --> 00:26:19.454
[laughs]

00:26:19.538 --> 00:26:21.498
I knew you was gonna say that.

00:26:24.918 --> 00:26:26.378
[music ends]

00:26:26.461 --> 00:26:27.713
[music plays softly on radio]

00:26:27.796 --> 00:26:29.047
[phone chimes]

00:26:32.551 --> 00:26:34.511
-[clicks tongue, sighs]
-Okay, baby?

00:26:35.012 --> 00:26:36.680
Yeah. Just tired.

00:26:37.514 --> 00:26:39.057
Bad tires or the engine?

00:26:39.975 --> 00:26:41.519
Come on, Mum.
You don't know about the cars.

00:26:41.602 --> 00:26:43.812
[chuckles] Facety.

00:26:43.896 --> 00:26:47.274
All right, I may not know much about cars,
but I know a lot about you.

00:26:47.941 --> 00:26:48.942
Go.

00:26:50.235 --> 00:26:51.403
[sighs]

00:26:51.486 --> 00:26:53.947
I might lose my seat
if the team don't win a race.

00:26:54.948 --> 00:26:55.949
Any race.

00:26:56.783 --> 00:26:57.868
There are other teams?

00:26:57.951 --> 00:26:59.791
Yeah, there's 20 seats,
but they're all filled.

00:27:00.662 --> 00:27:02.831
Plus, there's this new guy, and… [sighs]

00:27:02.915 --> 00:27:03.916
…he's old.

00:27:03.999 --> 00:27:05.167
How old?

00:27:05.250 --> 00:27:07.753
Like, really old. Like… 80.

00:27:07.836 --> 00:27:09.588
[laughs]

00:27:11.256 --> 00:27:13.008
He's such an arsehole, Mum.

00:27:13.717 --> 00:27:14.968
He's quick, though.

00:27:15.552 --> 00:27:16.929
Don't mind that.

00:27:17.012 --> 00:27:18.555
Focus on you.

00:27:18.639 --> 00:27:20.850
You can spend your whole life
worrying about other people,

00:27:20.933 --> 00:27:23.310
but your time is right now.

00:27:25.270 --> 00:27:26.396
You still love it?

00:27:27.940 --> 00:27:29.274
Course I still love it.

00:27:29.358 --> 00:27:31.568
Then remember what
your father used to say.

00:27:32.444 --> 00:27:34.905
"Put your head down and drive."

00:27:36.073 --> 00:27:37.074
Yes, ma'am.

00:27:37.157 --> 00:27:38.909
-[chuckles]
-[chuckles]

00:27:38.992 --> 00:27:40.285
[jaunty music playing]

00:27:54.049 --> 00:27:56.260
-[bells ring]
-[cows moo]

00:27:59.596 --> 00:28:01.265
[bicycle bell rings]

00:28:01.348 --> 00:28:03.934
[herder 1] Come on, then. It's all good.
Come on. Come on, then.

00:28:04.017 --> 00:28:05.811
Come on. Come on.

00:28:06.436 --> 00:28:08.480
-Come here. Come on, then.
-You're kiddin' me.

00:28:08.564 --> 00:28:10.649
[herders clamoring]

00:28:10.732 --> 00:28:13.402
[herder 2] Don't park there.
It's just a car. Quieten down.

00:28:13.485 --> 00:28:14.736
Come on, eh? Come on.

00:28:21.034 --> 00:28:22.369
[music ends]

00:28:24.162 --> 00:28:26.540
Thought your job was to build
the fastest car on the planet.

00:28:27.165 --> 00:28:29.585
[chuckles] My job is wind.

00:28:30.460 --> 00:28:32.462
So, helps to feel it.

00:28:33.797 --> 00:28:34.798
Mmm. [sighs]

00:28:34.882 --> 00:28:36.300
["Bright Lights" playing]

00:28:36.383 --> 00:28:38.760
Mysterious moves at Apex GP,

00:28:38.844 --> 00:28:42.514
who have finally announced the driver
who will take their second seat.

00:28:42.598 --> 00:28:45.726
And in a bizarre twist,
it's American Sonny Hayes,

00:28:45.809 --> 00:28:49.062
who hasn't raced in Formula 1
for over three decades.

00:28:49.146 --> 00:28:50.856
Son of an IndyCar mechanic,

00:28:50.939 --> 00:28:54.401
Hayes was considered something
of a reckless young phenomenon,

00:28:54.484 --> 00:28:56.737
the greatest who never was.

00:28:56.820 --> 00:28:59.615
His former career
being brought to an abrupt halt

00:28:59.698 --> 00:29:02.492
by a horrific accident
at the Spanish Grand Prix.

00:29:03.035 --> 00:29:06.246
He reappeared a decade later
in racing championships

00:29:06.330 --> 00:29:09.666
as diverse as Le Mans,
NASCAR, the Dakar Rally,

00:29:09.750 --> 00:29:12.628
and even a stint as
a New York taxi driver.

00:29:12.711 --> 00:29:14.630
-Oh, no.
-[crowd applauding]

00:29:14.713 --> 00:29:16.715
[Will Buxton] But now he's back
racing for a team which has,

00:29:16.798 --> 00:29:21.303
in its entire F1 history,
never even finished in the top ten.

00:29:21.386 --> 00:29:23.305
None of this will dampen speculation

00:29:23.388 --> 00:29:27.726
that majority shareholder Cervantes
Capital are looking to sell the team.

00:29:27.809 --> 00:29:30.479
And if they do,
that will likely also bring an end

00:29:30.562 --> 00:29:33.273
to the career of F1 rookie Joshua Pearce.

00:29:33.357 --> 00:29:35.109
-Can we go now?
-"Desperate times," they say,

00:29:35.192 --> 00:29:36.568
"call for desperate measures,"

00:29:36.652 --> 00:29:39.404
but I honestly cannot recall
a driver signing

00:29:39.488 --> 00:29:41.448
-quite as desperate as this.
-Let's go.

00:29:42.699 --> 00:29:45.327
Boy, look at my son.

00:29:45.410 --> 00:29:47.371
-[Joshua] Huh? [chuckles]
-Hey. [laughs]

00:29:47.454 --> 00:29:49.165
-[manager] That's the one.
-[Joshua's mom] Huh.

00:29:49.248 --> 00:29:51.458
-[music ends]
-That's the other driver?

00:29:51.542 --> 00:29:54.294
Yep. That's him and his stupid face.

00:29:54.378 --> 00:29:56.880
But, wait, you said he was old.
He not that old.

00:29:56.964 --> 00:29:58.382
[manager] Hey, Josh.

00:29:58.465 --> 00:29:59.967
You want a next shot anywhere?

00:30:00.050 --> 00:30:02.970
Nine races means nine times
you have to beat Chuck Norris.

00:30:05.013 --> 00:30:07.266
For now, start by winning over the press.

00:30:07.349 --> 00:30:09.434
-Yeah? You ready?
-Mm-hmm.

00:30:09.518 --> 00:30:10.644
Cool. Let's go.

00:30:11.186 --> 00:30:12.187
-[sighs]
-Mmm.

00:30:12.271 --> 00:30:15.315
That's a handsome man right there.
[chuckles]

00:30:17.067 --> 00:30:22.447
[Will Buxton] Joshua. Hey. Um, it's been
an undeniably messy start to your season.

00:30:22.531 --> 00:30:28.370
No wins, car problems throughout,
and now you have another new teammate.

00:30:28.453 --> 00:30:30.163
How exactly are you finding it?

00:30:30.956 --> 00:30:33.917
Messy start doesn't mean
you can't finish neat. All right?

00:30:34.001 --> 00:30:37.754
Apex have a fire crew of engineers,
so I'm confident we'll come back fightin'.

00:30:37.838 --> 00:30:39.715
In terms of new teammates,

00:30:40.507 --> 00:30:43.927
I think it's really wonderful that Apex
are giving second chances to the elderly.

00:30:44.011 --> 00:30:46.013
[all laugh]

00:30:46.096 --> 00:30:48.807
Ah, yes. Next question.
Thank you. Yes, Don. Yeah.

00:30:49.558 --> 00:30:52.477
Mr. Hayes. Hi. Don Cavendish.
Um, welcome back to the UK.

00:30:52.561 --> 00:30:53.896
It's been a while, mmm?

00:30:53.979 --> 00:30:55.606
I mean, last time
you raced at Silverstone,

00:30:55.689 --> 00:30:59.193
Bill Clinton was your president,
and we were all dancing the Macarena.

00:30:59.276 --> 00:31:01.904
-So, uh, it must be surreal to be back.
-[reporters laugh]

00:31:04.198 --> 00:31:05.240
Yeah.

00:31:07.367 --> 00:31:09.995
And, uh, during that decade,
you gave up racing,

00:31:10.078 --> 00:31:12.080
and, uh, gambled professionally?

00:31:12.164 --> 00:31:13.165
Uh-huh.

00:31:13.790 --> 00:31:16.543
Before declaring yourself
personally bankrupt?

00:31:16.627 --> 00:31:17.920
Yep.

00:31:18.003 --> 00:31:20.923
[Don] You had a marriage annulled
and two more ended in divorce?

00:31:21.006 --> 00:31:22.341
Yep.

00:31:24.134 --> 00:31:25.844
Anything you wish you'd done differently?

00:31:27.638 --> 00:31:28.639
Yeah.

00:31:28.722 --> 00:31:30.891
[reporters murmuring]

00:31:31.975 --> 00:31:34.478
[chuckles] No more questions.
Thank you. Yes. Thank you.

00:31:34.561 --> 00:31:38.982
[reporters clamoring]

00:31:39.066 --> 00:31:41.610
[somber orchestral music playing]

00:31:47.658 --> 00:31:50.327
[grunts]

00:31:57.793 --> 00:31:59.003
[music becomes electronic, dramatic]

00:31:59.086 --> 00:32:00.295
[panting]

00:32:00.379 --> 00:32:03.632
[breathing heavily]

00:32:03.715 --> 00:32:06.009
[grunts]

00:32:06.093 --> 00:32:08.178
[grunting]

00:32:09.972 --> 00:32:12.140
[sighs]

00:32:34.204 --> 00:32:37.332
[people chattering]

00:32:53.098 --> 00:32:54.099
[Joshua] Yes, Dodge.

00:32:57.978 --> 00:32:59.229
What time was he here?

00:32:59.313 --> 00:33:00.355
Before me.

00:33:07.154 --> 00:33:09.323
-And before you.
-[Joshua sighs]

00:33:09.406 --> 00:33:10.490
[music fades]

00:33:10.574 --> 00:33:13.243
[people cheering]

00:33:13.327 --> 00:33:15.329
[ball bouncing in distance]

00:33:16.538 --> 00:33:17.873
[sighs]

00:33:21.084 --> 00:33:23.337
Okay, here he comes. Apologize.

00:33:23.420 --> 00:33:25.047
[scoffs] Apologize? I can't do that.

00:33:25.547 --> 00:33:28.342
-How you mean? Why not?
-Because it's a sign of weakness.

00:33:28.425 --> 00:33:29.468
It's a sign of strength.

00:33:29.551 --> 00:33:30.761
Sign of weakness.

00:33:31.303 --> 00:33:32.888
You hard ears, just do it.

00:33:32.971 --> 00:33:34.223
Mum, I can't.

00:33:34.306 --> 00:33:35.891
You can. You will.

00:33:36.558 --> 00:33:37.559
[sighs]

00:33:40.604 --> 00:33:41.813
[sucks teeth]

00:33:44.107 --> 00:33:45.317
[sighs]

00:33:48.195 --> 00:33:49.196
Hey, man.

00:33:50.697 --> 00:33:53.325
Other day at the press conference,
stuff I said wasn't cool.

00:33:54.743 --> 00:33:56.870
[muttering] You say sorry.

00:33:56.954 --> 00:34:02.042
So, basically what I'm trying to say is…
I'm sorry.

00:34:02.125 --> 00:34:05.087
It's all right. You're just worried I'm
quicker than you. Hi, I'm Sonny.

00:34:05.796 --> 00:34:07.798
Oh, Bernadette Pearce. Nice to meet you.

00:34:08.382 --> 00:34:10.759
Pleasure.
It's all good. I'll see you out there.

00:34:10.842 --> 00:34:12.219
[scoffs]

00:34:12.302 --> 00:34:14.221
[ball bouncing]

00:34:17.766 --> 00:34:19.768
[pop song playing, muffled]

00:34:19.851 --> 00:34:20.853
[sighs]

00:34:22.062 --> 00:34:23.355
[sighs] How are you feeling?

00:34:23.438 --> 00:34:24.940
-So good.
-Good.

00:34:28.193 --> 00:34:29.277
-You good?
-Good.

00:34:29.777 --> 00:34:30.779
Good.

00:34:31.864 --> 00:34:32.864
No pressure.

00:34:32.947 --> 00:34:33.949
None.

00:34:35.117 --> 00:34:36.118
[sighs]

00:34:39.371 --> 00:34:41.248
-Great.
-Great. [clears throat]

00:34:41.331 --> 00:34:42.498
Great.

00:34:43.208 --> 00:34:44.918
[Croft] Welcome along to Silverstone,

00:34:45.002 --> 00:34:50.591
the circuit where on the 13th of May 1950
the Formula 1 World Championship began.

00:34:50.674 --> 00:34:55.304
Today, we kick off the final nine races
of this thrilling championship season

00:34:55.387 --> 00:34:58.557
here at the 77th British Grand Prix.

00:34:58.640 --> 00:35:01.101
[Brundle] As always,
11 teams will take the grid,

00:35:01.185 --> 00:35:03.103
fielding two drivers each.

00:35:03.187 --> 00:35:06.982
With race order determined
by the qualifying times set yesterday.

00:35:07.065 --> 00:35:09.067
Red Bull will start on pole

00:35:09.151 --> 00:35:12.654
followed by the two McLarens
and two Ferraris.

00:35:13.864 --> 00:35:16.283
[Croft] Drivers,
two minutes to national anthem.

00:35:16.366 --> 00:35:18.952
["God Save the King" playing]

00:35:32.925 --> 00:35:34.927
[marching band playing]

00:35:41.475 --> 00:35:43.727
["We Will Rock You" playing]

00:35:45.187 --> 00:35:46.271
Sonny!

00:35:47.189 --> 00:35:49.024
Ah, Ruben.
Don't make me talk to the money.

00:35:49.107 --> 00:35:51.360
Come on, give me a moment.
Just smile and shake hands.

00:35:51.443 --> 00:35:53.111
He's an important member of the board.

00:35:53.195 --> 00:35:54.655
Sonny, this is Peter Banning,

00:35:54.738 --> 00:35:55.948
-one of my investors.
-Hi.

00:35:56.031 --> 00:35:57.032
Hi.

00:35:57.115 --> 00:35:59.076
He knows absolutely nothing about racing…

00:35:59.159 --> 00:36:01.703
-Yeah.
-…but he's my eyes and ears on the board.

00:36:01.787 --> 00:36:04.164
And, uh, you're Ruben's Hail Mary.

00:36:04.248 --> 00:36:05.916
Now, that is
an American football term, right?

00:36:05.999 --> 00:36:07.543
The Hail Mary, the long shot. The...

00:36:07.626 --> 00:36:09.044
I believe it's a religious term,
originally.

00:36:09.127 --> 00:36:10.129
That is true. That is true.

00:36:10.212 --> 00:36:11.922
I'm praying to them all.

00:36:12.005 --> 00:36:14.258
I'm the one guy on the board
who actually wants to keep the team.

00:36:14.341 --> 00:36:16.177
The rest are calling it, you know,
Ruben's Inferno.

00:36:16.260 --> 00:36:17.970
But, seriously, man, I'm hooked.

00:36:18.053 --> 00:36:20.514
I've binged all of Drive to Survive.

00:36:20.597 --> 00:36:23.684
I honestly don't think I've ever known
so much about car tires. It's incredible.

00:36:23.767 --> 00:36:24.935
I'm gonna get back to my day job.

00:36:25.018 --> 00:36:26.770
-Okay.
-Okay.

00:36:26.854 --> 00:36:28.188
["We Will Rock You" continues]

00:36:28.272 --> 00:36:30.440
Hey, man.
We're counting on you. Good luck.

00:37:29.041 --> 00:37:30.834
What are you doing here, Sonny?

00:37:46.808 --> 00:37:49.436
[Croft] And as the clock ticks then
to the top of the hour,

00:37:49.520 --> 00:37:52.272
it's time to get things going here
at Silverstone.

00:37:52.356 --> 00:37:53.982
It's formation lap first.

00:37:54.066 --> 00:37:59.071
One tour of the track and a chance for the
drivers to warm up their tires and brakes.

00:38:01.907 --> 00:38:04.493
[Brundle] Oh, no.
There's a problem for Apex.

00:38:04.576 --> 00:38:07.829
That's Hayes in P22. His car hasn't moved.

00:38:07.913 --> 00:38:09.998
Hang on. I got power trouble.

00:38:10.082 --> 00:38:12.501
It's start mode, Sonny.

00:38:12.584 --> 00:38:13.919
Start mode on.

00:38:14.002 --> 00:38:16.004
[Brundle] Yes,
a lesson for everyone at home.

00:38:16.088 --> 00:38:18.131
New car? Do read the manual.

00:38:18.215 --> 00:38:20.593
[Croft] It's been a while since he was
out on the track. At this rate…

00:38:20.676 --> 00:38:22.761
-Dios mío.
-…he's not even gonna get into the race.

00:38:22.845 --> 00:38:23.846
Ay.

00:38:25.389 --> 00:38:26.473
-I got it.
-[engine revs]

00:38:26.557 --> 00:38:27.558
All good.

00:38:29.560 --> 00:38:32.229
[Croft] And he's away at last.
Thank goodness for that.

00:38:32.312 --> 00:38:34.690
[Brundle] If he falls too far behind
on the formation lap…

00:38:34.773 --> 00:38:35.775
-Drink?
-…he'll be at risk…

00:38:35.858 --> 00:38:38.277
-Eh? No.
-…of having to start in the pit lane.

00:38:39.444 --> 00:38:41.989
Where's Sonny? He's holding us up.

00:38:42.072 --> 00:38:44.408
Yeah. Just checking, Joshua.
Just checking.

00:38:45.576 --> 00:38:47.536
-What's wrong with his car?
-What? Nothing.

00:38:47.619 --> 00:38:49.037
[Brundle] With a clear track ahead,

00:38:49.121 --> 00:38:52.332
Hayes has been able
to push much harder on this formation lap.

00:38:52.416 --> 00:38:55.836
He'll turn up at the back of the grid
with warm tires, ready to go.

00:38:57.004 --> 00:38:59.548
Cheeky shit. It's on purpose.

00:39:04.428 --> 00:39:05.762
What is this guy doing?

00:39:05.846 --> 00:39:09.725
[Croft] This is actually now
turning into an advantage for Sonny Hayes.

00:39:09.808 --> 00:39:13.937
[Brundle] And he's just made it in time.
Watch out for his start.

00:39:22.905 --> 00:39:27.075
[Croft] Five lights ahead of the drivers.
It's lights out and away we go!

00:39:27.159 --> 00:39:28.285
[crowd cheering]

00:39:40.130 --> 00:39:42.341
Here comes Sonny Hayes,
ladies and gentlemen.

00:39:42.424 --> 00:39:46.220
Using those warm tires to carve his way
through the back of the field.

00:39:46.303 --> 00:39:49.181
[Brundle] And if you ever need
confidence in your car,

00:39:49.264 --> 00:39:50.724
it's here at Silverstone.

00:40:07.533 --> 00:40:09.451
Hayes is just sailing past people.

00:40:09.535 --> 00:40:12.454
He's moved up seven places
since the start.

00:40:12.538 --> 00:40:15.374
-Apex GP has struggled with this car…
-Yes!

00:40:15.457 --> 00:40:17.751
…but they've brought an upgrade package
this weekend.

00:40:17.835 --> 00:40:21.755
Let's see if it makes a difference
as Hayes attacks Perez in the Red Bull.

00:40:25.676 --> 00:40:28.554
Car's bouncing around this dirty air.
I can't position to attack.

00:40:29.346 --> 00:40:31.723
[Brundle] Hayes complaining
about his car over the radio.

00:40:31.807 --> 00:40:34.560
That's not what the team wants to hear.

00:40:34.643 --> 00:40:37.813
Copy. Gap is 0.9 to Perez.
You're within DRS range.

00:40:37.896 --> 00:40:40.065
Should be able to take him
on the next straight.

00:40:42.734 --> 00:40:46.280
[Croft] Hayes now using
the drag reduction system to get past.

00:40:46.363 --> 00:40:47.781
-[cheering]
-Yeah!

00:40:47.865 --> 00:40:50.033
Won't be able to hold him off, guys.
I got no grip.

00:40:50.117 --> 00:40:52.119
-This is trouble now for Apex GP.
-Oh, come on.

00:40:52.202 --> 00:40:53.954
The Red Bull's tires are now warm

00:40:54.037 --> 00:40:57.583
and Hayes hasn't got his tire advantage
from the start anymore.

00:40:57.666 --> 00:41:01.044
We've seen the attack.
Now it's all about defense.

00:41:01.128 --> 00:41:03.839
And Perez on the attack into Vale.

00:41:03.922 --> 00:41:07.217
Hayes is in trouble.
This could be the places reversed.

00:41:07.301 --> 00:41:09.261
-[crowd cheering]
-And it is.

00:41:09.344 --> 00:41:10.345
Damn.

00:41:10.429 --> 00:41:12.472
Rear end is loose.
Tell me if you see a fix.

00:41:12.556 --> 00:41:15.350
Tell him to pull back the entry
to get a better exit.

00:41:15.434 --> 00:41:17.644
He-He thinks it's the setup. It's not.

00:41:20.022 --> 00:41:21.148
[Croft] Twenty laps down.

00:41:21.231 --> 00:41:25.152
Verstappen leads but Joshua Pearce
is struggling out there at the moment.

00:41:25.235 --> 00:41:28.113
Guys, get me off these softs.
I'm going backwards.

00:41:28.197 --> 00:41:30.949
Copy that. Lap 20. Box, box.

00:41:31.033 --> 00:41:33.452
[Brundle] Stakes couldn't be higher
for rookie Joshua Pearce.

00:41:33.535 --> 00:41:37.164
This is not where you want to be,
in last place.

00:41:39.583 --> 00:41:41.168
[groans] I'm jammed. Back up!

00:41:48.258 --> 00:41:49.635
Hit something. What was that?

00:41:49.718 --> 00:41:50.719
[crowd shrieks]

00:41:50.802 --> 00:41:53.263
[Croft] Ooh, a seven-second pit stop.

00:41:53.347 --> 00:41:55.390
Apex GP won't be happy with that.

00:41:55.474 --> 00:41:58.393
That's double the time it should've taken.

00:41:58.477 --> 00:42:00.020
Lost the rears. Box, box.

00:42:00.103 --> 00:42:02.022
Copy. Go to plan B. Box, box.

00:42:02.731 --> 00:42:05.442
[Croft] And here comes Sonny Hayes
for a fresh set of tires.

00:42:05.526 --> 00:42:10.280
He'll be hoping these will help him
hold on to his current position of P15.

00:42:10.364 --> 00:42:11.281
Front jacks! Front jacks!

00:42:11.365 --> 00:42:12.992
[Brundle] The front jack has
not worked properly.

00:42:13.075 --> 00:42:16.328
-You're kidding me.
-This is causing absolute pandemonium

00:42:16.411 --> 00:42:18.705
in the Apex GP pit lane.

00:42:20.541 --> 00:42:23.919
Whatever could go wrong
is going wrong for this team.

00:42:27.089 --> 00:42:30.676
[Croft] And coming out of the pit,
Hayes just ahead of his teammate.

00:42:30.759 --> 00:42:35.222
As Pearce and Hayes go battling it out
here at Silverstone.

00:42:35.305 --> 00:42:36.557
Coming for you, old man.

00:42:43.939 --> 00:42:45.732
Got the pace, man.
Tell him to let me pass.

00:42:45.816 --> 00:42:47.485
Yeah. Copy. Hold position. Stand by. Kate.

00:42:47.568 --> 00:42:50.320
Josh is faster. Sonny is on cold tires.

00:42:55.826 --> 00:42:57.706
Yeah, okay, Sonny, no fighting.
Let him through.

00:43:03.000 --> 00:43:05.127
Sonny, no fighting.

00:43:05.210 --> 00:43:06.670
Who's fighting? I'm racing.

00:43:06.753 --> 00:43:09.131
[Croft] Pearce on the inside,
Hayes on the outside.

00:43:09.214 --> 00:43:11.550
[Brundle] Hayes trying
to make him eat concrete

00:43:11.633 --> 00:43:13.302
up against the old pit wall there.

00:43:13.385 --> 00:43:15.554
Joshua, you're gonna
have to fight for position.

00:43:15.637 --> 00:43:16.638
You are racing Sonny.

00:43:16.722 --> 00:43:17.806
A-ffirm.

00:43:17.890 --> 00:43:20.392
[Brundle] They're giving
absolutely no quarter.

00:43:20.475 --> 00:43:22.394
No benefit to their teammate at all.

00:43:22.477 --> 00:43:25.147
They're pushing as if
they're trying to win a Grand Prix.

00:43:25.230 --> 00:43:28.442
[Croft] But this is the battle
for last place, remember?

00:43:28.525 --> 00:43:29.693
And what a brawl it is.

00:43:29.776 --> 00:43:31.195
Let's go, kid. Bring it.

00:43:34.740 --> 00:43:36.491
What is this guy doing? Let me through.

00:43:36.575 --> 00:43:38.785
[crowd cheering]

00:43:46.710 --> 00:43:47.753
[spectators gasp]

00:43:52.925 --> 00:43:54.760
[Croft] Round the final corner.

00:43:54.843 --> 00:43:55.969
It's close!

00:43:56.053 --> 00:43:57.596
They make contact.

00:43:57.679 --> 00:44:01.141
- Both Apex GP cars into the gravel,
- [Sonny grunts]

00:44:01.225 --> 00:44:03.227
and Pearce hits the barrier.

00:44:03.310 --> 00:44:05.270
[crowd clamoring]

00:44:05.354 --> 00:44:06.605
-Ah, no!
-No!

00:44:07.314 --> 00:44:08.482
[Brundle] This is mad.

00:44:08.565 --> 00:44:10.776
The cardinal sin of motor racing.

00:44:10.859 --> 00:44:12.486
-A double DNF.
-[Ruben groans]

00:44:12.569 --> 00:44:16.448
Just when it couldn't get any worse
for the black and gold.

00:44:16.532 --> 00:44:18.692
-[Peter] That's a tough one, man.
-[mutters, sighing]

00:44:23.789 --> 00:44:26.166
[crowd shrieking, booing]

00:44:34.550 --> 00:44:35.843
We can't corner.

00:44:35.926 --> 00:44:38.512
We're bouncing around the place
like we're on the bloody Tube

00:44:38.595 --> 00:44:41.035
and now we think it's cool
to leave wheel guns in the pit box.

00:44:41.431 --> 00:44:42.432
Who even was that?

00:44:42.516 --> 00:44:44.685
-That was me.
-Of course.

00:44:47.312 --> 00:44:48.313
Old man.

00:44:51.275 --> 00:44:53.944
You losing your hearing? What was that?

00:44:54.945 --> 00:44:55.946
You wanna do this here?

00:44:56.029 --> 00:44:58.324
Yeah, I'd love to do this here
in front of the team, right.

00:44:58.407 --> 00:44:59.742
The one that you're apparently a part of.

00:44:59.825 --> 00:45:02.578
-Okay. You made a mistake. It happens.
-[laughs]

00:45:02.661 --> 00:45:04.329
I made a mistake. I love this guy, man.

00:45:04.413 --> 00:45:06.791
-Don't worry about it, Jodie.
-Are you even listening to me?

00:45:06.874 --> 00:45:08.750
-Not really.
-[Kaspar] No!

00:45:08.834 --> 00:45:10.169
Stop.

00:45:10.252 --> 00:45:11.670
Joshua is right.

00:45:11.753 --> 00:45:13.338
An order is an order.

00:45:13.422 --> 00:45:16.258
May I remind you that you report to me?

00:45:19.928 --> 00:45:20.929
Cool.

00:45:21.722 --> 00:45:23.640
Just don't ask me to give up position.

00:45:26.685 --> 00:45:28.604
Sorry. Sorry, guys.

00:45:30.731 --> 00:45:32.357
Hold up.

00:45:32.441 --> 00:45:34.026
You swan into our garage
like some entitled prick.

00:45:34.109 --> 00:45:35.903
-"Swan"?
-Calling us piss poor…

00:45:35.986 --> 00:45:37.613
-What's "swan"?
-…and then you drive like that. Huh?

00:45:37.696 --> 00:45:39.573
You said I "swan." What's that mean?

00:45:39.656 --> 00:45:42.367
You. You're an arsehole.
You come in like an arsehole. You swan.

00:45:42.451 --> 00:45:44.119
So swans are assholes?

00:45:46.163 --> 00:45:48.916
You're making the mistake of thinking
that I'm just gonna be some grateful kid

00:45:48.999 --> 00:45:50.751
who'll bend a knee to an old-timer.

00:45:51.418 --> 00:45:53.629
I climbed a mountain to get here, bro.

00:45:54.421 --> 00:45:55.506
Formula 1.

00:45:55.589 --> 00:45:58.342
Back home we call that
a participation trophy.

00:45:58.425 --> 00:46:00.344
[reporters] Joshua, Joshua! Josh!

00:46:00.427 --> 00:46:01.470
[clamoring]

00:46:01.553 --> 00:46:03.472
[chuckles] Yeah.

00:46:04.806 --> 00:46:07.142
What the hell are you smiling about, man?

00:46:07.226 --> 00:46:08.393
Did you win something?

00:46:08.936 --> 00:46:11.188
There's 20 other drivers
still out on that track

00:46:11.271 --> 00:46:13.273
and you're in here
posing for that nonsense.

00:46:13.357 --> 00:46:16.276
Do you think any of them respect us?
Do you?

00:46:17.402 --> 00:46:20.739
They need to learn that
no one gets past us without a fight.

00:46:20.822 --> 00:46:21.823
No one.

00:46:24.826 --> 00:46:27.579
You don't like the way I'm driving?
Beat me, swan.

00:46:34.920 --> 00:46:35.921
Hell of a race, huh?

00:46:36.463 --> 00:46:37.589
Whoo!

00:46:48.392 --> 00:46:51.854
[breathes deeply]

00:46:55.983 --> 00:46:59.194
Sorry, I didn't see you. Um… [sighs]

00:46:59.945 --> 00:47:01.947
[sighs] You still beating yourself up?

00:47:02.030 --> 00:47:03.240
Yeah.

00:47:03.323 --> 00:47:05.409
Yeah, I know that one. [chuckles]

00:47:07.744 --> 00:47:10.622
Um, thanks for what you said out there.

00:47:12.124 --> 00:47:14.877
Just don't do it again, okay?

00:47:15.586 --> 00:47:17.171
Makes me look like I need help.

00:47:17.880 --> 00:47:20.716
Oh, man. You're right. [sighs] Got it.

00:47:21.300 --> 00:47:24.386
Hey, for what it's worth,
don't be shitty to yourself.

00:47:24.469 --> 00:47:26.472
There's plenty of people out there
that'll do that for you.

00:47:26.555 --> 00:47:27.806
Yeah.

00:47:32.686 --> 00:47:33.854
[sighs]

00:47:36.273 --> 00:47:40.903
"I'm sorry, Ruben, for demolishing not one
but both of your lovely cars.

00:47:40.986 --> 00:47:43.447
For coming back into your life
only to destroy it."

00:47:43.530 --> 00:47:44.865
Is this your revenge for Monaco?

00:47:44.948 --> 00:47:46.366
Yeah, I waited 30 years

00:47:46.450 --> 00:47:49.786
and came all this way
to humiliate myself on global television.

00:47:49.870 --> 00:47:53.207
Funny. You think I brought you in
to make my other driver quit?

00:47:53.916 --> 00:47:57.377
Listen, he's cocky.
He's arrogant. He's got a lot to learn.

00:47:57.461 --> 00:47:59.463
[laughs]

00:48:01.006 --> 00:48:03.842
You were cocky, you were arrogant
and you had a lot to learn.

00:48:03.926 --> 00:48:06.678
I'm not here to hold anyone's hand.
I'm here to race.

00:48:06.762 --> 00:48:09.681
No, you're not, Sonny.
You're here to give me a heart attack.

00:48:10.933 --> 00:48:12.559
The board is up my ass

00:48:13.936 --> 00:48:16.355
and I have to decide
whether to continue this fiasco

00:48:16.438 --> 00:48:19.149
-or pull the plug now.
-You have till the end of the season.

00:48:19.233 --> 00:48:21.985
By which time Apex will be worth less
than my shoes!

00:48:22.694 --> 00:48:24.446
Sonny! God…

00:48:27.157 --> 00:48:28.200
Tell me about Kate.

00:48:29.701 --> 00:48:31.370
The car.
I wanna talk to her about the car.

00:48:31.453 --> 00:48:33.956
She's the world's first
female tech director of an F1 team.

00:48:34.039 --> 00:48:35.499
I mean, that takes balls.

00:48:35.582 --> 00:48:37.584
Wow. Is that your line?

00:48:38.168 --> 00:48:39.253
She'll see right through it.

00:48:39.336 --> 00:48:40.462
It's not a line.

00:48:40.546 --> 00:48:42.840
-I'm sorry. Sorry.
-Is she married?

00:48:43.423 --> 00:48:46.635
Okay, stay there in that tub of ice
until Budapest.

00:48:46.718 --> 00:48:48.178
You don't move.

00:48:50.556 --> 00:48:51.723
Hey, Ruben…

00:48:53.809 --> 00:48:55.310
We can't get there with this car.

00:49:04.361 --> 00:49:05.404
[sighs]

00:49:41.732 --> 00:49:43.442
Hey. Hey.

00:49:43.525 --> 00:49:44.943
Yeah, sorry. Hi, hi, hi.

00:49:45.569 --> 00:49:46.570
What you working on?

00:49:47.279 --> 00:49:51.783
I'm working on a new front wing concept.
Trying to pick us up a tenth or so.

00:49:51.867 --> 00:49:55.329
Cool. And you can replicate turns?
Lateral airflow?

00:49:55.412 --> 00:49:57.206
No, just straight line drag.

00:49:57.289 --> 00:49:59.374
But, I mean,
we can calculate it from there.

00:50:00.125 --> 00:50:03.378
Okay, what about turbulent air
from a car we're following?

00:50:03.462 --> 00:50:05.380
No, not exactly, but...

00:50:05.464 --> 00:50:08.258
Track conditions, surface quality,
weather, ambient temps?

00:50:08.342 --> 00:50:12.554
[chuckles] I'm sorry, uh, is there
something that you wanted to discuss?

00:50:12.638 --> 00:50:15.224
Kate, you read my mind.

00:50:19.228 --> 00:50:23.065
So how does one get to be the first female
technical director of an F1 team?

00:50:23.148 --> 00:50:24.316
Must take…

00:50:27.653 --> 00:50:30.656
Dedication and lots of hard work.

00:50:30.739 --> 00:50:34.117
-That's your urgent question?
-Hmm? Mm-mmm.

00:50:34.201 --> 00:50:38.121
Plenty of people think I don't belong here
and I'm happy to add you to the list

00:50:38.205 --> 00:50:39.999
if you're implying
what I… I think you're implying.

00:50:40.082 --> 00:50:41.375
As a rule I don't imply stuff.

00:50:41.458 --> 00:50:42.876
So you like straight talk?

00:50:42.960 --> 00:50:44.711
Straight as an arrow. No sugar.

00:50:45.671 --> 00:50:47.506
Everyone thinks Ruben's lost it.

00:50:47.589 --> 00:50:48.841
That he is clutching at straws.

00:50:48.924 --> 00:50:50.676
They're saying maybe he lost a bet.

00:50:50.759 --> 00:50:53.136
-Ran over your dog.
-[chuckles]

00:50:53.220 --> 00:50:57.808
They're saying Sonny Hayes
isn't a has-been.

00:50:58.308 --> 00:50:59.476
He's a never-was.

00:51:03.063 --> 00:51:05.691
Yeah, when I said I like straight talk
I meant me.

00:51:06.233 --> 00:51:09.528
From others, I mostly prefer praise,
flattery, hero worship,

00:51:09.611 --> 00:51:11.405
at times, straight-up bullshit.

00:51:11.488 --> 00:51:13.866
-Is that what Ruben's for?
-[laughs]

00:51:13.949 --> 00:51:16.326
Ruben. I love the guy.
Most solid, steadfast...

00:51:16.410 --> 00:51:17.786
Said you asked if I was married.

00:51:17.870 --> 00:51:21.248
Disloyal, mean, twisted,
bitter, husk of a man.

00:51:21.331 --> 00:51:27.629
Mmm, yeah. And he also told me about
a big string of ex-wives and girlfriends.

00:51:27.713 --> 00:51:29.298
He said to avoid you like the plague.

00:51:29.381 --> 00:51:32.718
Okay… [chuckles] …let me explain this.

00:51:33.760 --> 00:51:36.096
When you're going 200 miles per hour
into Eau Rouge,

00:51:36.180 --> 00:51:38.348
it's good to know who's got your back.

00:51:39.600 --> 00:51:41.393
And for the record,
in all my years of racing,

00:51:41.476 --> 00:51:45.856
I have never ever hit on
the team technical director.

00:51:45.939 --> 00:51:50.152
[smacks lips] Well, now that's
a huge weight off my mind.

00:51:53.989 --> 00:51:56.241
So what's this urgent question?

00:51:56.325 --> 00:51:57.534
Okay.

00:51:58.410 --> 00:52:01.788
Red Bull, Ferrari,
Mercedes, Aston, now McLaren

00:52:01.872 --> 00:52:03.415
all have us beat on straight line speed.

00:52:03.498 --> 00:52:05.959
Our shot is battling in the turns.

00:52:06.043 --> 00:52:08.754
I need a way
to chase through the dirty air.

00:52:11.215 --> 00:52:15.344
You want me to redesign
so you can follow closer?

00:52:15.427 --> 00:52:16.929
We need to build our car for combat.

00:52:18.013 --> 00:52:20.307
Uh, how am I supposed to make that safe?

00:52:20.390 --> 00:52:21.850
Who said anything about safe?

00:52:24.353 --> 00:52:25.687
That's your question?

00:52:25.771 --> 00:52:26.980
Yeah.

00:52:27.064 --> 00:52:28.273
And here's the straight talk.

00:52:29.441 --> 00:52:30.442
It's urgent.

00:52:32.945 --> 00:52:34.530
[scoffs]

00:52:36.281 --> 00:52:38.867
You know,
I bet when you look in the mirror,

00:52:38.951 --> 00:52:45.415
you see this rough-and-tumble,
old school, no bullshit cowboy.

00:52:45.499 --> 00:52:48.585
Doesn't take orders.
Goes his own way. Huh?

00:52:48.669 --> 00:52:50.087
A lone wolf.

00:52:51.088 --> 00:52:52.589
Well, I have news for you.

00:52:52.673 --> 00:52:55.592
Formula 1 is a team sport. It always was.

00:52:55.676 --> 00:52:58.512
And maybe that's why you failed at it?

00:52:59.638 --> 00:53:03.475
The only question here is,
"Why did Sonny Hayes come back to F1?"

00:53:03.559 --> 00:53:08.146
Now that question
is extremely fucking urgent.

00:53:12.359 --> 00:53:15.779
I'll start listening to you
when you finish a race.

00:53:20.284 --> 00:53:21.285
[grumbles]

00:53:23.287 --> 00:53:24.788
[electronic pop song playing]

00:53:30.544 --> 00:53:32.462
♪ Don't let me down ♪

00:53:38.677 --> 00:53:41.638
♪ Don't let me down ♪

00:53:44.183 --> 00:53:47.019
♪ Don't let me down ♪

00:53:47.102 --> 00:53:48.187
♪ Oh yeah, oh yeah, oh yeah ♪

00:53:48.270 --> 00:53:50.772
♪ Don't let me drown ♪

00:53:50.856 --> 00:53:52.733
♪ Oh yeah, oh yeah, oh yeah ♪

00:53:52.816 --> 00:53:55.319
♪ Don't let me down ♪

00:53:55.402 --> 00:53:57.029
♪ Oh yeah, oh yeah, oh yeah ♪

00:53:57.112 --> 00:54:01.074
♪ Don't let me drown ♪

00:54:05.495 --> 00:54:07.789
[song continues]

00:54:08.498 --> 00:54:10.584
♪ Don't let me down ♪

00:54:16.924 --> 00:54:19.718
♪ Don't let me drown ♪

00:54:22.888 --> 00:54:25.265
♪ Nights like these ♪

00:54:25.349 --> 00:54:29.061
♪ There's something mystical
About nights like these ♪

00:54:29.853 --> 00:54:32.356
♪ And the concept of time don't matter ♪

00:54:32.439 --> 00:54:34.066
[song fades]

00:54:34.149 --> 00:54:35.400
[brakes hiss]

00:54:36.652 --> 00:54:40.113
[Buxton] At the Spanish Grand Prix,
the American rookie Sonny Hayes

00:54:40.197 --> 00:54:44.117
had just signed a new contract,
and his future looked very bright.

00:54:44.201 --> 00:54:47.913
He'd earned a reputation
for his aggressive driving style.

00:54:47.996 --> 00:54:51.875
Seen by some as reckless,
it nevertheless served him well

00:54:51.959 --> 00:54:54.711
as he climbed up the order
over the course of the season,

00:54:54.795 --> 00:54:57.798
relentlessly pursuing
his first F1 victory.

00:54:59.508 --> 00:55:02.302
Hayes was running well
in the opening laps,

00:55:02.386 --> 00:55:05.013
chasing down race leader Ayrton Senna.

00:55:05.097 --> 00:55:07.266
However when Hayes made a risky move

00:55:07.349 --> 00:55:11.395
and attacked Senna on the outside of
a high-speed right-hand turn,

00:55:11.979 --> 00:55:15.357
a frightening scene unfolded
as quick as a flash.

00:55:15.440 --> 00:55:17.985
[commentator 1] My goodness!
I just saw him plunge off to the right.

00:55:18.068 --> 00:55:19.612
There you can see the debris on the right.

00:55:19.695 --> 00:55:22.281
What on earth happened there,
I don't know.

00:55:22.364 --> 00:55:23.741
[commentator 2]
Yes, this looks very severe indeed.

00:55:23.824 --> 00:55:27.202
I must say, it looks like, uh, he is…
he really needs help.

00:55:27.286 --> 00:55:29.121
There is nobody coming to him
at the moment.

00:55:29.204 --> 00:55:31.415
The race has been stopped.
The red flag is out.

00:55:31.498 --> 00:55:33.333
This looks a little bit like a...

00:55:50.601 --> 00:55:54.188
[Kate] Our models predict all teams
are gonna be targeting a one-stop race.

00:55:54.271 --> 00:55:58.525
Plan A is to switch from mediums to hards,
between lap 27 and 33.

00:55:58.609 --> 00:56:04.823
Plan B will be medium-hard-medium,
first window 16 to 21, second, 45 to 51.

00:56:04.907 --> 00:56:06.617
Plan C for softs doesn't make sense.

00:56:06.700 --> 00:56:08.911
At this temp,
the tire deg will be too high.

00:56:10.662 --> 00:56:11.663
Nothing else?

00:56:12.247 --> 00:56:14.082
-Yep.
-Yeah, Joshua?

00:56:14.166 --> 00:56:16.293
So, we've just got to
drive our race, all right?

00:56:16.376 --> 00:56:17.378
Let's not try and be heroes.

00:56:17.461 --> 00:56:19.546
Just make it through
those first turns clean.

00:56:19.630 --> 00:56:21.757
Can't win at lap one,
starting at the back,

00:56:21.840 --> 00:56:25.010
so we just gotta hope for some
lucky breaks later on, all right?

00:56:25.093 --> 00:56:26.261
-[crew member] Yeah.
-Yeah.

00:56:26.345 --> 00:56:27.930
Create your own breaks.

00:56:29.264 --> 00:56:31.183
Um, hello, hi? I just said that.

00:56:32.476 --> 00:56:33.769
Hope is not a strategy.

00:56:37.606 --> 00:56:39.024
Anything else, Professor?

00:56:39.942 --> 00:56:41.902
Um… [sighs]

00:56:42.402 --> 00:56:43.487
Drive fast?

00:56:55.791 --> 00:56:59.878
-[crowd cheering]
-[timer beeps]

00:56:59.962 --> 00:57:00.963
[timer stops]

00:57:01.046 --> 00:57:03.298
[Croft] It's lights out, and away we go.

00:57:03.382 --> 00:57:06.051
Great start from Hamilton,
Verstappen battling with him.

00:57:06.134 --> 00:57:09.513
Piastri, Zhou, Leclerc…
and here come the two Apex GPs.

00:57:10.472 --> 00:57:14.893
But Gasly shuts the door,
leaving them with nowhere to go.

00:57:21.275 --> 00:57:24.653
Into turn one,
and there's three cars gone off.

00:57:24.736 --> 00:57:27.865
Gasly, Ocon, and the AlphaTauri, Tsunoda.

00:57:27.948 --> 00:57:29.241
[Sonny] Hit debris. Check my tires.

00:57:29.324 --> 00:57:32.035
Yeah, you've got a puncture. Right rear.
Box. Box this lap.

00:57:32.119 --> 00:57:34.204
First goddamn turn. A ruined race.

00:57:35.163 --> 00:57:37.708
[Sonny] Oh, shit, shit, shit. Ah, shit.

00:57:41.211 --> 00:57:42.713
He's coming in! Let's go.

00:57:43.297 --> 00:57:44.798
[Sonny] Let's go Plan C.

00:57:44.882 --> 00:57:49.261
No, Plan C is for soft tires.
They won't last ten laps in this heat. No.

00:57:49.344 --> 00:57:50.513
That's a negative, Sonny. Plan A.

00:57:50.596 --> 00:57:53.140
[Sonny] Plan A is called Plan A 'cause
it's when everything is going right.

00:57:53.223 --> 00:57:54.383
You see anything going right?

00:57:54.933 --> 00:57:56.602
Plan C. Softs.

00:57:56.685 --> 00:57:59.813
It's not his call.
Tell him A, as in "asshole."

00:58:00.564 --> 00:58:02.232
Okay, let's go! Turn 'em out! Hard tires.

00:58:02.316 --> 00:58:03.817
[Sonny] Softs, goddamn it.

00:58:09.198 --> 00:58:12.159
-What's wrong with the car?
-The guy sitting in it.

00:58:12.242 --> 00:58:16.955
Are you insane? We need hard tires.
Everybody here is at a one-stop race.

00:58:17.039 --> 00:58:19.124
[Sonny] We do what
everybody does, we lose.

00:58:20.834 --> 00:58:22.377
-Make him go!
-How?

00:58:23.128 --> 00:58:26.131
You think I don't know my tires?
I was a mechanic.

00:58:26.215 --> 00:58:29.927
Five championship titles
with my bare freaking hands!

00:58:32.971 --> 00:58:33.972
Give him his tires.

00:58:34.973 --> 00:58:36.892
-[Hugh] Okay, let's go.
-Go, go, change!

00:58:36.975 --> 00:58:38.602
Let's go, let's go! Change quick, now!

00:58:43.941 --> 00:58:44.942
[Sonny] Be ready.

00:58:45.025 --> 00:58:46.652
Ready for what?

00:58:53.951 --> 00:58:57.037
-Where's JP sitting?
-[Hugh] Currently running P14.

00:58:59.331 --> 00:59:00.791
[Sonny] All right, here we go now.

00:59:01.291 --> 00:59:02.584
[Croft] Hayes makes his move,

00:59:02.668 --> 00:59:05.254
chasing Kevin Magnussen.
It's a late lunge!

00:59:05.337 --> 00:59:06.922
[Brundle] He's damaged his front wing.

00:59:07.005 --> 00:59:11.844
Any driver knows Magnussen will shut
the door on a clumsy move like that.

00:59:11.927 --> 00:59:13.679
[Sonny] Aw, dagnabbit.

00:59:13.762 --> 00:59:15.180
Plan C for "chaos."

00:59:15.264 --> 00:59:16.390
[chuckles]

00:59:16.473 --> 00:59:19.768
[Croft] So that will bring out a
safety car, which always shakes up a race.

00:59:19.852 --> 00:59:22.896
Slows down the leaders,
leaves the field bunched up together,

00:59:22.980 --> 00:59:25.315
and gives teams
the chance for a quick pit stop,

00:59:25.399 --> 00:59:27.734
which only costs half the usual time.

00:59:27.818 --> 00:59:29.278
[Joshua] Safety car. We're boxing, right?

00:59:29.361 --> 00:59:30.612
Standby. Kate,

00:59:30.696 --> 00:59:33.073
shouldn't we take advantage
while the safety car window is open?

00:59:33.156 --> 00:59:35.242
It's early. We gain track position
if we stay out.

00:59:35.325 --> 00:59:38.704
[Rico] Stay out, stay out.
Want you out. Push, push, Joshua.

00:59:38.787 --> 00:59:40.873
[Brundle] So, the midfield moves up
for the moment,

00:59:40.956 --> 00:59:43.292
including Joshua Pearce to P12.

00:59:43.959 --> 00:59:46.211
[Joshua] This guy better not
be messing up my race.

00:59:51.717 --> 00:59:52.718
Where's JP now?

00:59:52.801 --> 00:59:54.261
Currently running P12.

01:00:00.976 --> 01:00:02.936
Okay. Plan C. Be ready.

01:00:03.896 --> 01:00:05.314
He's gonna do it again.

01:00:08.984 --> 01:00:11.320
[Croft] Back marker Hayes
is now down a lap.

01:00:11.403 --> 01:00:14.740
He has to let Bottas pass,
or face a five-second penalty.

01:00:14.823 --> 01:00:17.492
[Brundle] Hayes is making it
very difficult for Bottas.

01:00:17.576 --> 01:00:20.746
Under the rules he has to let him through
before passing three blue flags,

01:00:20.829 --> 01:00:22.497
or risk a penalty.

01:00:22.581 --> 01:00:25.792
Hey, I'm just putting it out there,
but, uh, maybe you should drive.

01:00:27.294 --> 01:00:30.047
[Hugh] Sonny, you've gotten the blue flag.
Let Bottas through.

01:00:30.923 --> 01:00:32.674
[Sonny] Come on, now. Little closer.

01:00:34.635 --> 01:00:36.220
[Hugh] Sonny, do you copy?

01:00:36.303 --> 01:00:38.013
[Sonny] I hear ya. Lettin' him through.

01:00:39.515 --> 01:00:40.849
Whoops, my bad.

01:00:40.933 --> 01:00:42.768
[Croft] And that's his front wing again!

01:00:42.851 --> 01:00:45.729
Oh, that's gonna bring out
another safety car.

01:00:45.812 --> 01:00:48.774
Given that each wing
costs more than £200,000,

01:00:48.857 --> 01:00:51.568
I think the team might want
Sonny to start chipping in there.

01:00:52.194 --> 01:00:53.362
[chuckles]

01:00:56.782 --> 01:00:59.034
[Joshua] Guys, it's another free stop.
Please tell me we're boxing.

01:00:59.117 --> 01:01:00.577
[Rico] Uh, we're checking.

01:01:00.661 --> 01:01:03.205
-Keep him out.
-Stay out. Stay out. You are staying out.

01:01:03.288 --> 01:01:05.541
[Croft] More drivers come in
to take fresh tires,

01:01:05.624 --> 01:01:09.878
but still, Joshua Pearce remains on track.
He's moved up to P11.

01:01:12.714 --> 01:01:14.132
Look who's back.

01:01:17.886 --> 01:01:19.596
I know, I know. Be ready.

01:01:23.225 --> 01:01:24.393
What is he doing?

01:01:26.144 --> 01:01:27.744
I think he's trying to score us a point.

01:01:29.982 --> 01:01:32.192
[Sonny] Tell JP to save his tires.

01:01:33.360 --> 01:01:36.029
Joshua, just take care of
your tires, okay?

01:01:36.113 --> 01:01:37.823
You have to make them last.

01:01:37.906 --> 01:01:40.701
[Joshua] Last? No shit. I will be.

01:01:43.829 --> 01:01:46.623
[Brundle] With four laps to go
in this stop-and-go race,

01:01:46.707 --> 01:01:47.875
thanks to Sonny Hayes,

01:01:47.958 --> 01:01:50.711
the driver helped most is his teammate,
now in tenth.

01:01:50.794 --> 01:01:53.714
With a 12-second gap ahead of Stroll.

01:01:54.214 --> 01:01:56.175
Tell JP to maintain that gap.

01:01:56.258 --> 01:01:57.426
Keep pushing.

01:01:58.635 --> 01:02:01.180
[Joshua] My tires are gone, man.
What are you waiting for?

01:02:01.263 --> 01:02:03.056
Copy that. We have to call it.

01:02:03.140 --> 01:02:04.600
He's losing over a second every lap.

01:02:05.309 --> 01:02:06.476
Stand by.

01:02:06.560 --> 01:02:10.314
[Croft] Into turn two. Hayes battles with
the Williams and pushes it wide.

01:02:10.397 --> 01:02:12.274
Seriously, what are we waiting for?

01:02:15.819 --> 01:02:16.862
[Croft] Sonny's off the track.

01:02:16.945 --> 01:02:19.698
He's gone too far over. [groans]

01:02:19.781 --> 01:02:21.158
And that's gonna cause damage.

01:02:21.241 --> 01:02:23.911
-Plan C.
-[laughs]

01:02:24.536 --> 01:02:26.246
Oopsie. Sorry, guys.

01:02:26.330 --> 01:02:30.250
[Croft] That's the third safety car
involving the Apex GP driver,

01:02:30.334 --> 01:02:33.420
bringing the Hungarian Grand Prix
to an absolute crawl.

01:02:33.962 --> 01:02:36.131
A sub three-second stop,
and he'll keep P10.

01:02:36.215 --> 01:02:37.549
Box, Joshua. Box, box, box.

01:02:37.633 --> 01:02:39.176
[Joshua] Copy. Coming in.

01:02:41.595 --> 01:02:42.804
What did you say?

01:02:42.888 --> 01:02:45.349
[Brundle] Joshua Pearce
finally gets to pit.

01:02:45.432 --> 01:02:49.102
[Croft] And with a quick stop here,
he could stay in the top ten.

01:02:56.985 --> 01:02:58.028
[grunts]

01:02:58.111 --> 01:03:00.113
[Brundle] This is critical.

01:03:00.197 --> 01:03:04.535
Pearce must beat Stroll to the
pit exit line to maintain tenth place.

01:03:06.078 --> 01:03:07.371
[Croft] And he's done it!

01:03:07.454 --> 01:03:11.208
With yellow flags out, all the cars
are forced to hold track position,

01:03:11.291 --> 01:03:13.419
-meaning that thanks to Sonny Hayes…
-[Joshua] Let's go!

01:03:13.502 --> 01:03:15.712
-…the race ends under a safety car.
-Yeah!

01:03:15.796 --> 01:03:17.631
-Vegas!
-What? Whoa!

01:03:18.590 --> 01:03:20.884
Hey, yeah. Fuck you. [laughs]

01:03:22.970 --> 01:03:25.305
Yeah! [laughs, grunts]

01:03:25.389 --> 01:03:26.723
Yes, baby!

01:03:26.807 --> 01:03:29.810
[crowd cheering]

01:03:37.734 --> 01:03:39.403
[Joshua chuckles] You're crazy, bro.

01:03:39.486 --> 01:03:42.030
[Sonny] It's just tenth.
What are you smiling about?

01:03:44.366 --> 01:03:46.201
[Croft] And behind our podium placings,

01:03:46.285 --> 01:03:48.871
Hamilton and Piastri
complete the top five,

01:03:48.954 --> 01:03:50.747
-and Joshua Pearce in tenth…
-Wow.

01:03:50.831 --> 01:03:53.458
-…scoring Expensify Apex GP…
-Yeah, baby.

01:03:53.542 --> 01:03:55.127
…their first ever point.

01:03:57.379 --> 01:04:00.007
Did you see me? Crazy, right?

01:04:00.090 --> 01:04:02.926
-[Sonny] A deal's a deal. I finished.
-Yeah, in last place.

01:04:03.010 --> 01:04:04.970
Sounds great when you say it.

01:04:11.143 --> 01:04:13.104
[interviewer] I know you have to go
see the stewards later,

01:04:13.187 --> 01:04:14.772
what do you think they're
gonna make of your race today?

01:04:14.855 --> 01:04:16.940
Well, I have to admit,
you guys got this one right.

01:04:17.024 --> 01:04:19.776
-I'm, like… Thank you. Thank you.
-Good job. Yeah.

01:04:20.319 --> 01:04:23.363
I'm still a bit rusty and, you know,
finding my way with this car,

01:04:23.447 --> 01:04:24.865
but I'm confident we'll get there.

01:04:24.948 --> 01:04:28.827
A rope-a-dope at Silverstone,
a demolition derby here in Hungary…

01:04:28.911 --> 01:04:30.204
You've been banned from casinos.

01:04:30.287 --> 01:04:32.665
Are you trying to get banned from F1?
Take the whole team down with you?

01:04:32.748 --> 01:04:35.042
Tell you what, Don,
what do you say we make a bet?

01:04:35.125 --> 01:04:37.294
Your £10 against my 10 grand.

01:04:37.377 --> 01:04:40.214
We place at Monza, I win your 10.
We don't, you win mine.

01:04:40.297 --> 01:04:41.882
-[scoffs]
-Let's do this, man.

01:04:41.965 --> 01:04:43.365
Put your money where your mouth is.

01:04:44.801 --> 01:04:46.386
What the hell? I'll take that.

01:04:46.470 --> 01:04:48.222
-Thank you.
-Thank you so much.

01:04:48.305 --> 01:04:50.891
Hey. No more press.

01:04:50.974 --> 01:04:53.143
No, Sonny, you don't wanna make
the media your enemy.

01:04:53.227 --> 01:04:54.478
And you'll be fined.

01:04:54.561 --> 01:04:55.687
Take it out of my paycheck.

01:04:56.271 --> 01:04:57.648
We don't pay you enough.

01:04:58.774 --> 01:05:00.234
You know, I have to say.

01:05:01.735 --> 01:05:02.778
I kinda like it.

01:05:04.154 --> 01:05:07.491
It's very sort of punk rock for the brand.

01:05:07.574 --> 01:05:08.825
[Peter sighs]

01:05:10.577 --> 01:05:11.578
[Ruben] Hmm.

01:05:20.379 --> 01:05:21.630
Let's run it again.

01:05:30.097 --> 01:05:31.431
How long's he been in there?

01:05:32.015 --> 01:05:35.602
All day. Playing with different
tire pressures, ride heights.

01:05:36.937 --> 01:05:38.188
What were his times?

01:05:38.689 --> 01:05:39.773
He found half a second.

01:05:45.404 --> 01:05:46.738
Give me the same setup as him.

01:05:47.447 --> 01:05:49.616
[typing]

01:06:08.302 --> 01:06:10.262
It must be late. I'm seeing double.

01:06:10.345 --> 01:06:11.346
[Kate chuckles]

01:06:12.389 --> 01:06:14.850
A deal's a deal.
I'm building her for combat.

01:06:16.393 --> 01:06:17.477
At the Dutch Grand Prix,

01:06:17.561 --> 01:06:21.940
you'll be entering the Tarzan Corner
at 322 kilometers per hour.

01:06:22.024 --> 01:06:24.193
Yeah. Too late to change my mind?

01:06:24.276 --> 01:06:25.903
-Yeah.
-[chuckles]

01:06:32.326 --> 01:06:34.119
To answer your question,

01:06:34.203 --> 01:06:37.873
I was in aerospace at Lockheed
when Ruben came in and…

01:06:38.874 --> 01:06:40.959
He liked my work, liked my attitude,

01:06:41.043 --> 01:06:45.172
and he sold me on the thrill of fighting
to the death for a tenth of a second.

01:06:46.381 --> 01:06:49.718
Traveling the world, the roar of a crowd…

01:06:50.302 --> 01:06:53.347
So, I ran the idea past my husband.

01:06:55.933 --> 01:06:58.727
Who swiftly became my ex-husband.

01:07:01.146 --> 01:07:02.147
Good night.

01:07:03.106 --> 01:07:04.107
Good night.

01:07:26.797 --> 01:07:29.132
[line ringing]

01:07:29.216 --> 01:07:30.717
[Ruben] Do you know what time it is?

01:07:31.552 --> 01:07:32.845
All right.

01:07:32.928 --> 01:07:34.429
Tell me about the kid.

01:07:41.270 --> 01:07:43.146
Okay, here's another one my dad would say.

01:07:43.230 --> 01:07:45.357
"Slow is smooth, smooth is fast."

01:07:46.275 --> 01:07:48.652
For what it's worth. One more time around?

01:07:48.735 --> 01:07:51.822
-Just one? Come on. Is that all?
-[Sonny chuckles]

01:07:51.905 --> 01:07:53.407
-[grunts]
-I'd never live with myself,

01:07:53.490 --> 01:07:55.909
if I can't keep up with you, Mr. 1990s.

01:07:55.993 --> 01:07:57.536
-[chuckles]
-Let's go!

01:07:58.078 --> 01:08:00.414
Joining us today,
we have Kaspar Smolinski,

01:08:00.497 --> 01:08:02.624
Zak Brown and Fred Vasseur.

01:08:02.708 --> 01:08:06.128
Now, Kaspar, can we start with you,
after what was a fantastic result

01:08:06.211 --> 01:08:08.547
-for the team in Hungary last time out…
-Thank you.

01:08:08.630 --> 01:08:13.844
…but Sonny has got you skirting the line
of penalties and violations.

01:08:13.927 --> 01:08:16.137
Is this your only strategy,

01:08:16.220 --> 01:08:19.140
and have you got any spare parts left
in the factory?

01:08:19.224 --> 01:08:20.725
[audience chuckling]

01:08:20.809 --> 01:08:22.185
We compete like everybody else.

01:08:22.269 --> 01:08:23.604
Race models change.

01:08:23.687 --> 01:08:25.272
We must adapt, huh?

01:08:25.856 --> 01:08:27.399
Well, Zak, can we bring you in on this?

01:08:27.482 --> 01:08:32.613
Because you've faced Hayes before,
you know the gray areas in which he works.

01:08:33.363 --> 01:08:36.575
Certainly do. Uh, first of all,
he's a lot grayer now.

01:08:36.658 --> 01:08:38.660
-[audience chuckles]
-And, uh, we keep tabs on him,

01:08:38.743 --> 01:08:40.037
you know, back there behind us.

01:08:40.120 --> 01:08:43.207
-[audience chuckles]
-And Fred, any concerns from Ferrari?

01:08:43.290 --> 01:08:45.375
What does Ferrari think of Apex?

01:08:46.126 --> 01:08:49.171
-We don't.
-[audience chuckling]

01:08:49.254 --> 01:08:51.173
["Hold Me" playing]

01:09:03.185 --> 01:09:08.106
[fans clamoring] Sonny! You're the best!

01:09:10.108 --> 01:09:12.944
[Kate] A better qualifying yesterday
gets us in the thick of things.

01:09:13.028 --> 01:09:15.488
P10, P15. [inhales sharply]

01:09:15.572 --> 01:09:17.282
So we're gonna go for a two stop.

01:09:17.366 --> 01:09:22.162
Medium-hard-medium, that's plan A.
Final stint, we go hards for plan B.

01:09:22.246 --> 01:09:24.539
So, on this,
do you have any track concerns?

01:09:24.622 --> 01:09:26.625
Don't look at me. Look at him.

01:09:28.417 --> 01:09:29.670
It's good for JP.

01:09:30.212 --> 01:09:31.212
Start me on hards.

01:09:32.089 --> 01:09:34.800
Nah, the track's cooled down.
You won't have any grip.

01:09:34.883 --> 01:09:36.176
That's right.

01:09:36.844 --> 01:09:39.595
For three weeks,
all the talk's been how reckless I am.

01:09:40.180 --> 01:09:42.765
Everyone's wondering
if I'm gonna drive 'em off track,

01:09:42.850 --> 01:09:45.310
which means no one's
gonna be watching out for him.

01:09:47.437 --> 01:09:50.983
Today, you win us this race.

01:09:58.282 --> 01:10:01.618
[Croft] Twenty laps down here at Monza,
and the pack have been split.

01:10:01.702 --> 01:10:04.413
The leaders are pulling away,
led by Max Verstappen,

01:10:04.496 --> 01:10:06.957
with Joshua Pearce back in P10.

01:10:07.040 --> 01:10:09.751
[Brundle] Meanwhile, Sonny Hayes
is holding up the rest of the pack,

01:10:09.835 --> 01:10:12.171
stuck behind him in a DRS train.

01:10:13.130 --> 01:10:16.800
[Croft] Pearce looks to be in
a great position to finish in the top ten,

01:10:16.884 --> 01:10:19.803
and maybe even a run to the podium.

01:10:21.889 --> 01:10:24.058
[Brundle] But there's still a long way
to go in this race,

01:10:24.141 --> 01:10:28.103
and with rain potentially forecast,
anything can happen.

01:10:28.687 --> 01:10:30.063
Tires are gone. Coming in.

01:10:30.147 --> 01:10:31.481
Yeah, copy. Box. Box.

01:10:32.065 --> 01:10:34.568
[Croft] Apex GP is prepping
a fresh set of tires for Hayes.

01:10:34.651 --> 01:10:38.405
That's gonna bring in
all the other teams to avoid the undercut.

01:10:38.488 --> 01:10:40.073
Uh, changed my mind.

01:10:40.157 --> 01:10:43.702
[Croft] But, no! He's staying out,
with the cars behind him all scrambling

01:10:43.785 --> 01:10:48.248
to get on fresh tires that apparently
he doesn't think he needs anymore.

01:10:48.332 --> 01:10:50.834
Should we just do the opposite
of what he tells us to do?

01:10:50.918 --> 01:10:52.878
Stand by till I lose my tires.

01:10:53.921 --> 01:10:57.007
-I thought he had lost his tires.
-[stammers] I think he means literally.

01:10:59.968 --> 01:11:01.970
Puncture, left rear. Coming in.

01:11:02.054 --> 01:11:04.014
[Croft] And there goes Hayes's tires.

01:11:04.097 --> 01:11:06.517
[Brundle] That's quite a mess,
gravel on the track.

01:11:06.600 --> 01:11:09.978
That will bring out the virtual safety car
for a quick sweep.

01:11:10.062 --> 01:11:11.522
[Croft] So the race gets neutralized.

01:11:11.605 --> 01:11:15.317
Everyone slows down
to 40% of their racing speed,

01:11:15.400 --> 01:11:17.402
and all the race strategies
will get a reset.

01:11:17.486 --> 01:11:20.531
[Brundle] And that is why this is
the perfect time to take a pit stop.

01:11:20.614 --> 01:11:21.990
While you're in the pit lane,

01:11:22.074 --> 01:11:25.118
your opponents
are restricted to a much slower pace

01:11:25.202 --> 01:11:27.913
and you're not going to lose
as much track position when you rejoin.

01:11:27.996 --> 01:11:31.250
-I take it I'm staying out, right?
-Copy. Joshua, stay out. Stay out.

01:11:31.333 --> 01:11:34.002
-We want you out to gain track position.
-Copy.

01:11:34.086 --> 01:11:36.088
Up is down, down is up.

01:11:43.053 --> 01:11:46.306
[Croft] Sonny Hayes hesitated
before he left his pit box,

01:11:46.390 --> 01:11:49.226
and he's come out just in front
of Max Verstappen.

01:11:49.309 --> 01:11:50.561
[Max] That was naughty.

01:11:50.644 --> 01:11:52.855
[Brundle] Hayes has slowed a bit
in the pit lane,

01:11:52.938 --> 01:11:56.900
which will cost the Red Bull
and the two Ferraris precious time.

01:11:56.984 --> 01:11:58.193
Push, Joshua. Push.

01:11:58.277 --> 01:11:59.820
You are now P4. P4.

01:11:59.903 --> 01:12:04.199
[Croft] Who's coming up from behind?
Here he is, Joshua Pearce.

01:12:04.283 --> 01:12:06.076
-Let's see! Let's go!
-Yes!

01:12:06.159 --> 01:12:07.787
-This is all playing into his hands…
-Wow.

01:12:07.870 --> 01:12:10.247
…at the moment.
Could be a dream afternoon.

01:12:10.330 --> 01:12:13.208
But can Hayes hold Verstappen
for a little bit longer?

01:12:13.292 --> 01:12:16.336
Verstappen tries into turn one,
nothing doing there.

01:12:16.420 --> 01:12:19.214
Gets the better exit.
Through the Curva Grande we go.

01:12:19.298 --> 01:12:21.550
-Damn, he's good.
-Verstappen's trying to get past.

01:12:21.633 --> 01:12:23.594
[Brundle] Sonny Hayes
looking carefully in his mirrors.

01:12:23.677 --> 01:12:25.929
He must let Max Verstappen through.

01:12:26.013 --> 01:12:27.639
Yeah, I deserved that.

01:12:27.723 --> 01:12:30.017
[Brundle] And Max shows his disapproval,

01:12:30.100 --> 01:12:33.770
and I don't blame him, as they head down
towards the second chicane.

01:12:33.854 --> 01:12:36.481
[Croft]
And through goes Joshua Pearce in P4,

01:12:36.565 --> 01:12:39.193
now much closer to the front of the pack.

01:12:39.276 --> 01:12:40.277
[thunder rumbles]

01:12:42.112 --> 01:12:44.907
[Brundle] Just seven laps to go,
and here comes the rain.

01:12:44.990 --> 01:12:48.118
[Croft] Let's see who plays it safe
with a switch to the intermediate tire,

01:12:48.202 --> 01:12:50.746
and who might gamble
to stay out on slicks.

01:12:57.169 --> 01:12:58.963
It's getting tricky out here, guys.
What's the plan?

01:12:59.046 --> 01:13:02.966
You're running P4. We think P2 and P3
are switching to inters for safety,

01:13:03.050 --> 01:13:04.760
and it looks like P1 is staying out.

01:13:04.843 --> 01:13:06.723
-What do you wanna do?
-What's Sonny gonna do?

01:13:07.471 --> 01:13:08.889
Take a wild guess.

01:13:08.972 --> 01:13:10.532
-[Joshua] I'm staying out.
-Copy that.

01:13:11.600 --> 01:13:14.978
[Brundle] And the two Ferraris
come in for intermediate tires.

01:13:15.062 --> 01:13:17.439
Let's see who else
decides to play it safe.

01:13:17.523 --> 01:13:21.485
[Croft] And as George Russell pits,
Joshua Pearce moves into P2.

01:13:21.568 --> 01:13:23.111
[cheering]

01:13:23.195 --> 01:13:25.656
Sonny, Joshua is staying out on slicks.
If he can hold on and find a dry line,

01:13:25.739 --> 01:13:26.823
he's gonna finish second.

01:13:26.907 --> 01:13:27.950
Second's not enough.

01:13:29.326 --> 01:13:30.452
Damn it.

01:13:30.994 --> 01:13:32.704
Okay, coming in for inters.

01:13:32.788 --> 01:13:35.415
-Inters, inters.
-Let's go! He's coming in!

01:13:41.922 --> 01:13:44.299
-How far behind me are they?
-Thirty seconds.

01:13:44.842 --> 01:13:46.718
Oh, my God.
He's gonna take out Verstappen.

01:13:46.802 --> 01:13:48.554
Let me know
when they hit the main straight.

01:13:48.637 --> 01:13:52.057
Don't tell him! They penalize both cars.
They will take the win away.

01:13:52.140 --> 01:13:53.141
Just trust me, will ya?

01:13:55.644 --> 01:13:57.646
I'm pushing but I can't catch him.

01:13:57.729 --> 01:13:59.732
[Brundle] As the race leaders
approach the main straight,

01:13:59.815 --> 01:14:03.110
Sonny Hayes is in another standoff
over team strategy.

01:14:03.193 --> 01:14:04.695
-Now.
-No!

01:14:05.946 --> 01:14:08.574
[Croft] Finally,
Hayes back out onto the track,

01:14:08.657 --> 01:14:10.409
and just in front of Verstappen.

01:14:10.492 --> 01:14:13.537
Now he'll get a blue flag here
so Verstappen can get past,

01:14:13.620 --> 01:14:18.041
but until then, the Dutch driver
is caught up in Hayes's dirty air.

01:14:18.125 --> 01:14:20.043
[Brundle] With every turn he hangs on,

01:14:20.127 --> 01:14:22.629
he slows Verstappen
a fraction of a second,

01:14:22.713 --> 01:14:26.133
providing Joshua Pearce
one last chance to catch up.

01:14:26.216 --> 01:14:27.496
I can see him. I'm almost there.

01:14:29.344 --> 01:14:30.345
Tell JP to follow me.

01:14:30.429 --> 01:14:34.433
-Copy. Uh, Joshua, Sonny is your tow.
-I'm right behind him.

01:14:35.601 --> 01:14:37.227
[Croft] Verstappen pulls away then.

01:14:37.311 --> 01:14:40.105
But now, onto the rear wing
of his teammate's car

01:14:40.189 --> 01:14:41.523
comes Joshua Pearce.

01:14:41.607 --> 01:14:44.026
[Brundle] Pearce picks up
the slipstream from Hayes,

01:14:44.109 --> 01:14:47.196
gaining time,
but driving blind in the spray.

01:14:49.865 --> 01:14:51.992
Come on. Stay with me. Stay with me now.

01:14:58.582 --> 01:14:59.750
Pass. Pass.

01:14:59.833 --> 01:15:01.293
-Overtake him. Overtake.
-Copy.

01:15:01.376 --> 01:15:06.131
[Croft] He's been gaining, and boom!
Joshua Pearce slingshots past Sonny Hayes,

01:15:06.215 --> 01:15:09.301
-and now is in striking distance of P1.
-[cheering]

01:15:09.384 --> 01:15:11.845
Tell JP to wait for the straight
into turn one.

01:15:11.929 --> 01:15:13.305
Be patient.

01:15:13.388 --> 01:15:15.516
-Straight at turn one.
-[crew member] Copy.

01:15:15.599 --> 01:15:19.853
Joshua, Sonny says wait for the straight.
The straight into turn one.

01:15:21.355 --> 01:15:23.148
[Joshua] I'm right there.

01:15:23.232 --> 01:15:24.441
I've got him.

01:15:25.317 --> 01:15:27.736
[Brundle] Pearce is right on the gearbox
of Verstappen,

01:15:27.819 --> 01:15:30.656
down the back straight
at over 200 miles an hour.

01:15:30.739 --> 01:15:32.157
I see an opening. Going for it.

01:15:32.783 --> 01:15:34.868
[Brundle] The rookie attacks in 11.

01:15:35.369 --> 01:15:36.370
No, no!

01:15:37.829 --> 01:15:39.540
[Croft]
Pearce pulls alongside the Red Bull,

01:15:39.623 --> 01:15:42.334
he's wheels ahead,
for the first time ever…

01:15:42.417 --> 01:15:45.337
Apex GP… Oh, no!

01:15:45.420 --> 01:15:46.797
No!

01:16:05.607 --> 01:16:08.068
-[sad music playing]
-[no audible dialogue]

01:17:01.205 --> 01:17:06.001
[monitor beeping]

01:17:14.301 --> 01:17:16.637
[reporter speaking Italian on television]

01:17:19.765 --> 01:17:20.807
[sighs]

01:17:22.726 --> 01:17:24.645
[sighs, in English] For God's sake.

01:17:33.946 --> 01:17:36.573
-[Ruben] Bernadette, how's he doing?
-[Bernadette grunts]

01:17:36.657 --> 01:17:37.908
He's stable.

01:17:37.991 --> 01:17:39.660
He's resting now.

01:17:40.661 --> 01:17:42.412
[exhales heavily, mutters]

01:17:43.038 --> 01:17:44.623
Very happy to hear it.

01:17:44.706 --> 01:17:47.209
I'm so sorry for what happened.
It was clearly...

01:17:47.292 --> 01:17:49.461
Sonny, over here, please.

01:17:56.051 --> 01:17:57.511
[sighing]

01:18:03.976 --> 01:18:06.812
Um, I just wanna say I've been...

01:18:06.895 --> 01:18:08.480
Joshua says you're an asshole.

01:18:11.108 --> 01:18:12.609
Yeah, that tracks.

01:18:12.693 --> 01:18:15.070
I think you're a dangerous asshole.

01:18:17.030 --> 01:18:19.658
-Ms. Pearce...
-You're part of the same team, right?

01:18:19.741 --> 01:18:20.951
Looking out for each other.

01:18:21.034 --> 01:18:23.745
Except you had him
doing something so dangerous

01:18:23.829 --> 01:18:25.998
it almost got him killed.

01:18:27.457 --> 01:18:30.502
-Okay, listen...
-No, you listen to me.

01:18:31.336 --> 01:18:33.255
This is my son.

01:18:34.381 --> 01:18:36.633
And if anything…
anything else happens to him,

01:18:36.717 --> 01:18:38.051
I'm coming after you.

01:18:38.135 --> 01:18:40.721
And you better pray I don't put you
in a bed next to Joshua

01:18:40.804 --> 01:18:42.848
for a very, very long time.

01:18:43.599 --> 01:18:44.600
Clear?

01:18:47.060 --> 01:18:48.395
Sure.

01:18:52.399 --> 01:18:53.901
[sighs]

01:19:02.201 --> 01:19:04.995
[reporters murmuring, clamoring]

01:19:05.829 --> 01:19:06.955
Sonny, Sonny.

01:19:07.039 --> 01:19:09.917
Do you think Joshua blames you
for what happened in Monza?

01:19:13.629 --> 01:19:16.590
-[reporters clamoring]
-[reporter] Sonny, come on.

01:19:16.673 --> 01:19:18.967
It was clear
that you were running his race.

01:19:19.051 --> 01:19:22.596
Look, you kept him out on slick tires,
in dangerous conditions,

01:19:22.679 --> 01:19:26.350
that even if you told him not to pass,
wasn't the accident inevitable?

01:19:26.433 --> 01:19:28.477
-If I may. If I may.
-[reporters clamoring]

01:19:28.560 --> 01:19:30.604
Joshua's back home, recovering.

01:19:30.687 --> 01:19:32.856
We are expecting his return
in a few weeks.

01:19:32.940 --> 01:19:38.779
Until that moment, our reserve driver,
Luca Cortez right there, will drive and…

01:19:38.862 --> 01:19:41.448
-Next man up.
-[clamoring] Answer the question!

01:19:43.825 --> 01:19:46.912
[Buxton] A chaotic week
for Expensify Apex GP,

01:19:46.995 --> 01:19:49.873
and again, it's Sonny Hayes at the center.

01:19:49.957 --> 01:19:53.627
Many are blaming him for his teammate's
horrific accident at Monza.

01:19:53.710 --> 01:19:58.215
His high-stakes, gambling style of racing
has the whole grid on edge,

01:19:58.298 --> 01:20:02.135
and while the controversy continues
over who was to blame,

01:20:02.219 --> 01:20:05.722
doctors have said that Pearce
will miss the next three races,

01:20:05.806 --> 01:20:10.143
due to the burns suffered on his hands
as he begins his road to recovery.

01:20:17.651 --> 01:20:20.028
[Kate] Today, we're going
with our combat upgrade.

01:20:20.696 --> 01:20:24.116
The revised shapes will improve
the flow field under the floor,

01:20:24.199 --> 01:20:28.078
allowing us to run in dirty air
with minimal loss of performance.

01:20:28.161 --> 01:20:30.873
Means we have to keep the field close
at all times,

01:20:31.373 --> 01:20:34.710
and as for this week's plan C…

01:20:40.757 --> 01:20:44.469
They've docked us to the back of the grid
'cause they don't like the way we drive.

01:20:44.553 --> 01:20:46.513
Fine. Fuck 'em.

01:20:47.431 --> 01:20:50.642
'Cause if we can pick up
a tenth of a second from you,

01:20:50.726 --> 01:20:54.396
and from you, and you, and me…

01:20:54.479 --> 01:20:57.191
If everyone in this room
can make one critical contribution,

01:20:57.274 --> 01:20:58.567
that's a second every lap.

01:20:59.276 --> 01:21:03.822
And after 72 laps, that's the difference
between last and first.

01:21:05.866 --> 01:21:06.992
Plan C…

01:21:08.619 --> 01:21:10.287
Plan C's for combat.

01:21:12.789 --> 01:21:17.628
Combat, combat, combat.

01:21:17.711 --> 01:21:23.425
[crew chanting] Combat, combat,
combat, combat.

01:21:23.509 --> 01:21:25.135
[chanting continues]

01:21:25.219 --> 01:21:26.387
[driving electronic song playing]

01:21:26.470 --> 01:21:30.474
♪ I don't wanna lose my mind
I don't wanna lose myself ♪

01:21:30.557 --> 01:21:34.853
♪ Tell me if I crossed a line
I ain't trying to hurt myself ♪

01:21:34.937 --> 01:21:40.067
♪ Didn't want to call your name
Only got myself to blame ♪

01:21:40.150 --> 01:21:41.818
♪ Oh, yeah ♪

01:21:41.902 --> 01:21:44.071
♪ In my world, in my mind
Always running out of time ♪

01:21:44.154 --> 01:21:45.239
[crowd cheering]

01:21:45.322 --> 01:21:47.407
[Croft] And that's Hayes
in the upgraded Apex.

01:21:47.491 --> 01:21:50.827
Now the team were penalized
back to last place after Monza,

01:21:50.911 --> 01:21:55.165
but here he is, coming from the cellar,
passing his new teammate, Luca Cortez.

01:21:55.249 --> 01:21:57.626
♪ …still I wait for you ♪

01:21:57.709 --> 01:21:59.211
[vocalizes]

01:21:59.294 --> 01:22:00.754
♪ Yeah, it feels… ♪

01:22:00.838 --> 01:22:03.715
[Croft] Round the banking,
Hayes has got past Ocon.

01:22:03.799 --> 01:22:07.553
This is brilliant last lap drama.
What a fantastic finish.

01:22:07.636 --> 01:22:09.137
[laughs]

01:22:10.931 --> 01:22:12.474
[exclaims, chuckles]

01:22:12.558 --> 01:22:17.479
♪ Ain't no way to tell
Which way it's gonna go ♪

01:22:17.563 --> 01:22:21.024
♪ But it feels ♪

01:22:21.108 --> 01:22:24.987
♪ So good I might just lose my mind ♪

01:22:25.070 --> 01:22:29.241
♪ No question if it's wrong or right ♪

01:22:29.825 --> 01:22:33.495
♪ And now it's too late
No way to take it slow ♪

01:22:44.047 --> 01:22:46.508
[Brundle] Another fearless attack
from Hayes.

01:22:46.592 --> 01:22:49.428
And here's where the Apex GP
has found strength.

01:22:49.511 --> 01:22:52.681
Three-tenths gained every lap,
and in the corners alone.

01:22:53.348 --> 01:22:56.685
♪ I don't wanna lose my mind
I don't wanna lose myself ♪

01:22:56.768 --> 01:22:58.562
[Croft] Scrapping away on the last lap,

01:22:58.645 --> 01:23:01.899
Sonny Hayes gets the inside line,
but he can't quite get past.

01:23:01.982 --> 01:23:04.610
George Russell will hang on here
for sixth place,

01:23:04.693 --> 01:23:07.988
but this is Apex GP's best ever finish.

01:23:08.071 --> 01:23:11.450
-It's a valiant seventh.
-Combat, I love it!

01:23:11.533 --> 01:23:14.494
[crowd cheering]

01:23:14.578 --> 01:23:16.618
[manager] Every race you miss,
fans just forget you.

01:23:17.039 --> 01:23:19.291
Sonny always seems to be one step ahead.

01:23:20.709 --> 01:23:24.338
You never know.
Sonny may be a saboteur, Josh.

01:23:24.421 --> 01:23:25.506
He may be a saboteur.

01:23:25.589 --> 01:23:27.299
-[crowd cheering]
-[song continues]

01:23:27.382 --> 01:23:30.469
♪ Yeah it feels ♪

01:23:30.552 --> 01:23:34.848
♪ So good I might just lose my mind ♪

01:23:34.932 --> 01:23:37.518
♪ No question if it's wrong or right ♪

01:23:37.601 --> 01:23:40.103
[Croft] …and they go wheel to wheel,
Verstappen and Leclerc.

01:23:40.187 --> 01:23:43.398
Verstappen will have the inside.
Perez goes round the outside.

01:23:43.482 --> 01:23:45.817
Perez makes contact with Charles Leclerc

01:23:45.901 --> 01:23:50.364
as Sonny Hayes threads that Apex GP car
through the midfield.

01:24:01.416 --> 01:24:02.709
♪ Yeah ♪

01:24:02.793 --> 01:24:04.628
♪ Bounce back
When the bottles is on me ♪

01:24:04.711 --> 01:24:07.005
♪ I'm pushin' a new pen
Rewriting the story ♪

01:24:07.089 --> 01:24:09.091
♪ Hello to my old ways
Goodbye to the nosebleeds ♪

01:24:09.174 --> 01:24:11.885
♪ You fighting to stay here
You probably OD'ing ♪

01:24:11.969 --> 01:24:14.054
♪ Ain't finna pop for no reason ♪

01:24:14.137 --> 01:24:15.973
♪ I don't throw shots, I run legions ♪

01:24:16.056 --> 01:24:17.683
♪ I been goin' over the top
Where no queen been ♪

01:24:17.766 --> 01:24:19.685
♪ Die with with no regrets
This is my season ♪

01:24:19.768 --> 01:24:21.436
[Croft] Talk about leaving it late.

01:24:21.520 --> 01:24:25.399
Hayes squeezes through on the inside,
and with a run to the line now,

01:24:25.482 --> 01:24:28.402
for their best position ever, P5.

01:24:28.485 --> 01:24:30.404
[Brundle] Give the design team a bonus,

01:24:30.487 --> 01:24:33.156
because the upgrade
has completely changed this car.

01:24:33.240 --> 01:24:35.409
[Croft] And if Joshua Pearce is watching,

01:24:35.492 --> 01:24:38.412
well, he must be thinking,
"What might have been?"

01:24:38.495 --> 01:24:40.372
♪ Yeah, it feels ♪

01:24:40.455 --> 01:24:43.917
♪ So good I might just lose my mind ♪

01:24:44.001 --> 01:24:46.044
He's treating you like a pawn, Josh.

01:24:46.128 --> 01:24:49.798
-Be a knight! Be a knight! Be a knight!
-[bicycle bell ringing]

01:24:53.802 --> 01:24:55.679
[Croft]
Who would have believed this weeks ago?

01:24:55.762 --> 01:24:59.725
Expensify Apex GP
has the racing world on notice.

01:24:59.808 --> 01:25:02.728
[crowd chanting] Apex! Apex! Apex!

01:25:02.811 --> 01:25:05.230
[chanting continues]

01:25:07.399 --> 01:25:12.905
[Brundle] Someone call the 1990s.
Sonny Hayes, if you missed him, he's back.

01:25:12.988 --> 01:25:15.157
[song ends]

01:25:20.037 --> 01:25:22.623
Last one up buys breakfast. [chuckles]

01:25:23.332 --> 01:25:25.876
[indistinct chattering]

01:25:30.672 --> 01:25:31.757
Look who's back.

01:25:32.633 --> 01:25:36.887
[crew cheering, applauding]

01:25:38.347 --> 01:25:39.389
Hello.

01:25:46.438 --> 01:25:48.106
Good to have you back, JP. We missed you.

01:25:49.316 --> 01:25:51.318
[dramatic rap song playing]

01:25:59.576 --> 01:26:04.039
♪ This for the underdogs
This for the underdogs, underdogs ♪

01:26:04.122 --> 01:26:07.918
♪ Slide out the garage
I got a hundred cars ♪

01:26:08.001 --> 01:26:10.087
♪ This for the underdogs ♪

01:26:10.170 --> 01:26:12.172
♪ The teller just ask me
How I want the cashy ♪

01:26:12.256 --> 01:26:13.758
[crowd chanting] Apex! Apex! Apex! Apex!

01:26:13.841 --> 01:26:15.384
♪ I told 'em a hundred large ♪

01:26:15.467 --> 01:26:18.178
♪ I want them gold wraps
Put it up double R ♪

01:26:19.304 --> 01:26:22.766
♪ Tell 'em get out the way
4x4 big Phantom, supe ♪

01:26:22.850 --> 01:26:26.270
♪ They thought I was canceled
I piped up and flipped the channel ♪

01:26:32.943 --> 01:26:35.612
[Croft] It's lights out and away we go!

01:26:35.696 --> 01:26:37.197
And it's a decent start,

01:26:37.281 --> 01:26:40.242
and everyone keeping it clean
as into La Source we go.

01:26:40.325 --> 01:26:41.827
Ferrari ahead of Red Bull,

01:26:41.910 --> 01:26:47.416
but here the two Apex GP cars
looking to work together as a team.

01:26:47.499 --> 01:26:50.627
It's a welcome back to the track
for Joshua Pearce,

01:26:50.711 --> 01:26:52.337
and Sonny Hayes glad to see him,

01:26:52.421 --> 01:26:56.049
as they slice their way
through positions four and five.

01:26:56.133 --> 01:26:58.093
And onto the Kemmel Straight we go.

01:26:58.802 --> 01:27:03.265
Now approaching top speed,
Sonny Hayes ahead of Joshua Pearce.

01:27:03.348 --> 01:27:06.852
He's showing no ill effects
from that time off after the crash.

01:27:06.935 --> 01:27:10.480
The car's working beautifully.
They're working as a team.

01:27:10.564 --> 01:27:14.401
But hang on, Pearce right on his tail,
using the slipstream.

01:27:14.484 --> 01:27:16.820
Is he about to try and overtake?

01:27:16.904 --> 01:27:19.656
Into the chicane we go
and they touch wheels!

01:27:19.740 --> 01:27:21.658
-This is disaster for Apex…
-[exclaiming]

01:27:21.742 --> 01:27:25.495
…as out goes Sonny Hayes
and into the gravel!

01:27:26.955 --> 01:27:28.248
Assholes! [grunts]

01:27:28.832 --> 01:27:31.376
[Brundle]
What is happening with this team?

01:27:31.460 --> 01:27:35.714
Their first race back together,
and they've run into each other.

01:27:37.841 --> 01:27:38.884
-You did great, Joshua.
-Well done, mate.

01:27:38.967 --> 01:27:40.385
[laughs]

01:27:40.469 --> 01:27:41.720
Whoo! [grunts]

01:27:42.262 --> 01:27:44.556
You pull that shit again,
I will knock your teeth out.

01:27:44.640 --> 01:27:46.392
Oh, no one gets past us
without a fight, right?

01:27:46.475 --> 01:27:48.561
Oh, is this funny?
You think you got a seat next year?

01:27:48.644 --> 01:27:50.687
'Cause you just cut your chances in half.

01:27:50.771 --> 01:27:53.148
-That's how dumb you are.
-You failed. You failed!

01:27:53.232 --> 01:27:55.112
-Why should I listen to you anyway, man?
-Hey.

01:27:55.943 --> 01:27:57.069
[exhales heavily]

01:27:57.152 --> 01:27:59.780
Look, man.
I don't give two shits about you.

01:27:59.863 --> 01:28:02.115
You wanna sabotage your career,
you go right ahead.

01:28:02.199 --> 01:28:04.535
I've seen hundreds of guys
with your talent come and go.

01:28:04.618 --> 01:28:06.078
No one cares!

01:28:06.954 --> 01:28:10.624
But you sabotage Ruben, who backed you?
You sabotage his team?

01:28:12.042 --> 01:28:13.210
I won't let you do it.

01:28:18.423 --> 01:28:21.927
-Thanks, coach. [laughs]
-Get your shit together!

01:28:22.010 --> 01:28:24.680
So stupid! God…

01:28:32.813 --> 01:28:34.273
[interviewer]
How would you sum up your race today?

01:28:34.356 --> 01:28:37.234
Ooh. Um, it was good.

01:28:37.317 --> 01:28:40.487
You know, the car feels great.
I think the team's done an amazing job.

01:28:41.196 --> 01:28:43.282
It's just a shame
about the contact with Sonny.

01:28:44.366 --> 01:28:45.659
You hate to see that happen.

01:28:55.586 --> 01:28:57.212
[pants]

01:29:08.724 --> 01:29:09.892
[sighs]

01:29:13.228 --> 01:29:14.980
-[Joshua] Hey, how are you doing?
-[host] Hi, how are you?

01:29:15.063 --> 01:29:16.523
Good. Sensational.

01:29:18.901 --> 01:29:20.944
-Where's the team?
-Right this way, gentlemen.

01:29:21.570 --> 01:29:22.821
[sighs]

01:29:31.705 --> 01:29:34.625
Brilliant, you made it. Come on. Sit down.

01:29:36.793 --> 01:29:38.545
Sonny, you know Joshua.

01:29:38.629 --> 01:29:40.464
Joshua, Sonny.

01:29:41.048 --> 01:29:42.967
So I'm sure you both
have heard the rumors. [sighs]

01:29:43.050 --> 01:29:46.011
We all lose our jobs
if you can't pull off a miracle,

01:29:46.094 --> 01:29:48.139
and that's starting with
staying on the bloody track.

01:29:48.222 --> 01:29:50.265
Well, we were doing just fine
while JP was out.

01:29:50.349 --> 01:29:51.684
I was out because I was listening to you.

01:29:51.767 --> 01:29:53.185
-Ish.
-And please don't call me JP.

01:29:53.268 --> 01:29:54.812
It's a nickname. You don't get to choose.

01:29:54.895 --> 01:29:57.231
And your name doesn't even make sense.
Is it Sonny, is it Hayesie?

01:29:57.314 --> 01:29:58.399
-We don't know, do we, Kate?
-[scoffs]

01:29:58.482 --> 01:29:59.522
-[chuckles]
-[Kate] Lads.

01:29:59.983 --> 01:30:01.318
Have I not delivered you a car?

01:30:04.488 --> 01:30:06.448
So you can do one thing for me.

01:30:06.532 --> 01:30:07.741
Cards.

01:30:08.408 --> 01:30:10.244
Come on. I know you have 'em with ya.

01:30:11.286 --> 01:30:13.205
It's my team meeting,
we're gonna do it my way.

01:30:13.288 --> 01:30:15.166
-We're playing poker.
-[Joshua scoffs] Come on.

01:30:15.249 --> 01:30:17.960
Yeah. Whoever wins gets to be
our number one driver tomorrow,

01:30:18.043 --> 01:30:20.003
and if I win, I get to choose.

01:30:22.089 --> 01:30:24.007
-Didn't he gamble for a living?
-Mm-hmm, yeah.

01:30:24.091 --> 01:30:25.467
Now he's living in a van.

01:30:25.551 --> 01:30:26.802
[chuckles]

01:30:27.511 --> 01:30:28.512
Texas Hold'em?

01:30:31.265 --> 01:30:32.850
["Just Cool" playing]

01:30:37.145 --> 01:30:39.231
[Sonny speaks indistinctly]

01:30:42.901 --> 01:30:45.195
So, Sonny here likes straight talk.

01:30:45.279 --> 01:30:46.864
-[chuckles]
-Isn't that right, Sonny?

01:30:46.947 --> 01:30:49.200
-[Sonny] Yeah, that's what I hear.
-[Kate] So, let's talk.

01:30:49.283 --> 01:30:50.367
Who wants to go first?

01:30:50.450 --> 01:30:52.160
-I'll go first.
-I'll go first.

01:30:52.244 --> 01:30:53.829
No, I'll go first.

01:30:53.912 --> 01:30:57.249
What's the difference between
Joshua Pearce and Sonny Hayes?

01:30:57.332 --> 01:30:58.333
A lot of decades.

01:30:58.417 --> 01:31:00.711
-Hard-won experience.
-Of living in a van?

01:31:00.794 --> 01:31:02.004
Total freedom.

01:31:02.087 --> 01:31:03.130
Total failure.

01:31:03.839 --> 01:31:05.508
Says the guy who still lives with his mom.

01:31:05.591 --> 01:31:07.009
Says the guy with two pair.

01:31:07.092 --> 01:31:10.012
-Says the guy with trips.
-Says the guy with a full house.

01:31:12.264 --> 01:31:14.057
-Girl.
-[Joshua scoffs]

01:31:14.141 --> 01:31:15.893
Wait, I don't even live with my mum.

01:31:15.976 --> 01:31:16.977
Okay.

01:31:17.561 --> 01:31:19.062
She just cooks for me sometimes.

01:31:19.146 --> 01:31:20.397
Mm-hmm.

01:31:22.316 --> 01:31:25.068
If you'd any constructive criticism
for each other, what would it be?

01:31:25.152 --> 01:31:27.352
-Don't be such an arsehole.
-Don't be such a dickhead.

01:31:28.947 --> 01:31:29.948
That was constructive.

01:31:30.032 --> 01:31:31.241
[scoffs]

01:31:32.868 --> 01:31:35.329
You have a deficient frontal cortex.

01:31:37.039 --> 01:31:38.916
-A what?
-You can't analyze risk.

01:31:38.999 --> 01:31:42.377
It's not all your fault.
It's not fully formed yet at your age.

01:31:42.461 --> 01:31:44.046
But come the day you learn patience,

01:31:44.129 --> 01:31:46.215
-and stop being so immature, thinking...
-Patience.

01:31:46.798 --> 01:31:48.318
-Patience is good.
-[Sonny] Patience.

01:31:49.301 --> 01:31:50.552
Joshua.

01:31:51.803 --> 01:31:54.181
He doesn't care about
what anyone else has to say but himself.

01:31:54.264 --> 01:31:57.601
He just comes in and imposes his will
on all of us with no discussion.

01:31:57.684 --> 01:32:00.312
He doesn't listen.
I'm trying, but he doesn't listen.

01:32:00.395 --> 01:32:01.438
Mmm.

01:32:02.022 --> 01:32:04.399
-Sonny?
-What?

01:32:04.483 --> 01:32:05.943
[Joshua scoffs]

01:32:06.777 --> 01:32:09.530
[sighs] Wow. [scoffs]

01:32:09.613 --> 01:32:11.532
[sighs]

01:32:11.615 --> 01:32:14.326
♪ Why they lie to the people?
Why the world is so evil? ♪

01:32:14.409 --> 01:32:15.536
[no audible dialogue]

01:32:15.619 --> 01:32:19.373
♪ Why cant just cool?
Just let me cool ♪

01:32:19.957 --> 01:32:22.709
♪ Walking explosives
Stressing all of the time ♪

01:32:22.793 --> 01:32:24.086
Who taught you how to play?

01:32:24.169 --> 01:32:26.004
My dad liked to gamble.

01:32:26.588 --> 01:32:29.007
-He make big bets too?
-Put a big one on me.

01:32:29.091 --> 01:32:30.926
How old were you when your fathers died?

01:32:35.472 --> 01:32:36.473
Sorry.

01:32:36.557 --> 01:32:37.808
-Thirteen.
-Thirteen.

01:32:40.519 --> 01:32:42.020
Huh.

01:32:43.063 --> 01:32:44.273
Why do you race?

01:32:44.356 --> 01:32:48.318
Money… [sighs]
…fame and free clothes. [chuckles]

01:32:48.402 --> 01:32:50.612
Oh, my God, with the phone.
Put the thing down, will ya?

01:32:50.696 --> 01:32:52.489
What do you care what they say?

01:32:52.573 --> 01:32:54.366
Easy for you to say. They all love you.

01:32:54.449 --> 01:32:55.701
It's just noise, man.

01:32:57.244 --> 01:32:58.787
Drive the car.

01:32:58.871 --> 01:33:00.163
You're really good at it.

01:33:03.125 --> 01:33:04.418
You might be great.

01:33:21.602 --> 01:33:24.813
♪ Hyperbolic catastrophic scatterbrain ♪

01:33:24.897 --> 01:33:28.942
♪ This is one diabolic catatonic parade ♪

01:33:29.026 --> 01:33:31.486
♪ Everyone just go away
There's nothing new to celebrate ♪

01:33:31.570 --> 01:33:32.779
[Kate exhales heavily]

01:33:32.863 --> 01:33:34.907
♪ There's nowhere left to run away ♪

01:33:34.990 --> 01:33:38.911
♪ They're closing off the open seas
They're locking off the runways ♪

01:33:38.994 --> 01:33:43.290
♪ They keep telling me the one thing
So far from everything I see ♪

01:33:43.373 --> 01:33:44.708
♪ Just go away ♪

01:33:44.791 --> 01:33:47.085
[groans] Yeah. [chuckles]

01:33:47.169 --> 01:33:50.297
Look at that, huh?
Number one driver tomorrow.

01:33:50.380 --> 01:33:51.882
-Bonding?
-[Joshua] Ooh.

01:33:51.965 --> 01:33:52.966
Well, this is nice.

01:33:53.050 --> 01:33:55.052
We gotta go, mate. Sponsor party at OMNIA.

01:33:55.135 --> 01:33:56.303
Gotta steal ya.

01:33:56.887 --> 01:33:58.805
Uh, Uncle Sonny,
you're welcome to come with...

01:33:58.889 --> 01:34:00.609
Thank you, I'm good.
I have a race tomorrow.

01:34:01.183 --> 01:34:04.144
-Cool. Kate?
-No, thank you.

01:34:04.728 --> 01:34:06.439
-[manager] Come on.
-Thanks for this, Kate.

01:34:06.522 --> 01:34:09.608
[manager] Come on, boy.
Uh… Uh, girls, you might have to…

01:34:09.691 --> 01:34:11.652
We're gonna go dancing.
Should we go dancing?

01:34:11.735 --> 01:34:13.612
-Yeah!
-[all clamoring]

01:34:17.407 --> 01:34:19.368
[romantic pop song playing on speakers]

01:34:25.707 --> 01:34:26.959
Listen,

01:34:27.626 --> 01:34:29.211
let's get this straight, okay?

01:34:29.962 --> 01:34:33.382
I don't mess around during the season,
and never with a member of my team,

01:34:33.465 --> 01:34:35.175
and what I'm attracted to is winning.

01:34:35.926 --> 01:34:37.678
And you just lost to a pair of fives.

01:34:50.524 --> 01:34:55.821
♪ So, baby, let's get messy
Let's get all the way undone ♪

01:34:55.904 --> 01:35:00.784
♪ Come over, undress me
Just like I've never been touched ♪

01:35:00.868 --> 01:35:04.705
♪ Baby, I'm obsessed with you
And there's no replica ♪

01:35:04.788 --> 01:35:07.916
♪ Baby, let's get messy
Let's get all the way undone ♪

01:35:08.000 --> 01:35:09.501
[song continues as club remix]

01:35:23.015 --> 01:35:25.017
[energetic pop song plays]

01:35:26.810 --> 01:35:30.731
♪ I wanna let my hair down
While I'm staring down your face ♪

01:35:30.814 --> 01:35:34.234
♪ Wanna go till lights out
Take you right back to my place ♪

01:35:34.318 --> 01:35:37.613
♪ You out your mind
If you don't know what this is ♪

01:35:37.696 --> 01:35:38.697
Hey.

01:35:39.907 --> 01:35:41.366
You're a driver, aren't you?

01:35:42.284 --> 01:35:43.827
-Yeah.
-Which team?

01:35:43.911 --> 01:35:45.162
Apex GP.

01:35:45.245 --> 01:35:47.789
Can you introduce me to Carlos Sainz?

01:35:49.333 --> 01:35:50.459
I'll go get him.

01:35:50.542 --> 01:35:51.543
♪ Move from the back ♪

01:35:51.627 --> 01:35:53.545
♪ Eyes on me How you like that ♪

01:35:53.629 --> 01:35:55.339
♪ Just like this
Here for the night ♪

01:35:56.298 --> 01:35:58.133
Oh, hey. Hey.

01:35:58.217 --> 01:36:01.094
Oi, why do they say this place is weird?
I like this, bruv.

01:36:01.178 --> 01:36:03.472
Glad you're having fun, man.
Be safe. I'm gonna leave, yeah?

01:36:03.555 --> 01:36:04.806
-Huh?
-I said I'm gonna cut.

01:36:04.890 --> 01:36:07.560
-Oh, wait, no, no, no. You just got here!
-I just… I'm not feeling it.

01:36:07.643 --> 01:36:10.354
What do you mean?
We just got here, bruv. Josh!

01:36:12.147 --> 01:36:13.857
♪ Just keep watching ♪

01:36:14.900 --> 01:36:17.277
[car engine whirring]

01:36:33.460 --> 01:36:36.255
-[tires screech]
-[thuds]

01:36:38.340 --> 01:36:39.550
[screaming]

01:36:39.633 --> 01:36:42.803
[gasps, panting]

01:36:44.847 --> 01:36:45.848
[sighs]

01:37:07.953 --> 01:37:09.162
Hey.

01:37:11.290 --> 01:37:13.208
-[chuckles]
-[groans]

01:37:13.709 --> 01:37:15.210
I shouldn't drink tequila.

01:37:19.756 --> 01:37:21.175
Last night was Ruben's idea?

01:37:21.258 --> 01:37:22.926
[stammers] Yeah, the first part.

01:37:23.510 --> 01:37:26.597
-Well… [stammers, chuckles]
-Not the second! [chuckles]

01:37:37.024 --> 01:37:38.066
Come on.

01:37:39.234 --> 01:37:41.236
Why are you here, Sonny, huh?

01:37:44.489 --> 01:37:46.408
Not much of a story.

01:37:52.122 --> 01:37:53.207
Okay.

01:37:55.042 --> 01:37:56.960
I'm here to prove everyone wrong.

01:37:58.879 --> 01:38:01.548
My ex, my old boss,

01:38:03.258 --> 01:38:05.260
my first-year uni physics professor...

01:38:05.344 --> 01:38:06.887
-That bastard.
-Yeah.

01:38:06.970 --> 01:38:07.971
[chuckles]

01:38:09.181 --> 01:38:11.475
And until we win, I haven't.

01:38:12.684 --> 01:38:16.939
So, unfortunately, I now rely on you.

01:38:17.022 --> 01:38:18.065
Mmm.

01:38:23.820 --> 01:38:25.447
I was gonna be world champion.

01:38:27.074 --> 01:38:28.575
The best there ever was.

01:38:30.035 --> 01:38:32.454
I'm just a kid and I'm on the track
with my idols,

01:38:32.538 --> 01:38:34.748
Senna, Mansell, Prost.

01:38:34.831 --> 01:38:36.416
And I am quick.

01:38:37.835 --> 01:38:39.294
I'm fearless.

01:38:41.129 --> 01:38:42.422
I was next.

01:38:45.425 --> 01:38:46.426
And then…

01:38:47.928 --> 01:38:48.929
[clicks fingers]

01:38:49.847 --> 01:38:51.390
…it was all taken away.

01:38:53.725 --> 01:38:55.102
The crash, huh?

01:38:56.687 --> 01:39:00.482
So I lost my seat, my money,
my sanity, my…

01:39:01.441 --> 01:39:02.734
Myself, really.

01:39:03.694 --> 01:39:08.782
Just became this angry,
resentful shithead.

01:39:08.866 --> 01:39:12.536
[chuckles]
Not someone I'm particularly proud of.

01:39:16.915 --> 01:39:19.209
Till one day,
I realized what I had really lost,

01:39:19.293 --> 01:39:24.339
and it wasn't the titles,
or the trophies, or the records.

01:39:24.423 --> 01:39:27.759
It was my love for racing.

01:39:30.387 --> 01:39:32.097
So I started driving.

01:39:33.098 --> 01:39:36.643
Didn't matter the car, the circuit,
didn't need anyone to watch.

01:39:36.727 --> 01:39:40.606
Just as long as I was behind the wheel,
I was good.

01:39:43.775 --> 01:39:45.235
Sometimes…

01:39:51.700 --> 01:39:53.202
[sighs]

01:39:54.536 --> 01:39:57.414
What? Come on.

01:40:00.792 --> 01:40:06.256
It's rare, but sometimes,
there's this moment in the car

01:40:06.340 --> 01:40:08.967
where everything goes quiet,

01:40:09.843 --> 01:40:11.470
my heartbeat slows,

01:40:12.888 --> 01:40:14.348
it's peaceful,

01:40:15.015 --> 01:40:18.060
and I can see everything, and no one…

01:40:18.602 --> 01:40:20.229
No one can touch me.

01:40:23.273 --> 01:40:26.235
And I am chasing that moment
every time I get in the car.

01:40:29.321 --> 01:40:33.951
I don't know when I'll find it again,
but, man, I want to.

01:40:34.743 --> 01:40:36.203
[chuckles] I want to.

01:40:37.704 --> 01:40:40.916
'Cause in that moment, I'm flying.

01:40:52.427 --> 01:40:55.681
[doorbell rings]

01:41:03.021 --> 01:41:04.022
Kate.

01:41:04.565 --> 01:41:06.400
-Ruben.
-Where is he?

01:41:06.483 --> 01:41:07.609
Where's who?

01:41:08.443 --> 01:41:09.945
What are you talking about?

01:41:11.697 --> 01:41:13.115
Ruben, seriously?

01:41:14.074 --> 01:41:16.577
[scoffs] One, how dare you?

01:41:16.660 --> 01:41:19.329
Two, I respect professional boundaries.

01:41:20.122 --> 01:41:21.123
And three…

01:41:23.500 --> 01:41:25.086
Three, yeah, he's on… he's on the balcony.

01:41:25.169 --> 01:41:26.170
[grunts]

01:41:28.338 --> 01:41:30.049
-Well, you're up early.
-[Ruben] Get dressed.

01:41:30.132 --> 01:41:32.384
-Yeah, what's going on?
-They're coming for our car.

01:41:35.971 --> 01:41:39.016
[race director] It's my duty to inform you
that we've received an anonymous tip

01:41:39.099 --> 01:41:41.268
that your upgraded floor is in violation.

01:41:41.351 --> 01:41:42.561
[Ruben] From who?

01:41:42.644 --> 01:41:44.313
-I can't say.
-Ah. [chuckles]

01:41:44.396 --> 01:41:47.149
Sir, we submitted the drawings long ago.

01:41:47.232 --> 01:41:48.233
-Right?
-Mm-hmm.

01:41:48.317 --> 01:41:49.484
And you approved them all.

01:41:49.568 --> 01:41:54.114
It's whether the parts you're racing with
were developed outside of your facility.

01:41:54.198 --> 01:41:55.532
What? That's insane.

01:41:55.616 --> 01:41:58.285
Based on the paperwork we've received,
there are concerns.

01:41:58.368 --> 01:42:00.829
Hang on, where'd you get these?
These are internal documents.

01:42:00.913 --> 01:42:03.415
[Ruben] This team
doesn't break any rules, sir. No, no.

01:42:03.498 --> 01:42:06.460
-I'll take that with a pinch of salt.
-Someone can fabricate documents.

01:42:06.543 --> 01:42:07.836
Your car's under review.

01:42:07.920 --> 01:42:09.004
-You know the procedure.
-What?

01:42:09.087 --> 01:42:13.467
You cannot race unless you substitute
the previously approved components.

01:42:13.550 --> 01:42:15.677
-No!
-Do you mean our old design?

01:42:15.761 --> 01:42:16.887
A shit box!

01:42:16.970 --> 01:42:18.180
[in Spanish] No lo puedo creer.

01:42:18.263 --> 01:42:20.266
[in English] Where were you
the last two years? Why now?

01:42:20.349 --> 01:42:22.726
Because we might actually win a race?
Is that it?

01:42:22.809 --> 01:42:25.771
This is not car racing, sir,
this is like corporate espionage!

01:42:25.854 --> 01:42:27.898
I'm sorry. I'm sorry. Come… Come here.

01:42:27.981 --> 01:42:29.816
I'm talking to you! Sir!

01:42:29.900 --> 01:42:31.735
Without the upgrade, we're screwed.

01:42:58.345 --> 01:43:01.765
[Kaspar] Sonny, let it go.
Focus on a clean start.

01:43:01.849 --> 01:43:03.642
We'll never win clean.

01:43:04.226 --> 01:43:05.727
Can we just not break any rules?

01:43:05.811 --> 01:43:08.397
Yeah, the rules are always
against us though, aren't they?

01:43:11.900 --> 01:43:14.194
Get them safe through lap one. [sighs]

01:43:14.278 --> 01:43:17.197
[Hugh] Sonny, we just need
to keep it in one piece. Okay?

01:43:17.281 --> 01:43:20.033
[Sonny breathing shakily]

01:43:20.117 --> 01:43:22.578
[tense music playing]

01:43:22.661 --> 01:43:23.912
Sonny?

01:43:42.598 --> 01:43:43.891
[tires squeal]

01:43:48.395 --> 01:43:51.106
-Oi, what the hell?
-I don't know!

01:43:51.190 --> 01:43:52.233
[Joshua] What's wrong with Sonny?

01:43:52.316 --> 01:43:54.610
Joshua, yep. Keep focused.
You're still good.

01:43:54.693 --> 01:43:55.736
What's he doing?

01:44:02.242 --> 01:44:03.619
He's driving angry.

01:44:04.286 --> 01:44:05.621
Not good. It's not good.

01:44:12.794 --> 01:44:14.630
Sonny, we need to make these tires last.

01:44:14.713 --> 01:44:16.131
Take it easy.

01:44:23.013 --> 01:44:25.265
No, he's put the car in qualifying mode.

01:44:25.349 --> 01:44:27.560
He's gonna run the battery down.
Tell him to put it back.

01:44:27.643 --> 01:44:29.883
[Hugh] Sonny, you're in qualifying mode.
What's going on?

01:44:30.812 --> 01:44:31.813
Sonny, what's happening?

01:44:41.907 --> 01:44:46.328
[Croft] …blasting along
Las Vegas Boulevard, 210 miles an hour.

01:44:46.411 --> 01:44:48.872
Hard on the brakes now,
and into the chicane.

01:44:48.956 --> 01:44:53.460
Sergio Perez, ahead of Sonny Hayes,
but that's a mega exit from Hayes.

01:44:53.544 --> 01:44:56.672
He's gotta gain on Sergio Perez,
and he's closing.

01:44:56.755 --> 01:44:59.466
Meter by meter. Inch by inch.

01:44:59.550 --> 01:45:04.263
Is this the place to take a gamble?
Hayes attacks round the outside.

01:45:09.935 --> 01:45:11.937
[crowd gasping, clamoring]

01:45:12.437 --> 01:45:13.480
No! No!

01:45:23.657 --> 01:45:26.118
[somber orchestral music playing]

01:45:38.881 --> 01:45:41.341
Why do we do this?

01:45:41.967 --> 01:45:44.761
What's wrong with tennis, huh?

01:45:44.845 --> 01:45:46.430
-Or golf.
-[chuckles]

01:45:46.513 --> 01:45:48.182
[chuckles] Right?

01:45:49.141 --> 01:45:50.684
[exhales heavily]

01:45:51.518 --> 01:45:52.519
Christ.

01:45:54.479 --> 01:45:55.981
We are totally insane.

01:45:58.025 --> 01:45:59.026
[sighs]

01:46:00.986 --> 01:46:03.197
"C5 neck fracture."

01:46:04.531 --> 01:46:05.991
Spinal contusion.

01:46:06.533 --> 01:46:08.535
Compressed thoracic vertebrae.

01:46:09.119 --> 01:46:13.373
Further blunt force impact trauma
likely to result in vision loss,

01:46:13.457 --> 01:46:15.250
"paralysis, death."

01:46:18.504 --> 01:46:20.297
Really lead with the good news,
don't they?

01:46:20.964 --> 01:46:22.758
This is a report from 30 years ago.

01:46:24.468 --> 01:46:25.844
Why didn't you tell me?

01:46:28.680 --> 01:46:31.141
You never should have raced again, Sonny.

01:46:32.309 --> 01:46:34.853
How… How do you think I'd feel
if you die on the track?

01:46:36.980 --> 01:46:38.106
Revenge for Monaco.

01:46:38.190 --> 01:46:39.733
[stammers] It's not a joke!

01:46:42.945 --> 01:46:44.905
It's me who's liable, Sonny.

01:46:45.697 --> 01:46:48.575
And don't think there's some
bullshit loophole to get you out of this.

01:46:48.659 --> 01:46:50.118
-No.
-Ruben, we're drivers.

01:46:50.202 --> 01:46:52.913
We are not drivers, not anymore.
I'm sorry. We're not.

01:46:54.915 --> 01:46:56.208
We're losers.

01:46:57.918 --> 01:46:59.294
We're a pair of dumb,

01:46:59.920 --> 01:47:01.296
sentimental,

01:47:02.756 --> 01:47:03.966
broke losers.

01:47:07.845 --> 01:47:08.929
[sighs]

01:47:09.721 --> 01:47:11.139
Okay. You're off the team.

01:47:16.061 --> 01:47:19.815
[sighs] Your van is in the garage
with all your stuff in it, and…

01:47:24.361 --> 01:47:25.487
[chuckles]

01:47:26.363 --> 01:47:28.866
I never should have pulled you
into this, Sonny.

01:47:30.158 --> 01:47:31.368
I'm sorry.

01:47:33.954 --> 01:47:35.122
Ruben, wait!

01:47:36.623 --> 01:47:37.791
[sighs]

01:47:40.836 --> 01:47:41.962
I need this.

01:47:43.172 --> 01:47:44.173
[sighs]

01:47:44.923 --> 01:47:49.303
No one drives forever, Sonny.
Not even you.

01:48:03.859 --> 01:48:09.781
Pippa, load up Monza.
Just like it happened. In the rain.

01:48:10.991 --> 01:48:13.327
[crew member] Joshua,
Sonny says wait for the straight,

01:48:13.410 --> 01:48:15.370
the straight into turn one.

01:48:23.212 --> 01:48:24.463
Run it again, please.

01:48:28.967 --> 01:48:31.929
[crew member] …wait for the straight,
the straight into turn one.

01:48:34.556 --> 01:48:36.391
Run it again, please.

01:48:46.109 --> 01:48:48.111
[crew member] The straight into turn one.

01:48:54.576 --> 01:48:58.539
[exclaims] Whoo! [chuckles]

01:49:15.556 --> 01:49:16.849
[Peter] Sonny.

01:49:18.100 --> 01:49:19.142
Sonny.

01:49:20.394 --> 01:49:22.312
Hey. You're not in Abu Dhabi?

01:49:22.396 --> 01:49:24.857
I fly out tonight. I, uh…

01:49:24.940 --> 01:49:26.233
Yeah, I wanted to catch you.

01:49:27.776 --> 01:49:29.069
So, listen. [sighs]

01:49:29.152 --> 01:49:33.031
We both know that the board's
wanted to unload Apex from the start,

01:49:33.699 --> 01:49:36.702
but, yeah, then you rode into town,

01:49:36.785 --> 01:49:39.371
raised our whole profile,
and now I've, uh…

01:49:39.454 --> 01:49:41.915
Yeah, I've got… I've got buyers lining up.

01:49:43.834 --> 01:49:45.669
-Uh-huh.
-Gotta be honest with you, man,

01:49:45.752 --> 01:49:48.672
I thought you were gonna be the…
the final nail in the coffin.

01:49:49.256 --> 01:49:50.841
But now I see the play.

01:49:50.924 --> 01:49:54.553
And I want you as part of the package.

01:49:57.890 --> 01:49:59.433
What sort of package?

01:50:00.100 --> 01:50:02.853
I've set up a sale where I run the team,

01:50:02.936 --> 01:50:04.521
and keep you on for strategy,

01:50:05.314 --> 01:50:06.648
maybe even team principal.

01:50:07.983 --> 01:50:11.820
With the money from that deal,
I can make you a very rich man.

01:50:12.863 --> 01:50:14.239
Here's the thing.

01:50:14.323 --> 01:50:16.450
With the… the changing regulations,

01:50:16.533 --> 01:50:19.870
new Mercedes power unit,
Kate's aero, two new drivers…

01:50:21.246 --> 01:50:23.332
We've got a real shot
at the championship next year.

01:50:24.625 --> 01:50:25.834
What about Ruben?

01:50:25.918 --> 01:50:26.919
Don't worry.

01:50:27.669 --> 01:50:28.962
You know.

01:50:29.046 --> 01:50:30.172
We won't embarrass him.

01:50:30.839 --> 01:50:33.717
We'll keep him on with a… with a title,
or brand ambassador…

01:50:34.343 --> 01:50:35.427
You know, something.

01:50:39.515 --> 01:50:40.766
And I get final say?

01:50:40.849 --> 01:50:42.059
Don't change a thing.

01:50:42.142 --> 01:50:43.310
Do what you do, man.

01:50:44.353 --> 01:50:45.812
And that's the irony here.

01:50:45.896 --> 01:50:48.732
You know, the board
originally approved your hire

01:50:48.815 --> 01:50:50.359
because we thought you'd help us lose.

01:50:51.235 --> 01:50:52.569
-Sorry to make you sweat.
-Hey.

01:50:54.279 --> 01:50:55.405
That's my number.

01:50:55.489 --> 01:50:56.740
Talk to your people.

01:50:57.282 --> 01:51:03.205
But, uh… [chuckles] …right after the race,
I, uh… I wanna lock down the deal, okay?

01:51:03.705 --> 01:51:05.666
-So, by Sunday?
-Perfect.

01:51:06.834 --> 01:51:09.711
Listen, this thing can be your legacy,
you know?

01:51:11.839 --> 01:51:13.048
An F1 champion.

01:51:14.299 --> 01:51:15.717
What you always wanted, right?

01:51:19.263 --> 01:51:22.766
It was you who forged those documents,
wasn't it?

01:51:22.850 --> 01:51:23.851
Huh.

01:51:26.520 --> 01:51:28.355
[chuckles]

01:51:29.189 --> 01:51:32.025
-You're a killer, man, aren't you?
-Hey. I'm a winner.

01:51:33.652 --> 01:51:36.154
-Aren't you, huh?
-[sighs]

01:51:38.282 --> 01:51:39.283
Okay.

01:51:42.286 --> 01:51:44.621
Oh, hey. How's the back?

01:51:45.622 --> 01:51:46.748
Better.

01:51:46.832 --> 01:51:49.418
I've got an amazing guy.
I'll, uh… I'll hook you up.

01:51:50.711 --> 01:51:51.712
Hail Mary.

01:52:19.323 --> 01:52:20.449
You good?

01:52:25.162 --> 01:52:29.041
[sighs] Listen, Mum,
I've gotta tell you something.

01:52:32.920 --> 01:52:37.966
In Monza, right before the crash,
it was my decision to make the move.

01:52:39.384 --> 01:52:41.136
Sonny actually told me to wait.

01:52:43.138 --> 01:52:46.266
[breathes deeply]

01:52:48.852 --> 01:52:49.937
[knocks on door]

01:52:50.020 --> 01:52:51.146
Family.

01:52:51.230 --> 01:52:53.649
I've been working the phones with IndyCar,

01:52:53.732 --> 01:52:55.526
and I think I can get you
a test drive, bruv.

01:52:55.609 --> 01:52:56.818
-Hello, Auntie. [kisses]
-Hi.

01:52:58.070 --> 01:53:00.531
They're trying to pull in
a new demographic, obviously.

01:53:00.614 --> 01:53:03.325
And the ladies love that smile.

01:53:03.909 --> 01:53:06.620
And we can throw in some incentives,
like flights and cars.

01:53:06.703 --> 01:53:08.747
Listen, Cash, you can go.
I don't need you today.

01:53:09.831 --> 01:53:11.333
Nah, mate. You got media next.

01:53:11.416 --> 01:53:14.002
[chuckles] I don't care. They can fine me.

01:53:14.795 --> 01:53:15.796
Besides,

01:53:17.297 --> 01:53:18.924
that's not why I'm doing it, right?

01:53:19.842 --> 01:53:22.002
Josh, starting tomorrow,
we're not "doing it" anywhere.

01:53:23.637 --> 01:53:25.097
It's all just noise.

01:53:26.014 --> 01:53:28.183
Media, engagement, followers.

01:53:28.892 --> 01:53:32.062
Listen, I've gotta focus on the race.

01:53:33.897 --> 01:53:35.566
[Cash] Auntie, please.

01:53:37.192 --> 01:53:38.527
Well, you heard the man.

01:53:47.578 --> 01:53:50.122
-Deal.
-Deal. [chuckles]

01:53:53.083 --> 01:53:55.127
-Yo.
-Hey.

01:53:55.210 --> 01:53:56.712
-Hi.
-Hey.

01:53:59.673 --> 01:54:01.717
Guys, what's happening?

01:54:01.800 --> 01:54:04.970
Parc fermé.
Waiting for FIA to cut the seals.

01:54:05.053 --> 01:54:07.097
Oh, good. [sighs]

01:54:07.681 --> 01:54:10.142
-We got time then.
-For what?

01:54:11.101 --> 01:54:12.311
For…

01:54:13.812 --> 01:54:15.397
[chuckles]

01:54:15.480 --> 01:54:17.649
No, no, no.

01:54:22.237 --> 01:54:25.532
Welcome to the Paddock Club,
for our most valued guests.

01:54:25.616 --> 01:54:29.536
Please, uh, grab a drink,
make yourselves at home,

01:54:29.620 --> 01:54:33.916
and, uh, enjoy the very best view
there is of, uh… of Formula 1.

01:54:35.959 --> 01:54:37.461
Okay? Okay.

01:54:41.173 --> 01:54:42.341
[clears throat]

01:54:55.229 --> 01:54:57.397
Hey, guys, don't stop! Keep going!

01:55:00.317 --> 01:55:03.487
[chuckles]

01:55:07.449 --> 01:55:10.285
[sighing]

01:55:11.703 --> 01:55:12.788
[groans]

01:55:27.719 --> 01:55:30.097
[stirring orchestral music playing]

01:55:33.100 --> 01:55:36.019
No way. [chuckles]

01:55:39.857 --> 01:55:41.024
[sighs]

01:55:43.485 --> 01:55:46.405
Jesús, it's like a morgue around here.

01:55:48.740 --> 01:55:50.242
[stammers] How'd you get here?

01:55:50.325 --> 01:55:51.702
Premium economy.

01:55:52.536 --> 01:55:54.121
[Ruben scoffs]

01:55:55.956 --> 01:55:57.833
What? What is this?

01:55:57.916 --> 01:55:59.501
Well, that's my bullshit loophole.

01:55:59.585 --> 01:56:01.712
Oh, no, forget it.
I'm not even going to read that.

01:56:01.795 --> 01:56:04.339
That is a real legal document
from a real Tijuana lawyer…

01:56:04.423 --> 01:56:06.175
-[chuckles]
-…waiving all liability to you

01:56:06.258 --> 01:56:08.802
and your company vis-à-vis this race,
myself, and me.

01:56:09.887 --> 01:56:11.138
-And…
-[inhales sharply]

01:56:13.724 --> 01:56:17.144
…since you owe me my last paycheck,
technically I'm still on this team.

01:56:22.399 --> 01:56:23.901
Kate, where's the shitbox?

01:56:24.568 --> 01:56:26.987
The FIA confirmed that
the documents were forged,

01:56:27.070 --> 01:56:29.114
and they were sent by someone from Apex.

01:56:29.948 --> 01:56:31.033
Huh.

01:56:31.658 --> 01:56:34.620
Okay, I don't care about your loophole.
I don't.

01:56:34.703 --> 01:56:36.747
That is my car. You are not racing it.

01:56:36.830 --> 01:56:37.956
-Ruben.
-No, Sonny.

01:56:38.040 --> 01:56:39.333
Listen,

01:56:40.584 --> 01:56:42.377
I can't let you do that.

01:56:42.461 --> 01:56:43.462
I can't.

01:56:43.545 --> 01:56:44.671
Okay?

01:56:44.755 --> 01:56:45.756
[stammers]

01:56:46.423 --> 01:56:50.052
If the last thing I do is drive that car,
I will take that life, man.

01:56:53.931 --> 01:56:55.349
A thousand times.

01:56:57.309 --> 01:56:59.019
[sighs]

01:57:00.103 --> 01:57:01.355
We can't win.

01:57:03.190 --> 01:57:04.608
We can't if we don't try.

01:57:11.031 --> 01:57:12.032
[sighs]

01:57:15.619 --> 01:57:16.828
[sighs]

01:57:24.336 --> 01:57:26.129
[laughing]

01:57:27.798 --> 01:57:29.508
[laughs]

01:57:40.435 --> 01:57:42.729
[groaning]

01:57:43.939 --> 01:57:44.940
[knocks on door]

01:57:50.904 --> 01:57:52.406
How come you never look at the card?

01:57:52.489 --> 01:57:53.657
[Sonny] What card?

01:57:53.740 --> 01:57:54.741
[chuckles]

01:57:55.951 --> 01:57:58.412
[crowd cheering]

01:58:34.865 --> 01:58:37.284
Welcome to the very final spots
on the grid.

01:58:37.367 --> 01:58:41.747
And as ever, we'll go from last to first.
And breaking news here in P22,

01:58:41.830 --> 01:58:43.415
because we're hearing
the Apex GP team have made…

01:58:43.498 --> 01:58:45.209
-Hey, Peter.
-Yeah?

01:58:45.792 --> 01:58:47.044
That's your guy. Isn't it?

01:58:47.127 --> 01:58:51.131
…being replaced by Sonny Hayes, who
didn't even make the trip to Abu Dhabi…

01:58:51.215 --> 01:58:53.759
Uh, will you excuse me for one second?
I'm really sorry.

01:58:53.842 --> 01:58:56.637
Now, the rules require that
he has to start at the back of the pack.

01:58:57.304 --> 01:58:59.598
Excuse me. What the hell?

01:59:00.349 --> 01:59:01.558
What?

01:59:05.729 --> 01:59:06.813
You still got my phone?

01:59:10.651 --> 01:59:11.652
[phone buzzes]

01:59:25.791 --> 01:59:27.334
-Good luck today.
-You too, James.

01:59:27.417 --> 01:59:28.544
Excuse me. Hey, Sonny. Sonny!

01:59:28.627 --> 01:59:30.171
Hey, look,
I know we've had our differences,

01:59:30.254 --> 01:59:32.464
-but look, this is your last F1 race.
-Chaz! This guy.

01:59:32.548 --> 01:59:33.841
Any thought…

01:59:36.009 --> 01:59:37.010
What's that?

01:59:38.303 --> 01:59:40.097
[crowd cheering]

01:59:41.139 --> 01:59:42.432
Bloody hell.

01:59:44.351 --> 01:59:45.602
Bloody hell!

01:59:46.103 --> 01:59:47.646
[laughs]

01:59:47.729 --> 01:59:50.148
[UAE national anthem playing]

02:00:06.290 --> 02:00:07.291
Elbows out?

02:00:07.958 --> 02:00:08.959
Elbows out.

02:00:10.752 --> 02:00:16.300
[Croft] All set for our season finale
here in Abu Dhabi where it's lights out.

02:00:16.383 --> 02:00:19.928
And away we go.
Good start there for Joshua Pearce.

02:00:20.012 --> 02:00:22.181
Drivers jockeying for position

02:00:22.264 --> 02:00:26.894
as we head full-throttle
down the main straight and into turn one.

02:00:26.977 --> 02:00:31.815
Tricky first corner, and going wide,
the Aston Martin and the AlphaTauri

02:00:31.899 --> 02:00:34.067
-[laughs]
-as Pearce picks up two places.

02:00:34.151 --> 02:00:36.528
[Brundle] Yes, Pearce showing
some real maturity there.

02:00:36.612 --> 02:00:40.699
He saw a bad situation before it happened
and he's off to a great start.

02:00:59.259 --> 02:01:00.636
Don't even think about it.

02:01:16.610 --> 02:01:19.530
[Croft] Here comes the Alpine
down the inside. Contact!

02:01:20.781 --> 02:01:23.909
And three days out of hospital,
Hayes will feel that.

02:01:33.752 --> 02:01:35.796
Gained places, guys. We're alive.

02:01:35.879 --> 02:01:37.465
[Brundle]
I hope he hasn't damaged the car,

02:01:37.548 --> 02:01:40.425
but despite everything,
it's still a great first lap.

02:01:40.509 --> 02:01:42.511
[Croft] It is! Hayes in P16.

02:01:42.594 --> 02:01:45.138
Pearce, his teammate, up to P9.

02:01:47.099 --> 02:01:50.435
Red Bull, Mercedes and Ferrari
holding on to the lead.

02:01:50.519 --> 02:01:52.229
Apex in the midfield.

02:01:52.312 --> 02:01:55.232
Let's see if they can do anything
to shake up this race.

02:01:55.315 --> 02:01:56.400
Gap to leader?

02:01:56.483 --> 02:01:57.526
[Hugh] Fifteen seconds.

02:01:58.735 --> 02:02:01.280
Keep JP plus 20 seconds. Plus 20.

02:02:01.864 --> 02:02:03.699
-Length of a pit stop.
-You know why.

02:02:05.200 --> 02:02:07.077
[Croft] It's a busy race for Sonny Hayes,

02:02:07.160 --> 02:02:10.247
and now here comes Kevin Magnussen
looking to make a move.

02:02:10.330 --> 02:02:12.040
And this could spell trouble.

02:02:12.124 --> 02:02:13.751
[Brundle]
There's history between these two.

02:02:13.834 --> 02:02:17.171
Often, the irresistible force
meets the immovable object.

02:02:17.254 --> 02:02:19.173
And Magnussen, looking down the inside,

02:02:19.256 --> 02:02:22.801
-locks up and hits Hayes.
-Box, box. Box, box, box.

02:02:22.885 --> 02:02:24.261
Copy, coming in for hards.

02:02:25.846 --> 02:02:27.097
Damn.

02:02:28.599 --> 02:02:31.810
Slow is smooth. Smooth is fast.
Here we go, boys.

02:02:39.109 --> 02:02:40.319
[Croft] Hayes exit the pits.

02:02:40.402 --> 02:02:43.197
He had to come in
because of that damage to his tire.

02:02:43.280 --> 02:02:47.326
But what of Joshua Pearce?
Where do Apex GP go with him?

02:02:49.036 --> 02:02:50.954
[Joshua] Guys, am I boxing?
What's the plan?

02:02:51.038 --> 02:02:53.457
Plan C, Plan C. Stay out. Stay out.

02:02:53.540 --> 02:02:56.210
-[laughs] Chaos.
-Copy that.

02:02:56.293 --> 02:02:59.796
Joshua slows down the leaders for Sonny.
Sonny does the same for him.

02:03:01.215 --> 02:03:02.758
[Brundle] Pearce stays out.

02:03:02.841 --> 02:03:05.844
It's a strategy that Apex have used
before this season.

02:03:05.928 --> 02:03:09.932
It helps them with track position for now,
but they gotta keep these tires alive.

02:03:13.477 --> 02:03:15.145
It's the only way we keep this close.

02:03:15.729 --> 02:03:16.772
And then we need luck.

02:03:16.855 --> 02:03:18.148
I'm way ahead of ya.

02:03:19.733 --> 02:03:20.733
[Rico chuckles]

02:03:21.443 --> 02:03:25.030
[Croft] Lap 25, and every driver
so far has pitted, bar one.

02:03:25.113 --> 02:03:26.865
And he leads the race.

02:03:26.949 --> 02:03:29.868
Joshua Pearce controlling the pace
out in front.

02:03:29.952 --> 02:03:31.662
[Brundle] And that gives
his teammate, Hayes,

02:03:31.745 --> 02:03:34.122
a chance to maintain
his position in the midfield

02:03:34.206 --> 02:03:37.417
despite the contact,
puncture and pit stop.

02:03:37.501 --> 02:03:39.127
They're working really well together.

02:03:40.921 --> 02:03:42.089
How's JP doing up there?

02:03:42.172 --> 02:03:45.384
He's keeping the leaders at bay.
DRS active next straight, Sonny.

02:03:45.467 --> 02:03:46.760
Got it.

02:03:47.594 --> 02:03:51.139
[Croft] Onto the back straight.
He's enjoying this new upgrade,

02:03:51.223 --> 02:03:54.393
and he's got DRS,
and he's got Pierre Gasly.

02:03:54.476 --> 02:03:56.562
Sonny Hayes up into P15.

02:03:57.688 --> 02:04:00.065
[Hugh] Sonny, you have got the pace.
Keep pushing.

02:04:00.649 --> 02:04:02.610
[Brundle] Pearce has been doing
a great job out front

02:04:02.693 --> 02:04:06.280
despite the used tires,
but that moment is nearly over now.

02:04:06.363 --> 02:04:09.199
Verstappen up the inside and he's through.

02:04:09.283 --> 02:04:11.785
[Croft] Fabulous first stint
from Joshua Pearce.

02:04:11.869 --> 02:04:14.246
Max has passed,
and his troubles don't end there.

02:04:15.581 --> 02:04:17.457
Here comes Charles Leclerc.

02:04:17.541 --> 02:04:21.795
It's another overtake.
Pearce lost the lead and drops now to P3.

02:04:21.879 --> 02:04:24.339
Sorry, guys. My rear tires are shot.

02:04:24.423 --> 02:04:26.216
Copy that. Box, JP. Box, box.

02:04:27.801 --> 02:04:29.970
[Brundle] Pearce stretching those tires
to the limit.

02:04:30.053 --> 02:04:32.973
Short-term pain for long-term gain.

02:04:41.190 --> 02:04:44.151
And he exits the pit.
He'll have fresher tires.

02:04:44.234 --> 02:04:47.362
He can now attack
in the second half of the race.

02:04:47.946 --> 02:04:49.781
Sonny, the three leaders
are still on hards.

02:04:49.865 --> 02:04:51.784
They're gonna have to stop again.
This is their pit window.

02:04:51.867 --> 02:04:54.870
One of the leaders is gonna undercut.
I need to be there when they do.

02:04:56.288 --> 02:04:58.582
P3 Ferrari. Pippa, can he beat it to one?

02:05:01.126 --> 02:05:02.211
[Pippa] Depends on their stop.

02:05:02.294 --> 02:05:04.046
[Croft] Will the undercut
work for Ferrari?

02:05:04.129 --> 02:05:06.423
Five point eight.
He needs to pick up half a second.

02:05:08.634 --> 02:05:11.011
Sonny, you need half a second.
Go, go, go, go, go.

02:05:11.094 --> 02:05:12.513
[Croft] And Sonny Hayes is on the charge.

02:05:12.596 --> 02:05:15.015
Under the track goes the Ferrari.

02:05:15.098 --> 02:05:17.017
Through the first corner goes Sonny Hayes.

02:05:17.100 --> 02:05:19.770
It's neck and neck. It's really tight.

02:05:19.853 --> 02:05:23.357
Sonny Hayes is just ahead of Carlos Sainz.

02:05:23.440 --> 02:05:25.692
-Yes! Come on!
-[Croft] It's worked so far for Apex GP.

02:05:25.776 --> 02:05:27.569
But their trouble's not over.

02:05:27.653 --> 02:05:31.865
Down the inside, there's a chance
for Carlos Sainz, and he takes it.

02:05:31.949 --> 02:05:33.158
But he locks up.

02:05:33.242 --> 02:05:35.953
The Ferrari goes wide
and Sonny Hayes says,

02:05:36.036 --> 02:05:38.705
"Thank you very much indeed."

02:05:40.332 --> 02:05:42.417
How are they staying so close to the lead?

02:05:42.501 --> 02:05:45.671
Uh, they're, um… They're working together.

02:05:46.338 --> 02:05:49.842
[Brundle] Two Apex cars in the top 10,
but still a long way to go.

02:05:51.510 --> 02:05:55.347
[Croft] Twenty laps remaining, and Apex
has worked their way up the order.

02:05:55.430 --> 02:05:57.724
We're now at the final pit stop window.

02:05:57.808 --> 02:06:00.394
This is our chance for P1.
Make sure JP beats them out.

02:06:00.477 --> 02:06:05.148
[Croft] Hamilton and Leclerc
come into the pits, but Pearce stays out.

02:06:06.191 --> 02:06:08.944
-[Joshua] Talk to me. Can I catch 'em?
-Yep. They're just coming out.

02:06:09.027 --> 02:06:10.821
Push now. Push now. Push, push.

02:06:10.904 --> 02:06:12.197
Copy. Pushing.

02:06:12.781 --> 02:06:14.366
[Croft] Oh, this is gonna be close.

02:06:14.449 --> 02:06:17.411
Joshua Pearce inching ahead.
Staying ahead.

02:06:17.494 --> 02:06:20.289
For the second time in this race,
he leads.

02:06:20.372 --> 02:06:21.373
[laughs] Let's go!

02:06:21.456 --> 02:06:22.958
-[grunts]
-[grunts] Yes.

02:06:23.041 --> 02:06:26.044
You are P1, Joshua. [laughs]

02:06:26.128 --> 02:06:28.505
[Brundle] But Pearce will have
a hard time holding them off

02:06:28.589 --> 02:06:31.508
with Hamilton and Leclerc on fresh tires.

02:06:40.726 --> 02:06:43.103
[Croft] Four laps to go.
Sonny Hayes is in P4.

02:06:43.187 --> 02:06:45.105
He's five seconds behind his teammate,

02:06:45.189 --> 02:06:46.899
but both are on old tires.

02:06:46.982 --> 02:06:49.610
There's little chance
they'll gain any places now.

02:06:51.862 --> 02:06:55.824
And here's Hamilton
attacking Pearce into turn five.

02:06:55.908 --> 02:06:57.159
And he's through.

02:06:57.242 --> 02:07:01.079
Nobody has to stop again
and our tires are nine laps older.

02:07:02.831 --> 02:07:05.375
[Brundle] And Leclerc attacks and passes.

02:07:05.459 --> 02:07:09.880
Pearce's tires are absolutely finished.
There was nothing he could do about that.

02:07:10.631 --> 02:07:13.717
I'm sorry, guys. I've got nothing left.

02:07:13.800 --> 02:07:17.262
[Croft] It's been the Apex GP story
all year long.

02:07:17.346 --> 02:07:18.347
Plenty of risks.

02:07:18.430 --> 02:07:20.057
A great underdog story,

02:07:20.140 --> 02:07:22.142
but we know, Martin,
only talent crowns a champion.

02:07:22.226 --> 02:07:23.727
[Sonny] Losing grip. Tires are gone.

02:07:23.810 --> 02:07:26.438
[Brundle] Yeah. Sadly, the deck's
been stacked against them

02:07:26.522 --> 02:07:28.398
and now they're out of cards to play.

02:07:28.482 --> 02:07:29.566
It ain't over, right?

02:07:29.650 --> 02:07:32.945
No, but nothing can change.
It's the worst feeling in the world.

02:07:37.574 --> 02:07:39.368
George Russell on the attack.

02:07:39.451 --> 02:07:42.287
Hayes looking to defend,
through the left-hander they go…

02:07:42.371 --> 02:07:43.789
And there's contact!

02:07:43.872 --> 02:07:46.625
Hayes is spun round and into the barrier.

02:07:46.708 --> 02:07:48.418
That's a big one.

02:07:48.502 --> 02:07:49.503
[gasping]

02:07:50.128 --> 02:07:52.464
-Fucking yes, yes, yes.
-Oh, no.

02:07:53.674 --> 02:07:54.675
Yeah, no. Ooh.

02:07:54.758 --> 02:07:56.427
[Brundle] There's debris
all over the race track

02:07:56.510 --> 02:07:58.929
and substantial damage to the barriers.

02:07:59.012 --> 02:08:02.182
The stewards have no choice
but to red flag this race.

02:08:02.266 --> 02:08:03.267
Miracle.

02:08:03.350 --> 02:08:05.102
[Croft] And speaking of damage, Martin,

02:08:05.185 --> 02:08:07.729
Hayes will only be allowed
to continue in this race

02:08:07.813 --> 02:08:11.024
if he can get his car
all the way around the circuit

02:08:11.108 --> 02:08:12.484
and back to the pit lane.

02:08:13.068 --> 02:08:15.320
[Hugh] Sonny. Sonny, can you get it back?

02:08:15.404 --> 02:08:18.115
I'll get it back. I'll get it back
if I have to push it back.

02:08:18.699 --> 02:08:23.120
Come on, Sonny. Nice and easy.

02:08:23.203 --> 02:08:25.706
[grunting]

02:08:25.789 --> 02:08:28.500
He's still going.
[chuckling] He's still going.

02:08:28.584 --> 02:08:30.002
[crew member] JP, red flag.

02:08:30.085 --> 02:08:31.295
Red flag. Come in.

02:08:31.378 --> 02:08:35.716
We are still alive, hermano. [laughs]

02:08:35.799 --> 02:08:37.426
Red flag!

02:08:37.509 --> 02:08:41.138
[Brundle] And somehow Sonny Hayes
has got his car back to the pit lane.

02:08:41.221 --> 02:08:43.390
-It's a miracle.
-I know! I know.

02:08:43.473 --> 02:08:44.766
Never seen one until now.

02:08:44.850 --> 02:08:48.270
Home free. Good girl. Let's go.

02:08:48.979 --> 02:08:49.980
New softs, both cars.

02:08:50.063 --> 02:08:52.524
Raise the tire pressure
for three quick laps.

02:08:52.608 --> 02:08:54.693
-Team, time to build a car.
-[crew cheers, clamors]

02:08:54.776 --> 02:08:56.153
[Croft] Red flag rules then.

02:08:56.236 --> 02:08:59.531
The teams can make changes.
They can make repairs to their cars.

02:08:59.615 --> 02:09:00.991
But only in that pit lane.

02:09:01.074 --> 02:09:05.996
And with only ten minutes to make repairs,
Apex GP has their work cut out.

02:09:06.496 --> 02:09:09.875
[Brundle] And all cars
can fit a fresh set of tires

02:09:09.958 --> 02:09:11.919
for what will be a three-lap sprint.

02:09:12.002 --> 02:09:14.922
-Dodge! Dodge, are we gonna make it?
-I don't know. I don't know.

02:09:20.761 --> 02:09:23.347
That was clean.
That wasn't me. Not this time.

02:09:23.430 --> 02:09:27.142
"Not this time"?
Tell that to the stewards.

02:09:27.226 --> 02:09:28.477
Check the replay.

02:09:29.520 --> 02:09:31.438
I got this. Lift that corner.

02:09:39.821 --> 02:09:42.574
I'm good. I'm good, I'm good. I'm good.

02:09:42.658 --> 02:09:44.201
[Brundle] What the stewards
will be looking at

02:09:44.284 --> 02:09:46.119
is whether Hayes went off completely

02:09:46.203 --> 02:09:50.165
or kept at least one tire on track
during the contact with Russell.

02:09:50.249 --> 02:09:51.959
-Yo, you good?
-Yeah, good.

02:09:52.042 --> 02:09:53.252
Listen, you were on track.

02:09:53.335 --> 02:09:56.380
Yeah, it was your corner.
P3 and P4. Let's go!

02:09:56.463 --> 02:10:00.425
[Croft] Given Hayes's reputation, they'll
be looking at this really, really closely.

02:10:00.509 --> 02:10:02.177
I'm not expecting a quick decision.

02:10:02.261 --> 02:10:03.762
Come on, that's clearly a penalty.

02:10:03.846 --> 02:10:05.764
Like… I mean,
not that that's what we want,

02:10:05.848 --> 02:10:09.476
but, like, objectively, that's the guy.

02:10:09.560 --> 02:10:12.229
-Oh, man. It can't end this way.
-It's just a time-out.

02:10:12.312 --> 02:10:16.316
Like the last 30 years.
It's in the hands of the racing gods now.

02:10:16.400 --> 02:10:18.235
We gotta believe. Gotta believe.

02:10:19.736 --> 02:10:21.822
[Croft] Plenty going on here in the pit.

02:10:21.905 --> 02:10:25.075
Oh, look. Here comes the new wing.
This is a massive job.

02:10:25.158 --> 02:10:29.121
Yeah, but will the car hold together
for the remaining three laps?

02:10:32.332 --> 02:10:34.293
Well, that barrier looks okay now.

02:10:34.376 --> 02:10:37.754
The marshals just sweeping
the last few bits of debris off the track,

02:10:37.838 --> 02:10:39.923
and the clock continues to tick down.

02:10:40.007 --> 02:10:43.927
[Brundle] Yeah, it's just over two minutes
until this race gets underway again.

02:11:04.907 --> 02:11:06.366
JP, JP!

02:11:07.659 --> 02:11:08.785
Three laps.

02:11:08.869 --> 02:11:10.287
Three laps is a lifetime.

02:11:10.370 --> 02:11:11.705
Go win this thing.

02:11:23.634 --> 02:11:26.220
Hey, Sonny. Sonny, you got a minute?

02:11:28.430 --> 02:11:29.473
We got you a car.

02:11:30.140 --> 02:11:32.893
Ah, you rock. Thank you.

02:11:35.479 --> 02:11:38.774
[Brundle] Because Apex GP
didn't make the top 10 in qualifying,

02:11:38.857 --> 02:11:41.652
they have a new set
of soft tires available,

02:11:41.735 --> 02:11:45.030
which will give them extra speed
over the cars ahead of them

02:11:45.113 --> 02:11:47.366
on the used soft tires.

02:11:47.449 --> 02:11:50.327
This red flag is a lifeline.

02:11:50.410 --> 02:11:52.746
You'd almost wonder
if Sonny didn't engineer it.

02:11:53.580 --> 02:11:56.375
But wait, we're the only cars
on fresh tires

02:11:56.458 --> 02:11:58.210
because we sucked in qualifying yesterday?

02:11:58.293 --> 02:11:59.962
Never got the chance to use them.

02:12:00.045 --> 02:12:02.297
Sometimes when you lose, you win.

02:12:02.381 --> 02:12:04.883
-That don't make no sense.
-It's a Sonny thing.

02:12:05.759 --> 02:12:07.761
[Croft] Light at the end of the pit lane
is green.

02:12:07.845 --> 02:12:11.014
We're off on our second formation lap
of the evening,

02:12:11.098 --> 02:12:14.685
and when this race resumes,
this is gonna be an epic sprint.

02:12:14.768 --> 02:12:17.771
Hamilton, Leclerc, Pearce, Hayes.
That's the top four.

02:12:42.004 --> 02:12:43.964
[Hugh] Sonny, we just heard
from the stewards.

02:12:44.047 --> 02:12:45.048
Goddamn it. Now?

02:12:45.132 --> 02:12:46.759
[Hugh] We're debating whether to tell you.

02:12:46.842 --> 02:12:49.011
Kaspar says, "Yes,"
but Kate says, "Don't."

02:12:49.094 --> 02:12:51.221
-She says you're fast when you're angry.
-[chuckles]

02:12:51.305 --> 02:12:53.307
-Tell her, "Job well done."
-[laughs]

02:12:53.390 --> 02:12:56.435
[Croft] And here's news.
Stewards have made their decision.

02:12:56.518 --> 02:13:01.857
That Lap 55 collision between Hayes
and Russell is ruled a racing incident.

02:13:01.940 --> 02:13:04.109
-No further investigation.
-[cheering]

02:13:04.193 --> 02:13:06.236
Whoa! Sonny.

02:13:09.114 --> 02:13:12.492
That was your line, Sonny.
Go finish your race.

02:13:15.662 --> 02:13:18.373
Joshua, we still got two cars in the mix.

02:13:18.457 --> 02:13:19.833
Then we've got a team.

02:13:21.001 --> 02:13:22.503
[Brundle] Once those red lights go out,

02:13:22.586 --> 02:13:25.506
this will be an absolute sprint
to the finish.

02:13:26.381 --> 02:13:28.884
Position advantage to Mercedes
and Ferrari.

02:13:28.967 --> 02:13:31.345
Tire advantage to Apex GP.

02:13:57.871 --> 02:13:59.498
Tell JP to follow my lead.

02:13:59.581 --> 02:14:01.375
[crew member]
Joshua, Sonny says to follow him.

02:14:01.458 --> 02:14:03.043
Follow? He's behind me.

02:14:05.295 --> 02:14:07.923
-Cheeky bastard.
-[Sonny] That's it. Stay with me.

02:14:16.974 --> 02:14:18.476
[crew member] He's giving you a tow.
Take it.

02:14:18.559 --> 02:14:19.685
All the way.

02:14:47.171 --> 02:14:49.214
Come on, kid. Get it. Come on!

02:14:49.298 --> 02:14:51.175
[Croft] Hayes plays the decoy,

02:14:51.258 --> 02:14:55.637
and Pearce rockets past Leclerc
and up into second.

02:14:55.721 --> 02:15:01.185
And Leclerc's in danger from Sonny Hayes.
Round the outside, he's up into P3.

02:15:01.268 --> 02:15:02.644
[Brundle] Perfect teamwork.

02:15:02.728 --> 02:15:06.440
Hayes and Pearce working together,
it's like racing ballet.

02:15:07.024 --> 02:15:08.650
[Croft] It's a beautiful sight,

02:15:08.734 --> 02:15:12.696
but now their sights are set on
the race leader, Lewis Hamilton.

02:15:13.197 --> 02:15:14.656
Yeah! Remember me?

02:15:24.249 --> 02:15:26.001
Come on, boys. Send it!

02:15:53.195 --> 02:15:54.404
Why didn't they overtake?

02:15:54.488 --> 02:15:56.073
Lewis will defend
whichever car attacks first.

02:15:56.156 --> 02:15:59.493
-But they both can't wait.
-Someone has to sacrifice.

02:16:04.790 --> 02:16:05.791
[Croft] Two onto one,

02:16:05.874 --> 02:16:08.460
and all the pressure is on Lewis Hamilton

02:16:08.544 --> 02:16:11.380
as Apex work as a pack.

02:16:12.381 --> 02:16:13.423
Go win it, kid.

02:16:13.507 --> 02:16:15.259
Hayes makes the first move.

02:16:15.342 --> 02:16:18.262
-Hamilton defends. Pearce attacks.
-Yeah!

02:16:18.345 --> 02:16:20.848
-And Pearce has P1.
-[crowd cheering]

02:16:20.931 --> 02:16:22.224
-Yes!
-Yes, yes!

02:16:24.101 --> 02:16:26.228
[Croft] Toe-to-toe, wheel-to-wheel,

02:16:26.311 --> 02:16:29.898
this is epic racing
to finish off the season.

02:16:29.982 --> 02:16:32.651
And Sonny Hayes and Lewis Hamilton
aren't done yet.

02:16:32.734 --> 02:16:34.695
Hamilton, on Sonny Hayes.

02:16:34.778 --> 02:16:36.154
-There's contact!
-[crowd clamors]

02:16:36.237 --> 02:16:38.115
And through goes Hamilton.

02:16:40.993 --> 02:16:43.244
-Yes, yes!
-Come on!

02:16:43.327 --> 02:16:44.327
Yes!

02:16:44.996 --> 02:16:47.457
Guys, talk to me.
Where's Sonny? Can he finish?

02:16:47.540 --> 02:16:50.043
[crew member] One more lap, JP.
Hamilton never backs down.

02:16:50.127 --> 02:16:52.004
Can Sonny finish the race, man?

02:16:52.087 --> 02:16:54.381
[crew member] Yes, he's on track.
Just watch Lewis when he fights.

02:16:54.464 --> 02:16:57.175
You're P1. No more risks.

02:16:57.259 --> 02:16:58.343
No such thing.

02:16:59.636 --> 02:17:03.348
[Croft] The rookie holds his line.
He won't back down.

02:17:03.432 --> 02:17:07.019
He's here to fight
the seven-time world champion.

02:17:10.772 --> 02:17:11.982
That made contact.

02:17:12.065 --> 02:17:16.236
The leader and Lewis Hamilton
are out of this race.

02:17:16.320 --> 02:17:20.365
[Brundle] Despite yellow flags flying
at turn one, this race will continue.

02:17:20.449 --> 02:17:22.825
[Hugh] Sonny, push, push, push.
You're P1! You're P1!

02:17:23.368 --> 02:17:25.870
[Brundle] Apex GP has only one lap to go.

02:17:25.954 --> 02:17:29.040
The question is do they have the car?

02:17:29.625 --> 02:17:30.959
We have the driver.

02:17:34.796 --> 02:17:37.049
[muffled] Yeah! Go on, Sonny!

02:17:46.475 --> 02:17:48.184
[breathing heavily]

02:18:22.218 --> 02:18:23.218
What's happening?

02:18:23.887 --> 02:18:25.222
He's flying.

02:18:50.371 --> 02:18:52.290
[Hugh] Sonny, you did it! We won! We won!

02:18:52.374 --> 02:18:53.375
[crew cheering]

02:18:53.458 --> 02:18:55.043
Yeah!

02:18:59.840 --> 02:19:01.549
Yes!

02:19:06.305 --> 02:19:07.305
Yeah!

02:19:07.388 --> 02:19:09.099
[cheers]

02:19:11.894 --> 02:19:13.019
We won!

02:19:13.102 --> 02:19:15.981
-Yeah!
-[cheering continues]

02:19:18.901 --> 02:19:19.942
Yeah!

02:19:21.486 --> 02:19:22.779
We won!

02:19:24.656 --> 02:19:28.660
-We did it! Whoo!
-Oh, my God. Oh, my God.

02:19:29.995 --> 02:19:32.706
Thank you. Thank you. Thank you.

02:19:37.044 --> 02:19:39.504
-Come on! Yes!
-Yes!

02:19:50.807 --> 02:19:53.143
Means another three years
for Ruben, right?

02:19:54.853 --> 02:19:55.854
Yeah.

02:19:56.647 --> 02:19:58.524
I guess we'll check back about that deal.

02:20:01.485 --> 02:20:03.362
Presuming you're still on the board.

02:20:12.663 --> 02:20:16.458
[Croft] Breathtaking!
Breathless! Incredible!

02:20:16.542 --> 02:20:19.336
What an Abu Dhabi Grand Prix
this has been!

02:20:19.419 --> 02:20:21.421
What a victory as well!

02:20:21.505 --> 02:20:25.843
[Brundle] Absolutely. It's a race
for the ages. An absolute thriller.

02:20:25.926 --> 02:20:29.429
-And this man wins his first Grand Prix.
-Well done.

02:20:29.513 --> 02:20:31.223
-It's been 30 years in the making.
-Well done!

02:20:31.306 --> 02:20:34.601
And the team did a brilliant job
from the pit wall.

02:20:34.685 --> 02:20:38.105
-And of course we can't forget Pearce…
-Oi! What you smiling about?

02:20:38.188 --> 02:20:40.566
-…playing his part in this victory.
-[Sonny] You.

02:20:40.649 --> 02:20:43.026
I'm gonna win a million races.
You should at least have one.

02:20:43.110 --> 02:20:44.820
[Sonny laughing]

02:20:45.529 --> 02:20:46.947
We did it.

02:20:47.573 --> 02:20:48.949
[Sonny] Yeah, we did.

02:20:52.244 --> 02:20:53.871
[exclaims]

02:20:53.954 --> 02:20:54.955
Whoo!

02:20:57.708 --> 02:20:59.042
[sighs]

02:21:02.754 --> 02:21:03.839
[spectator] Sonny!

02:21:03.922 --> 02:21:05.340
No, no, no, no. Give it to him.

02:21:06.216 --> 02:21:07.718
No, no, no. Give it to him.

02:21:10.429 --> 02:21:12.764
Oh, my God. Thank you. Thank you.

02:21:17.519 --> 02:21:20.939
[cheering]

02:21:25.402 --> 02:21:27.237
Let's go!

02:21:28.322 --> 02:21:29.323
[mutters]

02:21:29.406 --> 02:21:31.033
[kisses] I love you.

02:21:38.999 --> 02:21:40.876
Yeah!

02:21:40.959 --> 02:21:43.045
Today we get to say…

02:21:43.128 --> 02:21:45.768
-"We are the best in the world!"
-"We are the best in the world!"

02:21:46.256 --> 02:21:48.550
[cheering]

02:22:08.654 --> 02:22:10.155
[cheering continues]

02:22:17.829 --> 02:22:19.831
[dramatic music playing]

02:22:24.753 --> 02:22:26.755
[breathing heavily]

02:22:37.474 --> 02:22:41.144
[breathing heavily]

02:22:52.739 --> 02:22:55.993
[cheering]

02:22:56.076 --> 02:22:57.077
Joshua.

02:22:57.160 --> 02:22:59.621
If you were ever to consider
to drive somewhere else,

02:22:59.705 --> 02:23:00.706
you know where to find me.

02:23:00.789 --> 02:23:04.418
Thanks, Toto, but I'm happy where I am.

02:23:05.127 --> 02:23:06.378
Congratulations.

02:23:08.839 --> 02:23:10.924
Yeah, baby! Let them wait!

02:23:11.008 --> 02:23:12.801
-Let them wait!
-[laughs]

02:23:12.885 --> 02:23:14.469
-[exclaims]
-[screams]

02:23:16.471 --> 02:23:17.639
[Ruben] The cup!

02:23:17.723 --> 02:23:20.517
Kate, you built a hell of a car.

02:23:20.601 --> 02:23:22.019
[chuckles]

02:23:24.396 --> 02:23:27.399
-[crowd exclaiming, chattering]
-[breathing heavily]

02:23:42.289 --> 02:23:43.290
[sighs]

02:24:02.309 --> 02:24:05.479
[panting]

02:24:14.238 --> 02:24:15.322
[chuckles]

02:24:16.031 --> 02:24:17.115
[chuckles]

02:24:24.164 --> 02:24:25.999
[Kate] Another race I don't know about?

02:24:27.751 --> 02:24:28.752
Somewhere.

02:24:30.420 --> 02:24:32.089
That beats this? [chuckles]

02:24:35.759 --> 02:24:36.760
Yeah.

02:24:40.264 --> 02:24:43.183
I wanted to say, "See you down the road,"

02:24:43.267 --> 02:24:45.769
but in a way that was more poetic.

02:24:48.605 --> 02:24:49.606
So…

02:24:51.984 --> 02:24:53.527
Can I see you down the road?

02:24:59.157 --> 02:25:00.158
Yes.

02:25:02.286 --> 02:25:03.537
[chuckles]

02:25:16.216 --> 02:25:17.968
Hang on to that until then.

02:25:20.137 --> 02:25:21.972
Okay. [chuckles]

02:25:25.350 --> 02:25:26.727
And drive fast.

02:25:26.810 --> 02:25:28.437
[Sonny chuckles]

02:25:36.737 --> 02:25:38.497
[Joshua] And where do you
think you're going?

02:25:39.156 --> 02:25:41.825
[chuckles] Don't worry about me.
Go celebrate.

02:25:41.909 --> 02:25:43.410
But you're off to where?

02:25:43.911 --> 02:25:46.538
You know, couple more dragons to slay.

02:25:47.039 --> 02:25:48.457
It's your team now.

02:25:51.251 --> 02:25:52.669
It was always my team.

02:25:52.753 --> 02:25:55.964
[both chuckle]

02:25:56.048 --> 02:25:57.216
I'll be watching.

02:25:58.592 --> 02:26:00.052
See you around, swan.

02:26:02.012 --> 02:26:04.848
[laughs]

02:26:04.932 --> 02:26:06.934
[dramatic music playing]

02:26:08.268 --> 02:26:09.269
[sighs]

02:26:43.220 --> 02:26:44.221
[music stops]

02:26:48.016 --> 02:26:50.269
["Hablando de Mí" playing on radio]

02:27:00.529 --> 02:27:02.573
[engine revving]

02:27:15.752 --> 02:27:16.753
Hello!

02:27:18.046 --> 02:27:19.089
[in Spanish] Buenas.

02:27:23.051 --> 02:27:24.531
I'm told you're looking for a driver.

02:27:25.804 --> 02:27:27.181
What's your name?

02:27:28.140 --> 02:27:29.391
Sonny Hayes.

02:27:33.854 --> 02:27:35.522
Have you ever driven Baja?

02:27:36.648 --> 02:27:37.649
Nope.

02:27:38.442 --> 02:27:39.651
We can't pay much.

02:27:40.235 --> 02:27:41.528
Not about the money.

02:27:46.283 --> 02:27:47.659
So what is it about?

02:27:49.369 --> 02:27:51.205
[chuckles]

02:27:51.288 --> 02:27:53.040
[rock music playing]

02:27:53.123 --> 02:27:55.751
♪ Hey ♪

02:27:55.834 --> 02:27:57.836
[engine revving]

02:28:00.923 --> 02:28:02.382
♪ Hey ♪

02:28:07.387 --> 02:28:09.890
♪ Flying through the city
With the speakers up loud ♪

02:28:09.973 --> 02:28:12.476
♪ Speeding by with the top down ♪

02:28:13.185 --> 02:28:15.771
♪ Fast lane living
Till they put me in the ground ♪

02:28:15.854 --> 02:28:17.898
♪ And I don't wanna stop now ♪

02:28:18.649 --> 02:28:21.318
♪ Pull away, wind blowing
Now I'm cruising ♪

02:28:21.401 --> 02:28:24.571
♪ Put the past in the past
A new day is coming ♪

02:28:24.655 --> 02:28:27.491
♪ Ha-la-lay-la, we can ride ♪

02:28:27.574 --> 02:28:30.494
♪ Four wheels, you and I
Gotta get out of here ♪

02:28:30.577 --> 02:28:34.456
♪ Ha-la-lay-la, my savior ♪

02:28:36.250 --> 02:28:39.294
♪ Ha-la-lay-la, we can fly ♪

02:28:39.378 --> 02:28:42.130
♪ Out of this burning fire
Just take me anywhere ♪

02:28:42.214 --> 02:28:45.968
♪ Ha-la-lay-la, my savior ♪

02:28:46.051 --> 02:28:48.220
♪ Pedal down and drive ♪

02:28:50.013 --> 02:28:51.348
♪ Drive ♪

02:28:51.890 --> 02:28:53.600
♪ Pedal down and ♪

02:28:53.684 --> 02:28:57.062
♪ Drive ♪

02:28:58.772 --> 02:29:02.526
♪ Just drive ♪

02:29:05.237 --> 02:29:07.823
♪ Out of the city
Now we're switching four lanes ♪

02:29:07.906 --> 02:29:10.117
♪ Got our eyes on a fresh start ♪

02:29:10.868 --> 02:29:13.620
♪ The world as we knew it
That was caught up in flames ♪

02:29:13.704 --> 02:29:15.789
♪ Get ready for the next part ♪

02:29:16.331 --> 02:29:19.251
♪ You know I'm good
If I'm back in the gutter ♪

02:29:19.334 --> 02:29:22.504
♪ 'Cause this life
It was never about the money ♪

02:29:22.588 --> 02:29:25.424
♪ Ha-la-lay-la, we can ride ♪

02:29:25.507 --> 02:29:28.427
♪ Four wheels, you and I
Gotta get out of here ♪

02:29:28.510 --> 02:29:32.222
♪ Ha-la-lay-la, my savior ♪

02:29:34.099 --> 02:29:36.935
♪ Ha-la-lay-la, we can fly ♪

02:29:37.019 --> 02:29:39.938
♪ Out of this, good and far
Just take me anywhere ♪

02:29:40.022 --> 02:29:43.901
♪ Ha-la-lay-la, my savior ♪

